    • dev - Tables supporting compilation of programs
      • dev.arch - System architecture

      • dev.htmlentity - Known HTML entity strings & codes
      • dev.include - A site where one file includes another
      • dev.license - Source code license
      • dev.linelim -

      • dev.msgfile - File in repo containing messages that should be normalized during CI
      • dev.noindent - Indicates that a file should not be automatically indented
      • dev.opt_type - Type of option (used in tool_opt)
      • dev.package - OpenACR package

      • dev.pkgkey - Keys belonging to the OpenACR package
      • dev.readme - File containing documentation

      • dev.scriptfile - Known script file
      • dev.srcfile - Source file or header (key is pathname)

    • dmmeta - Tables holding metadata (data model meta)
      • dmmeta.anonfld - Omit field name where possible (command line, enums, constants)
      • dmmeta.argvtype - Customize parsing of command lines (rarely used)
      • dmmeta.basepool - Specify pool to be used for allocating elements of a type
      • dmmeta.bitfld - Specify offset/width of a bitfield within another field
      • dmmeta.cafter - Control amc processing order for unrelated types (used in rare situations)
      • dmmeta.cascdel - Request cascading delete of referenced rows
      • dmmeta.ccmp - Generate hash function
      • dmmeta.cdflt - Specify default value for single-value types that lack fields
      • dmmeta.cextern - Externally defined ctype (a struct from system header, or from a c++ library)
      • dmmeta.cfast - FAST properties for ctype
      • dmmeta.cfmt - Specify options for printing/reading ctypes into multiple formats
      • dmmeta.cget - Generate state functions for these ctypes
      • dmmeta.charset - Generate functions to determine if a character is a member of a set
      • dmmeta.chash - Generate hash function
      • dmmeta.cppfunc - Value of field provided by this expression
      • dmmeta.cppkeyword - Built-in C++ keyword
      • dmmeta.cpptype - Specify whether a ctype can be passed by value, and other c++ options
      • dmmeta.csize - Specify size/alignment for built-in C++ types
      • dmmeta.cstr - Specify that type behaves like a string
      • dmmeta.ctype - Struct
      • dmmeta.ctypelen - Size of Ctype
      • dmmeta.dispatch - Generate code for a multi-way branch
      • dmmeta.dispatch_msg - Add message to a dispatch
      • dmmeta.dispctx - Use context with dispatch
      • dmmeta.dispfilter - Generate filter function on dispatch
      • dmmeta.dispsig - Cryptographic signature of all dispatches
      • dmmeta.dispsigcheck - Check signature of input data against executable’s version
      • dmmeta.disptrace - Generate trace fields (cycles, counts) for all dispatch branches
      • dmmeta.falias - Alias field
      • dmmeta.fastenc -
      • dmmeta.fastinstr -
      • dmmeta.fastop -
      • dmmeta.fbase - Customize imported Base fields
      • dmmeta.fbigend - Annotate field as having big-endian storage
      • dmmeta.fbitset - Generate bitset functions over integer field or array
      • dmmeta.fbuf - Buffer for reading/writing messages, works with Iohook
      • dmmeta.fbufdir - Buffer direction (in,out)
      • dmmeta.fbuftype - Buffer type
      • dmmeta.fcast - Generate implicit conversion from field to c++ expression
      • dmmeta.fcleanup - Request user-implemented function to be called at Uninit time for a field
      • dmmeta.fcmap - Bidirectional mapping between fconst values
      • dmmeta.fcmdline - Annotate field that holds process command line
      • dmmeta.fcmp - Request versionsort or case-insensitive sort for field
      • dmmeta.fcompact - Request compaction upon removal from index
      • dmmeta.fconst - Specify enum value (integer + string constant) for a field
      • dmmeta.fcurs - Request generation of custom cursor
      • dmmeta.fdec - Specify that field has an implied # of decimal places and specify formatting options
      • dmmeta.fdelay - Control elapsed time between execution of a step
      • dmmeta.ffast - FAST properties for field
      • dmmeta.fflag - Options for command-line flags
      • dmmeta.field - Specify field of a struct
      • dmmeta.findrem - Request generation of FindRemove function
      • dmmeta.finput - Describe input table of a program
      • dmmeta.fldoffset - Assert field offset - will result in compile-time error if violated
      • dmmeta.floadtuples - Request that process automatically load any input tables on startup
      • dmmeta.fnoremove - Omit any functions for removing elements from table; Table is append-only
      • dmmeta.foutput - Generate function to save index/table back to disk
      • dmmeta.fprefix - Mapping between field prefix and Reftype
      • dmmeta.fregx - Specify options for command-line regx field
      • dmmeta.fsort - Generate custom sort function for array field
      • dmmeta.fstep - Generate a main loop step to be executed whenever a field is non-empty
      • dmmeta.ftrace - Generate cycle/step counting fields for a step
      • dmmeta.ftuple -
      • dmmeta.func -
      • dmmeta.funique - This field must be unique in the table. Not needed for primary key
      • dmmeta.fuserinit - Add user-defined initialization function for field (see fcleanup)
      • dmmeta.fwddecl - Request forward declaration of a field
      • dmmeta.gconst - Import ssim table columns as fconst for a field
      • dmmeta.gstatic - Load entries for this table at startup time
      • dmmeta.gsymbol - Create C++ symbols from entries in ssim table
      • dmmeta.hashtype - Hash function type
      • dmmeta.hook - Required on Hook fields
      • dmmeta.inlary - Generate inline array of fixed or variable length (all entries fit within parent struct)
      • dmmeta.lenfld - Specify which gives length of varlen portion in bytes
      • dmmeta.listtype - Specify structure of linked list based on field prefix
      • dmmeta.llist - Options for Llist field
      • dmmeta.logcat - Log category
      • dmmeta.main - Generate Main function for namespace
      • dmmeta.msgtype - Specify message type for each eligible message, controls dispatch
      • dmmeta.nocascdel - Remove cascade delete for this index
      • dmmeta.nossimfile - Indicates that ssimfile does not exist for this ssimdb ctype
      • dmmeta.noxref - Explicitly specify that no x-ref exists between tables (don’t use unless forced)
      • dmmeta.ns - Namespace (for in-memory database, protocol, etc)
      • dmmeta.nscpp - Generate C++ code for this namespace
      • dmmeta.nsdb - Annotate ssimdb namespaces
      • dmmeta.nsfast - Whether namespace is FAST
      • dmmeta.nsinclude - Explicitly specify a C++ include file for namespace
      • dmmeta.nsjs - Generate JavaScript code for this namespace
      • dmmeta.nsproto - Annotate protocol namespace (collection of types, no state)
      • dmmeta.nstype - Namespace type
      • dmmeta.nsversion - Namespace version
      • dmmeta.nsx - Control code-generation and exception handling options for process/library
      • dmmeta.numstr - Add functions to read numbers out of a string field
      • dmmeta.pack - Request byte-packing of structure fields
      • dmmeta.pmaskfld - Specify which field holds presence mask bits (one for each field in struct)
      • dmmeta.pmaskfld_member - Explicit field-to-pmask association
      • dmmeta.pnew - Generate custom constructor (placement new), for use with binary protocols
      • dmmeta.pnewtype - Type of fbuf
      • dmmeta.printfmt - Print format
      • dmmeta.ptrary - Required for fields with reftype:Ptrary
      • dmmeta.reftype - Field type constructor (e.g. reference type)
      • dmmeta.rowid - Initialize field to row id of element
      • dmmeta.smallstr - Generated fixed-length padded or length-delimited string field
      • dmmeta.sortfld - Specify what field an index (Bheap,Atree) is sorted on
      • dmmeta.sorttype - Sort type
      • dmmeta.sqltype - Mapping of ctype -> SQL expression
      • dmmeta.ssimfile - File with ssim tuples
      • dmmeta.ssimreq - Extended constraints for ssim records
      • dmmeta.ssimsort - Define sort order for ssimfile
      • dmmeta.ssimvolatile - Types based on ssim files marked this way cannot be cross-referenced
      • dmmeta.steptype - Type of scheduler step
      • dmmeta.strfmt - Cfmt conversion type (misnomer, not necessarily a string)
      • dmmeta.strtype - Type of small string
      • dmmeta.substr - Specify that the field value is computed from a substring of another field
      • dmmeta.svtype - Table for determining ctype from separated value file
      • dmmeta.tary - Indirect linear dynamically alocated array (used for strings, arrays of data, etc)
      • dmmeta.thash - Hash index, required for fields with reftype Thash
      • dmmeta.tracefld - Trace fields
      • dmmeta.tracerec - Trace record
      • dmmeta.typefld - Specifies which field of a message carries the type
      • dmmeta.usertracefld - Add custom user trace fields to process’s trace struct
      • dmmeta.xref - Specify how to cross-reference (i.e. project, or group-by) one record with another

  198// --- wcli.FDb.tuples.Alloc
  199// Allocate memory for new default row.
  200// If out of memory, process is killed.
  201wcli::FTuples& wcli::tuples_Alloc() {
  202    wcli::FTuples* row = tuples_AllocMaybe();
  203    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
  204        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.tuples  comment:'Alloc failed'");
  205    }
  206    return *row;
  207}

  209// --- wcli.FDb.tuples.AllocMaybe
  210// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
  211wcli::FTuples* wcli::tuples_AllocMaybe() {
  212    wcli::FTuples *row = (wcli::FTuples*)tuples_AllocMem();
  213    if (row) {
  214        new (row) wcli::FTuples; // call constructor
  215    }
  216    return row;
  217}
  218
  219// --- wcli.FDb.tuples.AllocMem
  220// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
  221void* wcli::tuples_AllocMem() {
  222    u64 new_nelems     = _db.tuples_n+1;
  223    // compute level and index on level
  224    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
  225    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
  226    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
  227    void *ret = NULL;
  228    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
  229    wcli::FTuples*  lev   = NULL;
  230    if (bsr < 32) {
  231        lev = _db.tuples_lary[bsr];
  232        if (!lev) {
  233            lev=(wcli::FTuples*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FTuples) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
  234            _db.tuples_lary[bsr] = lev;
  235        }
  236    }
  237    // allocate element from this level
  238    if (lev) {
  239        _db.tuples_n = i32(new_nelems);
  240        ret = lev + index;
  241    }
  242    return ret;
  243}
  244
  245// --- wcli.FDb.tuples.RemoveAll
  246// Remove all elements from Lary
  247void wcli::tuples_RemoveAll() {
  248    for (u64 n = _db.tuples_n; n>0; ) {
  249        n--;
  250        tuples_qFind(u64(n)).~FTuples(); // destroy last element
  251        _db.tuples_n = i32(n);
  252    }
  253}
  254
  255// --- wcli.FDb.tuples.RemoveLast
  256// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
  257void wcli::tuples_RemoveLast() {
  258    u64 n = _db.tuples_n;
  259    if (n > 0) {
  260        n -= 1;
  261        tuples_qFind(u64(n)).~FTuples();
  262        _db.tuples_n = i32(n);
  263    }
  264}

  270    bool retval = true;
  271    (void)row;

  312        }

  343// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdc.XrefMaybe
  344// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
  345// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
  346bool wcli::wclicmdc_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdc &row) {
  347    bool retval = true;
  348    (void)row;
  349    // insert wclicmdc into index ind_wclicmdc
  350    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
  351        bool success = ind_wclicmdc_InsertMaybe(row);
  352        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
  353            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
  354            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdc"; // check for duplicate key
  355            return false;
  356        }
  357    }
  358    return retval;
  359}
  360
  361// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdc.Find
  362// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
  363wcli::FWclicmdc* wcli::ind_wclicmdc_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
  364    u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_wclicmdc_buckets_n - 1);
  365    wcli::FWclicmdc* *e = &_db.ind_wclicmdc_buckets_elems[index];
  366    wcli::FWclicmdc* ret=NULL;
  367    do {
  368        ret       = *e;
  369        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wclicmdc == key;
  370        if (done) break;
  371        e         = &ret->ind_wclicmdc_next;
  372    } while (true);
  373    return ret;
  374}
  375
  376// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdc.FindX
  377// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
  378wcli::FWclicmdc& wcli::ind_wclicmdc_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
  379    wcli::FWclicmdc* ret = ind_wclicmdc_Find(key);
  380    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_wclicmdc  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
  381    return *ret;
  382}
  383
  384// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdc.GetOrCreate
  385// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
  386wcli::FWclicmdc& wcli::ind_wclicmdc_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
  387    wcli::FWclicmdc* ret = ind_wclicmdc_Find(key);
  388    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
  389        ret         = &wclicmdc_Alloc();
  390        (*ret).wclicmdc = key;
  391        bool good = wclicmdc_XrefMaybe(*ret);
  392        if (!good) {
  393            wclicmdc_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
  394            ret = NULL;
  395        }
  396    }
  397    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_wclicmdc  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
  398    return *ret;
  399}
  400
  401// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdc.InsertMaybe
  402// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
  403bool wcli::ind_wclicmdc_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdc& row) {
  404    ind_wclicmdc_Reserve(1);
  405    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
  406    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wclicmdc_next == (wcli::FWclicmdc*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
  407        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdc) & (_db.ind_wclicmdc_buckets_n - 1);
  408        wcli::FWclicmdc* *prev = &_db.ind_wclicmdc_buckets_elems[index];
  409        do {
  410            wcli::FWclicmdc* ret = *prev;
  411            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
  412                break;
  413            }
  414            if ((*ret).wclicmdc == row.wclicmdc) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
  415                retval = false;
  416                break;
  417            }
  418            prev = &ret->ind_wclicmdc_next;
  419        } while (true);
  420        if (retval) {
  421            row.ind_wclicmdc_next = *prev;
  422            _db.ind_wclicmdc_n++;
  423            *prev = &row;
  424        }
  425    }
  426    return retval;
  427}
  428
  429// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdc.Remove
  430// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
  431void wcli::ind_wclicmdc_Remove(wcli::FWclicmdc& row) {
  432    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wclicmdc_next != (wcli::FWclicmdc*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
  433        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdc) & (_db.ind_wclicmdc_buckets_n - 1);
  434        wcli::FWclicmdc* *prev = &_db.ind_wclicmdc_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
  435        while (wcli::FWclicmdc *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
  436            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
  437                *prev = next->ind_wclicmdc_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
  438                _db.ind_wclicmdc_n--;
  439                row.ind_wclicmdc_next = (wcli::FWclicmdc*)-1;// not-in-hash
  440                break;
  441            }
  442            prev = &next->ind_wclicmdc_next;
  443        }
  444    }
  445}
  446
  447// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdc.Reserve
  448// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
  449void wcli::ind_wclicmdc_Reserve(int n) {
  450    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wclicmdc_buckets_n;
  451    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wclicmdc_n + n;
  452    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
  453    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
  454        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
  455        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdc*);
  456        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdc*);
  457        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
  458        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
  459        wcli::FWclicmdc* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWclicmdc**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
  460        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
  461            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdc");
  462        }
  463        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
  464        // rehash all entries
  465        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wclicmdc_buckets_n; i++) {
  466            wcli::FWclicmdc* elem = _db.ind_wclicmdc_buckets_elems[i];
  467            while (elem) {
  468                wcli::FWclicmdc &row        = *elem;
  469                wcli::FWclicmdc* next       = row.ind_wclicmdc_next;
  470                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdc) & (new_nbuckets-1);
  471                row.ind_wclicmdc_next     = new_buckets[index];
  472                new_buckets[index] = &row;
  473                elem               = next;
  474            }
  475        }
  476        // free old array
  477        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wclicmdc_buckets_elems, old_size);
  478        _db.ind_wclicmdc_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
  479        _db.ind_wclicmdc_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
  480    }
  481}
  482
  483// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf.Alloc
  484// Allocate memory for new default row.
  485// If out of memory, process is killed.
  486wcli::FWclicmdf& wcli::wclicmdf_Alloc() {
  487    wcli::FWclicmdf* row = wclicmdf_AllocMaybe();
  488    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
  489        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.wclicmdf  comment:'Alloc failed'");
  490    }
  491    return *row;
  492}
  493
  494// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf.AllocMaybe
  495// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
  496wcli::FWclicmdf* wcli::wclicmdf_AllocMaybe() {
  497    wcli::FWclicmdf *row = (wcli::FWclicmdf*)wclicmdf_AllocMem();
  498    if (row) {
  499        new (row) wcli::FWclicmdf; // call constructor
  500    }
  501    return row;
  502}
  503
  504// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf.AllocMem
  505// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
  506void* wcli::wclicmdf_AllocMem() {
  507    u64 new_nelems     = _db.wclicmdf_n+1;
  508    // compute level and index on level
  509    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
  510    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
  511    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
  512    void *ret = NULL;
  513    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
  514    wcli::FWclicmdf*  lev   = NULL;
  515    if (bsr < 32) {
  516        lev = _db.wclicmdf_lary[bsr];
  517        if (!lev) {
  518            lev=(wcli::FWclicmdf*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdf) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
  519            _db.wclicmdf_lary[bsr] = lev;
  520        }
  521    }
  522    // allocate element from this level
  523    if (lev) {
  524        _db.wclicmdf_n = i32(new_nelems);
  525        ret = lev + index;
  526    }
  527    return ret;
  528}
  529
  530// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf.RemoveAll
  531// Remove all elements from Lary
  532void wcli::wclicmdf_RemoveAll() {
  533    for (u64 n = _db.wclicmdf_n; n>0; ) {
  534        n--;
  535        wclicmdf_qFind(u64(n)).~FWclicmdf(); // destroy last element
  536        _db.wclicmdf_n = i32(n);
  537    }
  538}
  539
  540// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf.RemoveLast
  541// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
  542void wcli::wclicmdf_RemoveLast() {
  543    u64 n = _db.wclicmdf_n;
  544    if (n > 0) {
  545        n -= 1;
  546        wclicmdf_qFind(u64(n)).~FWclicmdf();
  547        _db.wclicmdf_n = i32(n);
  548    }
  549}
  550
  551// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf.XrefMaybe
  552// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
  553// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
  554bool wcli::wclicmdf_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdf &row) {
  555    bool retval = true;
  556    (void)row;
  557    // insert wclicmdf into index ind_wclicmdf
  558    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
  559        bool success = ind_wclicmdf_InsertMaybe(row);
  560        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
  561            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
  562            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdf"; // check for duplicate key
  563            return false;
  564        }
  565    }
  566    return retval;
  567}
  568
  569// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdf.Find
  570// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
  571wcli::FWclicmdf* wcli::ind_wclicmdf_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
  572    u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_wclicmdf_buckets_n - 1);
  573    wcli::FWclicmdf* *e = &_db.ind_wclicmdf_buckets_elems[index];
  574    wcli::FWclicmdf* ret=NULL;
  575    do {
  576        ret       = *e;
  577        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wclicmdf == key;
  578        if (done) break;
  579        e         = &ret->ind_wclicmdf_next;
  580    } while (true);
  581    return ret;
  582}
  583
  584// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdf.FindX
  585// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
  586wcli::FWclicmdf& wcli::ind_wclicmdf_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
  587    wcli::FWclicmdf* ret = ind_wclicmdf_Find(key);
  588    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_wclicmdf  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
  589    return *ret;
  590}
  591
  592// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdf.GetOrCreate
  593// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
  594wcli::FWclicmdf& wcli::ind_wclicmdf_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
  595    wcli::FWclicmdf* ret = ind_wclicmdf_Find(key);
  596    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
  597        ret         = &wclicmdf_Alloc();
  598        (*ret).wclicmdf = key;
  599        bool good = wclicmdf_XrefMaybe(*ret);
  600        if (!good) {
  601            wclicmdf_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
  602            ret = NULL;
  603        }
  604    }
  605    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_wclicmdf  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
  606    return *ret;
  607}

  609// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdf.InsertMaybe
  610// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
  611bool wcli::ind_wclicmdf_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdf& row) {
  612    ind_wclicmdf_Reserve(1);
  613    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
  614    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wclicmdf_next == (wcli::FWclicmdf*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
  615        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdf) & (_db.ind_wclicmdf_buckets_n - 1);
  616        wcli::FWclicmdf* *prev = &_db.ind_wclicmdf_buckets_elems[index];
  617        do {
  618            wcli::FWclicmdf* ret = *prev;
  619            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
  620                break;
  621            }
  622            if ((*ret).wclicmdf == row.wclicmdf) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
  623                retval = false;
  624                break;
  625            }
  626            prev = &ret->ind_wclicmdf_next;
  627        } while (true);
  628        if (retval) {
  629            row.ind_wclicmdf_next = *prev;
  630            _db.ind_wclicmdf_n++;
  631            *prev = &row;
  632        }
  633    }
  634    return retval;
  635}

  637// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdf.Remove
  638// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
  639void wcli::ind_wclicmdf_Remove(wcli::FWclicmdf& row) {
  640    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wclicmdf_next != (wcli::FWclicmdf*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
  641        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdf) & (_db.ind_wclicmdf_buckets_n - 1);
  642        wcli::FWclicmdf* *prev = &_db.ind_wclicmdf_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
  643        while (wcli::FWclicmdf *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
  644            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
  645                *prev = next->ind_wclicmdf_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
  646                _db.ind_wclicmdf_n--;
  647                row.ind_wclicmdf_next = (wcli::FWclicmdf*)-1;// not-in-hash
  648                break;
  649            }
  650            prev = &next->ind_wclicmdf_next;
  651        }
  652    }
  653}

  655// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdf.Reserve
  656// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
  657void wcli::ind_wclicmdf_Reserve(int n) {
  658    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wclicmdf_buckets_n;
  659    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wclicmdf_n + n;
  660    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
  661    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
  662        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
  663        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdf*);
  664        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdf*);
  665        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
  666        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
  667        wcli::FWclicmdf* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWclicmdf**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
  668        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
  669            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdf");
  670        }
  671        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
  672        // rehash all entries
  673        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wclicmdf_buckets_n; i++) {
  674            wcli::FWclicmdf* elem = _db.ind_wclicmdf_buckets_elems[i];
  675            while (elem) {
  676                wcli::FWclicmdf &row        = *elem;
  677                wcli::FWclicmdf* next       = row.ind_wclicmdf_next;
  678                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdf) & (new_nbuckets-1);
  679                row.ind_wclicmdf_next     = new_buckets[index];
  680                new_buckets[index] = &row;
  681                elem               = next;
  682            }
  683        }
  684        // free old array
  685        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wclicmdf_buckets_elems, old_size);
  686        _db.ind_wclicmdf_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
  687        _db.ind_wclicmdf_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
  688    }
  689}

  691// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf2j.Alloc
  692// Allocate memory for new default row.
  693// If out of memory, process is killed.
  694wcli::FWclicmdf2j& wcli::wclicmdf2j_Alloc() {
  695    wcli::FWclicmdf2j* row = wclicmdf2j_AllocMaybe();
  696    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
  697        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.wclicmdf2j  comment:'Alloc failed'");
  698    }
  699    return *row;
  700}
  701
  702// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf2j.AllocMaybe
  703// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
  704wcli::FWclicmdf2j* wcli::wclicmdf2j_AllocMaybe() {
  705    wcli::FWclicmdf2j *row = (wcli::FWclicmdf2j*)wclicmdf2j_AllocMem();
  706    if (row) {
  707        new (row) wcli::FWclicmdf2j; // call constructor
  708    }
  709    return row;
  710}
  711
  712// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf2j.InsertMaybe
  713// Create new row from struct.
  714// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
  715wcli::FWclicmdf2j* wcli::wclicmdf2j_InsertMaybe(const wclidb::Wclicmdf2j &value) {
  716    wcli::FWclicmdf2j *row = &wclicmdf2j_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
  717    wclicmdf2j_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<wclidb::Wclicmdf2j&>(value));
  718    bool ok = wclicmdf2j_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
  719    if (!ok) {
  720        wclicmdf2j_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
  721        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
  722    }
  723    return row;
  724}
  725
  726// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf2j.AllocMem
  727// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
  728void* wcli::wclicmdf2j_AllocMem() {
  729    u64 new_nelems     = _db.wclicmdf2j_n+1;
  730    // compute level and index on level
  731    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
  732    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
  733    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
  734    void *ret = NULL;
  735    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
  736    wcli::FWclicmdf2j*  lev   = NULL;
  737    if (bsr < 32) {
  738        lev = _db.wclicmdf2j_lary[bsr];
  739        if (!lev) {
  740            lev=(wcli::FWclicmdf2j*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdf2j) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
  741            _db.wclicmdf2j_lary[bsr] = lev;
  742        }
  743    }
  744    // allocate element from this level
  745    if (lev) {
  746        _db.wclicmdf2j_n = i32(new_nelems);
  747        ret = lev + index;
  748    }
  749    return ret;
  750}
  751
  752// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf2j.RemoveAll
  753// Remove all elements from Lary
  754void wcli::wclicmdf2j_RemoveAll() {
  755    for (u64 n = _db.wclicmdf2j_n; n>0; ) {
  756        n--;
  757        wclicmdf2j_qFind(u64(n)).~FWclicmdf2j(); // destroy last element
  758        _db.wclicmdf2j_n = i32(n);
  759    }
  760}
  761
  762// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf2j.RemoveLast
  763// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
  764void wcli::wclicmdf2j_RemoveLast() {
  765    u64 n = _db.wclicmdf2j_n;
  766    if (n > 0) {
  767        n -= 1;
  768        wclicmdf2j_qFind(u64(n)).~FWclicmdf2j();
  769        _db.wclicmdf2j_n = i32(n);
  770    }
  771}
  772
  773// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf2j.InputMaybe
  774static bool wcli::wclicmdf2j_InputMaybe(wclidb::Wclicmdf2j &elem) {
  775    bool retval = true;
  776    retval = wclicmdf2j_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
  777    return retval;
  778}
  779
  780// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdf2j.XrefMaybe
  781// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
  782// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
  783bool wcli::wclicmdf2j_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdf2j &row) {
  784    bool retval = true;
  785    (void)row;
  786    wcli::FWclicmd* p_wclicmd = wcli::ind_wclicmd_Find(wclicmd_Get(row));
  787    if (UNLIKELY(!p_wclicmd)) {
  788        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "wcli.bad_xref  index:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmd" << Keyval("key", wclicmd_Get(row));
  789        return false;
  790    }
  791    // wclicmdf2j: save pointer to wclicmd
  792    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
  793        row.p_wclicmd = p_wclicmd;
  794    }
  795    // insert wclicmdf2j into index c_wclicmdf2j
  796    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
  797        c_wclicmdf2j_Insert(*p_wclicmd, row);
  798    }
  799    return retval;
  800}

  802// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdj2f.Alloc
  803// Allocate memory for new default row.
  804// If out of memory, process is killed.
  805wcli::FWclicmdj2f& wcli::wclicmdj2f_Alloc() {
  806    wcli::FWclicmdj2f* row = wclicmdj2f_AllocMaybe();
  807    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
  808        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.wclicmdj2f  comment:'Alloc failed'");
  809    }
  810    return *row;
  811}

  815wcli::FWclicmdj2f* wcli::wclicmdj2f_AllocMaybe() {

  817    if (row) {
  818        new (row) wcli::FWclicmdj2f; // call constructor
  819    }
  820    return row;
  821}
  822
  823// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdj2f.AllocMem
  824// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
  825void* wcli::wclicmdj2f_AllocMem() {
  826    u64 new_nelems     = _db.wclicmdj2f_n+1;
  827    // compute level and index on level
  828    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
  829    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
  830    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
  831    void *ret = NULL;
  832    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
  833    wcli::FWclicmdj2f*  lev   = NULL;
  834    if (bsr < 32) {
  835        lev = _db.wclicmdj2f_lary[bsr];
  836        if (!lev) {
  837            lev=(wcli::FWclicmdj2f*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdj2f) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
  838            _db.wclicmdj2f_lary[bsr] = lev;
  839        }
  840    }
  841    // allocate element from this level
  842    if (lev) {
  843        _db.wclicmdj2f_n = i32(new_nelems);
  844        ret = lev + index;
  845    }
  846    return ret;
  847}
  848
  849// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdj2f.RemoveAll
  850// Remove all elements from Lary
  851void wcli::wclicmdj2f_RemoveAll() {
  852    for (u64 n = _db.wclicmdj2f_n; n>0; ) {
  853        n--;
  854        wclicmdj2f_qFind(u64(n)).~FWclicmdj2f(); // destroy last element
  855        _db.wclicmdj2f_n = i32(n);
  856    }
  857}
  858
  859// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdj2f.RemoveLast
  860// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
  861void wcli::wclicmdj2f_RemoveLast() {
  862    u64 n = _db.wclicmdj2f_n;
  863    if (n > 0) {
  864        n -= 1;
  865        wclicmdj2f_qFind(u64(n)).~FWclicmdj2f();
  866        _db.wclicmdj2f_n = i32(n);
  867    }
  868}
  869
  870// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdj2f.XrefMaybe
  871// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
  872// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
  873bool wcli::wclicmdj2f_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdj2f &row) {
  874    bool retval = true;
  875    (void)row;
  876    // insert wclicmdj2f into index ind_wclicmdj2f
  877    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
  878        bool success = ind_wclicmdj2f_InsertMaybe(row);
  879        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
  880            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
  881            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdj2f"; // check for duplicate key
  882            return false;
  883        }
  884    }
  885    return retval;
  886}
  887
  888// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdj2f.Find
  889// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
  890wcli::FWclicmdj2f* wcli::ind_wclicmdj2f_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
  891    u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_wclicmdj2f_buckets_n - 1);
  892    wcli::FWclicmdj2f* *e = &_db.ind_wclicmdj2f_buckets_elems[index];
  893    wcli::FWclicmdj2f* ret=NULL;
  894    do {
  895        ret       = *e;
  896        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wclicmdj2f == key;
  897        if (done) break;
  898        e         = &ret->ind_wclicmdj2f_next;
  899    } while (true);
  900    return ret;
  901}
  902
  903// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdj2f.FindX
  904// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
  905wcli::FWclicmdj2f& wcli::ind_wclicmdj2f_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
  906    wcli::FWclicmdj2f* ret = ind_wclicmdj2f_Find(key);
  907    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_wclicmdj2f  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
  908    return *ret;
  909}
  910
  911// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdj2f.GetOrCreate
  912// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
  913wcli::FWclicmdj2f& wcli::ind_wclicmdj2f_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
  914    wcli::FWclicmdj2f* ret = ind_wclicmdj2f_Find(key);
  915    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
  916        ret         = &wclicmdj2f_Alloc();
  917        (*ret).wclicmdj2f = key;
  918        bool good = wclicmdj2f_XrefMaybe(*ret);
  919        if (!good) {
  920            wclicmdj2f_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
  921            ret = NULL;
  922        }
  923    }
  924    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_wclicmdj2f  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
  925    return *ret;
  926}
  927
  928// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdj2f.InsertMaybe
  929// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
  930bool wcli::ind_wclicmdj2f_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdj2f& row) {
  931    ind_wclicmdj2f_Reserve(1);
  932    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
  933    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wclicmdj2f_next == (wcli::FWclicmdj2f*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
  934        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdj2f) & (_db.ind_wclicmdj2f_buckets_n - 1);
  935        wcli::FWclicmdj2f* *prev = &_db.ind_wclicmdj2f_buckets_elems[index];
  936        do {
  937            wcli::FWclicmdj2f* ret = *prev;
  938            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
  939                break;
  940            }
  941            if ((*ret).wclicmdj2f == row.wclicmdj2f) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
  942                retval = false;
  943                break;
  944            }
  945            prev = &ret->ind_wclicmdj2f_next;
  946        } while (true);
  947        if (retval) {
  948            row.ind_wclicmdj2f_next = *prev;
  949            _db.ind_wclicmdj2f_n++;
  950            *prev = &row;
  951        }
  952    }
  953    return retval;
  954}
  955
  956// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdj2f.Remove
  957// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
  958void wcli::ind_wclicmdj2f_Remove(wcli::FWclicmdj2f& row) {
  959    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wclicmdj2f_next != (wcli::FWclicmdj2f*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
  960        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdj2f) & (_db.ind_wclicmdj2f_buckets_n - 1);
  961        wcli::FWclicmdj2f* *prev = &_db.ind_wclicmdj2f_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
  962        while (wcli::FWclicmdj2f *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
  963            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
  964                *prev = next->ind_wclicmdj2f_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
  965                _db.ind_wclicmdj2f_n--;
  966                row.ind_wclicmdj2f_next = (wcli::FWclicmdj2f*)-1;// not-in-hash
  967                break;
  968            }
  969            prev = &next->ind_wclicmdj2f_next;
  970        }
  971    }
  972}
  973
  974// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdj2f.Reserve
  975// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
  976void wcli::ind_wclicmdj2f_Reserve(int n) {
  977    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wclicmdj2f_buckets_n;
  978    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wclicmdj2f_n + n;
  979    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
  980    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
  981        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
  982        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdj2f*);
  983        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdj2f*);
  984        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
  985        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
  986        wcli::FWclicmdj2f* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWclicmdj2f**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
  987        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
  988            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdj2f");
  989        }
  990        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
  991        // rehash all entries
  992        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wclicmdj2f_buckets_n; i++) {
  993            wcli::FWclicmdj2f* elem = _db.ind_wclicmdj2f_buckets_elems[i];
  994            while (elem) {
  995                wcli::FWclicmdj2f &row        = *elem;
  996                wcli::FWclicmdj2f* next       = row.ind_wclicmdj2f_next;
  997                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdj2f) & (new_nbuckets-1);
  998                row.ind_wclicmdj2f_next     = new_buckets[index];
  999                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 1000                elem               = next;
 1001            }
 1002        }
 1003        // free old array
 1004        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wclicmdj2f_buckets_elems, old_size);
 1005        _db.ind_wclicmdj2f_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 1006        _db.ind_wclicmdj2f_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 1007    }
 1008}
 1009
 1010// --- wcli.FDb.wfld.Alloc
 1011// Allocate memory for new default row.
 1012// If out of memory, process is killed.
 1013wcli::FWfld& wcli::wfld_Alloc() {
 1014    wcli::FWfld* row = wfld_AllocMaybe();
 1015    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 1016        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.wfld  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 1017    }
 1018    return *row;
 1019}
 1020
 1021// --- wcli.FDb.wfld.AllocMaybe
 1022// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 1023wcli::FWfld* wcli::wfld_AllocMaybe() {
 1024    wcli::FWfld *row = (wcli::FWfld*)wfld_AllocMem();
 1025    if (row) {
 1026        new (row) wcli::FWfld; // call constructor
 1027    }
 1028    return row;
 1029}
 1030
 1031// --- wcli.FDb.wfld.InsertMaybe
 1032// Create new row from struct.
 1033// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 1034wcli::FWfld* wcli::wfld_InsertMaybe(const wclidb::Wfld &value) {
 1035    wcli::FWfld *row = &wfld_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 1036    wfld_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<wclidb::Wfld&>(value));
 1037    bool ok = wfld_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 1038    if (!ok) {
 1039        wfld_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 1040        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 1041    }
 1042    return row;
 1043}
 1044
 1045// --- wcli.FDb.wfld.AllocMem
 1046// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 1047void* wcli::wfld_AllocMem() {
 1048    u64 new_nelems     = _db.wfld_n+1;
 1049    // compute level and index on level
 1050    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 1051    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 1052    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 1053    void *ret = NULL;
 1054    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 1055    wcli::FWfld*  lev   = NULL;
 1056    if (bsr < 32) {
 1057        lev = _db.wfld_lary[bsr];
 1058        if (!lev) {
 1059            lev=(wcli::FWfld*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FWfld) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 1060            _db.wfld_lary[bsr] = lev;
 1061        }
 1062    }
 1063    // allocate element from this level
 1064    if (lev) {
 1065        _db.wfld_n = i32(new_nelems);
 1066        ret = lev + index;
 1067    }
 1068    return ret;
 1069}
 1070
 1071// --- wcli.FDb.wfld.RemoveAll
 1072// Remove all elements from Lary
 1073void wcli::wfld_RemoveAll() {
 1074    for (u64 n = _db.wfld_n; n>0; ) {
 1075        n--;
 1076        wfld_qFind(u64(n)).~FWfld(); // destroy last element
 1077        _db.wfld_n = i32(n);
 1078    }
 1079}
 1080
 1081// --- wcli.FDb.wfld.RemoveLast
 1082// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 1083void wcli::wfld_RemoveLast() {
 1084    u64 n = _db.wfld_n;
 1085    if (n > 0) {
 1086        n -= 1;
 1087        wfld_qFind(u64(n)).~FWfld();
 1088        _db.wfld_n = i32(n);
 1089    }
 1090}
 1091
 1092// --- wcli.FDb.wfld.InputMaybe
 1093static bool wcli::wfld_InputMaybe(wclidb::Wfld &elem) {
 1094    bool retval = true;
 1095    retval = wfld_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
 1096    return retval;
 1097}

 1099// --- wcli.FDb.wfld.XrefMaybe
 1100// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 1101// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 1102bool wcli::wfld_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWfld &row) {
 1103    bool retval = true;
 1104    (void)row;
 1105    // insert wfld into index ind_wfld
 1106    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 1107        bool success = ind_wfld_InsertMaybe(row);
 1108        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 1109            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 1110            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_wfld"; // check for duplicate key
 1111            return false;
 1112        }
 1113    }
 1114    return retval;
 1115}

 1117// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wfld.Find
 1118// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 1119wcli::FWfld* wcli::ind_wfld_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 1120    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_wfld_buckets_n - 1);
 1121    wcli::FWfld* *e = &_db.ind_wfld_buckets_elems[index];
 1122    wcli::FWfld* ret=NULL;
 1123    do {
 1124        ret       = *e;
 1125        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wfld == key;
 1126        if (done) break;
 1127        e         = &ret->ind_wfld_next;
 1128    } while (true);
 1129    return ret;
 1130}

 1140// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wfld.GetOrCreate
 1141// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 1142wcli::FWfld& wcli::ind_wfld_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 1143    wcli::FWfld* ret = ind_wfld_Find(key);
 1144    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 1145        ret         = &wfld_Alloc();
 1146        (*ret).wfld = key;
 1147        bool good = wfld_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 1148        if (!good) {
 1149            wfld_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 1150            ret = NULL;
 1151        }
 1152    }
 1153    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_wfld  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 1154    return *ret;
 1155}

 1157// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wfld.InsertMaybe
 1158// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 1159bool wcli::ind_wfld_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWfld& row) {
 1160    ind_wfld_Reserve(1);
 1161    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 1162    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wfld_next == (wcli::FWfld*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 1163        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wfld) & (_db.ind_wfld_buckets_n - 1);
 1164        wcli::FWfld* *prev = &_db.ind_wfld_buckets_elems[index];
 1165        do {
 1166            wcli::FWfld* ret = *prev;
 1167            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 1168                break;
 1169            }
 1170            if ((*ret).wfld == row.wfld) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 1171                retval = false;
 1172                break;
 1173            }
 1174            prev = &ret->ind_wfld_next;
 1175        } while (true);
 1176        if (retval) {
 1177            row.ind_wfld_next = *prev;
 1178            _db.ind_wfld_n++;
 1179            *prev = &row;
 1180        }
 1181    }
 1182    return retval;
 1183}
 1184
 1185// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wfld.Remove
 1186// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 1187void wcli::ind_wfld_Remove(wcli::FWfld& row) {
 1188    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wfld_next != (wcli::FWfld*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 1189        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wfld) & (_db.ind_wfld_buckets_n - 1);
 1190        wcli::FWfld* *prev = &_db.ind_wfld_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 1191        while (wcli::FWfld *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 1192            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 1193                *prev = next->ind_wfld_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 1194                _db.ind_wfld_n--;
 1195                row.ind_wfld_next = (wcli::FWfld*)-1;// not-in-hash
 1196                break;
 1197            }
 1198            prev = &next->ind_wfld_next;
 1199        }
 1200    }
 1201}
 1202
 1203// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wfld.Reserve
 1204// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 1205void wcli::ind_wfld_Reserve(int n) {
 1206    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wfld_buckets_n;
 1207    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wfld_n + n;
 1208    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 1209    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 1210        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 1211        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWfld*);
 1212        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWfld*);
 1213        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 1214        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 1215        wcli::FWfld* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWfld**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 1216        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 1217            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wfld");
 1218        }
 1219        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 1220        // rehash all entries
 1221        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wfld_buckets_n; i++) {
 1222            wcli::FWfld* elem = _db.ind_wfld_buckets_elems[i];
 1223            while (elem) {
 1224                wcli::FWfld &row        = *elem;
 1225                wcli::FWfld* next       = row.ind_wfld_next;
 1226                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wfld) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 1227                row.ind_wfld_next     = new_buckets[index];
 1228                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 1229                elem               = next;
 1230            }
 1231        }
 1232        // free old array
 1233        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wfld_buckets_elems, old_size);
 1234        _db.ind_wfld_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 1235        _db.ind_wfld_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 1236    }
 1237}
 1238
 1239// --- wcli.FDb.c_wfld.Insert
 1240// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
 1241// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
 1242void wcli::c_wfld_Insert(wcli::FWfld& row) {
 1243    if (bool_Update(row._db_c_wfld_in_ary,true)) {
 1244        // reserve space
 1245        c_wfld_Reserve(1);
 1246        u32 n  = _db.c_wfld_n;
 1247        u32 at = n;
 1248        wcli::FWfld* *elems = _db.c_wfld_elems;
 1249        elems[at] = &row;
 1250        _db.c_wfld_n = n+1;
 1251
 1252    }
 1253}
 1254
 1255// --- wcli.FDb.c_wfld.InsertMaybe
 1256// Insert pointer to row in array.
 1257// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
 1258// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
 1259bool wcli::c_wfld_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWfld& row) {
 1260    bool retval = !row._db_c_wfld_in_ary;
 1261    c_wfld_Insert(row); // check is performed in _Insert again
 1262    return retval;
 1263}
 1264
 1265// --- wcli.FDb.c_wfld.Remove
 1266// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
 1267void wcli::c_wfld_Remove(wcli::FWfld& row) {
 1268    if (bool_Update(row._db_c_wfld_in_ary,false)) {
 1269        int lim = _db.c_wfld_n;
 1270        wcli::FWfld* *elems = _db.c_wfld_elems;
 1271        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
 1272        // if found, shift array.
 1273        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
 1274            wcli::FWfld* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
 1275            if (elem == &row) {
 1276                int j = i + 1;
 1277                size_t nbytes = sizeof(wcli::FWfld*) * (lim - j);
 1278                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
 1279                _db.c_wfld_n = lim - 1;
 1280                break;
 1281            }
 1282        }
 1283    }
 1284}
 1285
 1286// --- wcli.FDb.c_wfld.Reserve
 1287// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
 1288void wcli::c_wfld_Reserve(u32 n) {
 1289    u32 old_max = _db.c_wfld_max;
 1290    if (UNLIKELY(_db.c_wfld_n + n > old_max)) {
 1291        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
 1292        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(wcli::FWfld*);
 1293        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(wcli::FWfld*);
 1294        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(_db.c_wfld_elems, old_size, new_size);
 1295        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 1296            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.c_wfld");
 1297        }
 1298        _db.c_wfld_elems = (wcli::FWfld**)new_mem;
 1299        _db.c_wfld_max = new_max;
 1300    }
 1301}
 1302
 1303// --- wcli.FDb.wtblactfld.Alloc
 1304// Allocate memory for new default row.
 1305// If out of memory, process is killed.
 1306wcli::FWtblactfld& wcli::wtblactfld_Alloc() {
 1307    wcli::FWtblactfld* row = wtblactfld_AllocMaybe();
 1308    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 1309        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.wtblactfld  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 1310    }
 1311    return *row;
 1312}
 1313
 1314// --- wcli.FDb.wtblactfld.AllocMaybe
 1315// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 1316wcli::FWtblactfld* wcli::wtblactfld_AllocMaybe() {
 1317    wcli::FWtblactfld *row = (wcli::FWtblactfld*)wtblactfld_AllocMem();
 1318    if (row) {
 1319        new (row) wcli::FWtblactfld; // call constructor
 1320    }
 1321    return row;
 1322}
 1323
 1324// --- wcli.FDb.wtblactfld.InsertMaybe
 1325// Create new row from struct.
 1326// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 1327wcli::FWtblactfld* wcli::wtblactfld_InsertMaybe(const wclidb::Wtblactfld &value) {
 1328    wcli::FWtblactfld *row = &wtblactfld_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 1329    wtblactfld_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<wclidb::Wtblactfld&>(value));
 1330    bool ok = wtblactfld_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 1331    if (!ok) {
 1332        wtblactfld_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 1333        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 1334    }
 1335    return row;
 1336}
 1337
 1338// --- wcli.FDb.wtblactfld.AllocMem
 1339// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 1340void* wcli::wtblactfld_AllocMem() {
 1341    u64 new_nelems     = _db.wtblactfld_n+1;
 1342    // compute level and index on level
 1343    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 1344    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 1345    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 1346    void *ret = NULL;
 1347    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 1348    wcli::FWtblactfld*  lev   = NULL;
 1349    if (bsr < 32) {
 1350        lev = _db.wtblactfld_lary[bsr];
 1351        if (!lev) {
 1352            lev=(wcli::FWtblactfld*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FWtblactfld) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 1353            _db.wtblactfld_lary[bsr] = lev;
 1354        }
 1355    }
 1356    // allocate element from this level
 1357    if (lev) {
 1358        _db.wtblactfld_n = i32(new_nelems);
 1359        ret = lev + index;
 1360    }
 1361    return ret;
 1362}
 1363
 1364// --- wcli.FDb.wtblactfld.RemoveAll
 1365// Remove all elements from Lary
 1366void wcli::wtblactfld_RemoveAll() {
 1367    for (u64 n = _db.wtblactfld_n; n>0; ) {
 1368        n--;
 1369        wtblactfld_qFind(u64(n)).~FWtblactfld(); // destroy last element
 1370        _db.wtblactfld_n = i32(n);
 1371    }
 1372}
 1373
 1374// --- wcli.FDb.wtblactfld.RemoveLast
 1375// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 1376void wcli::wtblactfld_RemoveLast() {
 1377    u64 n = _db.wtblactfld_n;
 1378    if (n > 0) {
 1379        n -= 1;
 1380        wtblactfld_qFind(u64(n)).~FWtblactfld();
 1381        _db.wtblactfld_n = i32(n);
 1382    }
 1383}
 1384
 1385// --- wcli.FDb.wtblactfld.InputMaybe
 1386static bool wcli::wtblactfld_InputMaybe(wclidb::Wtblactfld &elem) {
 1387    bool retval = true;
 1388    retval = wtblactfld_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
 1389    return retval;
 1390}
 1391
 1392// --- wcli.FDb.wtblactfld.XrefMaybe
 1393// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 1394// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 1395bool wcli::wtblactfld_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWtblactfld &row) {
 1396    bool retval = true;
 1397    (void)row;
 1398    wcli::FWfld* p_field = wcli::ind_wfld_Find(field_Get(row));
 1399    if (UNLIKELY(!p_field)) {
 1400        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "wcli.bad_xref  index:wcli.FDb.ind_wfld" << Keyval("key", field_Get(row));
 1401        return false;
 1402    }
 1403    // wtblactfld: save pointer to field
 1404    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 1405        row.p_wfld = p_field;
 1406    }
 1407    wcli::FWtblact* p_wtblact = wcli::ind_wtblact_Find(wtblact_Get(row));
 1408    if (UNLIKELY(!p_wtblact)) {
 1409        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "wcli.bad_xref  index:wcli.FDb.ind_wtblact" << Keyval("key", wtblact_Get(row));
 1410        return false;
 1411    }
 1412    // insert wtblactfld into index c_wtblactfld
 1413    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 1414        c_wtblactfld_Insert(*p_wtblact, row);
 1415    }
 1416    // insert wtblactfld into index c_wtblactfld
 1417    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 1418        c_wtblactfld_Insert(*p_field, row);
 1419    }
 1420    // insert wtblactfld into index ind_wtblactfld
 1421    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 1422        bool success = ind_wtblactfld_InsertMaybe(row);
 1423        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 1424            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 1425            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_wtblactfld"; // check for duplicate key
 1426            return false;
 1427        }
 1428    }
 1429    return retval;
 1430}
 1431
 1432// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wtblactfld.Find
 1433// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 1434wcli::FWtblactfld* wcli::ind_wtblactfld_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 1435    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_wtblactfld_buckets_n - 1);
 1436    wcli::FWtblactfld* *e = &_db.ind_wtblactfld_buckets_elems[index];
 1437    wcli::FWtblactfld* ret=NULL;
 1438    do {
 1439        ret       = *e;
 1440        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wtblactfld == key;
 1441        if (done) break;
 1442        e         = &ret->ind_wtblactfld_next;
 1443    } while (true);
 1444    return ret;
 1445}
 1446
 1447// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wtblactfld.FindX
 1448// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
 1449wcli::FWtblactfld& wcli::ind_wtblactfld_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
 1450    wcli::FWtblactfld* ret = ind_wtblactfld_Find(key);
 1451    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_wtblactfld  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
 1452    return *ret;
 1453}
 1454
 1455// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wtblactfld.InsertMaybe
 1456// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 1457bool wcli::ind_wtblactfld_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWtblactfld& row) {
 1458    ind_wtblactfld_Reserve(1);
 1459    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 1460    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wtblactfld_next == (wcli::FWtblactfld*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 1461        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wtblactfld) & (_db.ind_wtblactfld_buckets_n - 1);
 1462        wcli::FWtblactfld* *prev = &_db.ind_wtblactfld_buckets_elems[index];
 1463        do {
 1464            wcli::FWtblactfld* ret = *prev;
 1465            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 1466                break;
 1467            }
 1468            if ((*ret).wtblactfld == row.wtblactfld) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 1469                retval = false;
 1470                break;
 1471            }
 1472            prev = &ret->ind_wtblactfld_next;
 1473        } while (true);
 1474        if (retval) {
 1475            row.ind_wtblactfld_next = *prev;
 1476            _db.ind_wtblactfld_n++;
 1477            *prev = &row;
 1478        }
 1479    }
 1480    return retval;
 1481}
 1482
 1483// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wtblactfld.Remove
 1484// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 1485void wcli::ind_wtblactfld_Remove(wcli::FWtblactfld& row) {
 1486    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wtblactfld_next != (wcli::FWtblactfld*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 1487        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wtblactfld) & (_db.ind_wtblactfld_buckets_n - 1);
 1488        wcli::FWtblactfld* *prev = &_db.ind_wtblactfld_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 1489        while (wcli::FWtblactfld *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 1490            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 1491                *prev = next->ind_wtblactfld_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 1492                _db.ind_wtblactfld_n--;
 1493                row.ind_wtblactfld_next = (wcli::FWtblactfld*)-1;// not-in-hash
 1494                break;
 1495            }
 1496            prev = &next->ind_wtblactfld_next;
 1497        }
 1498    }
 1499}
 1500
 1501// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wtblactfld.Reserve
 1502// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 1503void wcli::ind_wtblactfld_Reserve(int n) {
 1504    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wtblactfld_buckets_n;
 1505    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wtblactfld_n + n;
 1506    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 1507    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 1508        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 1509        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWtblactfld*);
 1510        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWtblactfld*);
 1511        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 1512        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 1513        wcli::FWtblactfld* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWtblactfld**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 1514        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 1515            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wtblactfld");
 1516        }
 1517        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 1518        // rehash all entries
 1519        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wtblactfld_buckets_n; i++) {
 1520            wcli::FWtblactfld* elem = _db.ind_wtblactfld_buckets_elems[i];
 1521            while (elem) {
 1522                wcli::FWtblactfld &row        = *elem;
 1523                wcli::FWtblactfld* next       = row.ind_wtblactfld_next;
 1524                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wtblactfld) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 1525                row.ind_wtblactfld_next     = new_buckets[index];
 1526                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 1527                elem               = next;
 1528            }
 1529        }
 1530        // free old array
 1531        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wtblactfld_buckets_elems, old_size);
 1532        _db.ind_wtblactfld_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 1533        _db.ind_wtblactfld_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 1534    }
 1535}

 1619// --- wcli.FDb.wtblact.LoadStatic
 1620static void wcli::wtblact_LoadStatic() {
 1621    static struct _t {
 1622        const char *s;
 1623        void (*step)(wcli::FWtblact&);
 1624    } data[] = {
 1625        { "wclidb.wtblact  wtblact:help_list  t:Y  e:N  auth:N  comment:\"\"", wcli::wtblact_help_list }
 1626        ,{ "wclidb.wtblact  wtblact:wiki_create  t:N  e:N  auth:Y  comment:\"\"", wcli::wtblact_wiki_create }
 1627        ,{ "wclidb.wtblact  wtblact:wiki_update  t:N  e:N  auth:N  comment:\"\"", wcli::wtblact_wiki_update }
 1628        ,{ "wclidb.wtblact  wtblact:wiki_list  t:N  e:N  auth:N  comment:\"\"", wcli::wtblact_wiki_list }
 1629        ,{ "wclidb.wtblact  wtblact:siteinfo_list  t:N  e:N  auth:Y  comment:\"\"", wcli::wtblact_siteinfo_list }
 1630        ,{ "wclidb.wtblact  wtblact:page_list  t:Y  e:Y  auth:Y  comment:\"\"", wcli::wtblact_page_list }
 1631        ,{ "wclidb.wtblact  wtblact:page_create  t:N  e:Y  auth:Y  comment:\"\"", wcli::wtblact_page_create }
 1632        ,{ "wclidb.wtblact  wtblact:page_update  t:N  e:Y  auth:Y  comment:\"\"", wcli::wtblact_page_update }
 1633        ,{ "wclidb.wtblact  wtblact:page_remove  t:N  e:N  auth:Y  comment:\"\"", wcli::wtblact_page_remove }
 1634        ,{ "wclidb.wtblact  wtblact:page_download  t:N  e:N  auth:Y  comment:\"\"", wcli::wtblact_page_download }
 1635        ,{ "wclidb.wtblact  wtblact:page_upload  t:N  e:N  auth:Y  comment:\"\"", wcli::wtblact_page_upload }
 1636        ,{NULL, NULL}
 1637    };
 1638    (void)data;
 1639    wclidb::Wtblact wtblact;
 1640    for (int i=0; data[i].s; i++) {
 1641        (void)wclidb::Wtblact_ReadStrptrMaybe(wtblact, algo::strptr(data[i].s));
 1642        wcli::FWtblact *elem = wtblact_InsertMaybe(wtblact);
 1643        vrfy(elem, tempstr("wcli.static_insert_fatal_error")
 1644        << Keyval("tuple",algo::strptr(data[i].s))
 1645        << Keyval("comment",algo_lib::DetachBadTags()));
 1646        elem->step = data[i].step;
 1647    }
 1648}

 1650// --- wcli.FDb.wtblact.XrefMaybe
 1651// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 1652// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 1653bool wcli::wtblact_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWtblact &row) {
 1654    bool retval = true;
 1655    (void)row;
 1656    // insert wtblact into index ind_wtblact
 1657    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 1658        bool success = ind_wtblact_InsertMaybe(row);
 1659        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 1660            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 1661            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_wtblact"; // check for duplicate key
 1662            return false;
 1663        }
 1664    }
 1665    return retval;
 1666}

 1668// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wtblact.Find
 1669// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 1670wcli::FWtblact* wcli::ind_wtblact_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 1671    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_wtblact_buckets_n - 1);
 1672    wcli::FWtblact* *e = &_db.ind_wtblact_buckets_elems[index];
 1673    wcli::FWtblact* ret=NULL;
 1674    do {
 1675        ret       = *e;
 1676        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wtblact == key;
 1677        if (done) break;
 1678        e         = &ret->ind_wtblact_next;
 1679    } while (true);
 1680    return ret;
 1681}

 1683// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wtblact.FindX
 1684// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
 1685wcli::FWtblact& wcli::ind_wtblact_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
 1686    wcli::FWtblact* ret = ind_wtblact_Find(key);
 1687    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_wtblact  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
 1688    return *ret;
