 1690
 1691// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wtblact.GetOrCreate
 1692// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 1693wcli::FWtblact& wcli::ind_wtblact_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 1694    wcli::FWtblact* ret = ind_wtblact_Find(key);
 1695    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 1696        ret         = &wtblact_Alloc();
 1697        (*ret).wtblact = key;
 1698        bool good = wtblact_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 1699        if (!good) {
 1700            wtblact_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 1701            ret = NULL;
 1702        }
 1703    }
 1704    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_wtblact  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 1705    return *ret;
 1706}
 1707
 1708// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wtblact.InsertMaybe
 1709// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 1710bool wcli::ind_wtblact_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWtblact& row) {
 1711    ind_wtblact_Reserve(1);
 1712    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 1713    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wtblact_next == (wcli::FWtblact*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 1714        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wtblact) & (_db.ind_wtblact_buckets_n - 1);
 1715        wcli::FWtblact* *prev = &_db.ind_wtblact_buckets_elems[index];
 1716        do {
 1717            wcli::FWtblact* ret = *prev;
 1718            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 1719                break;
 1720            }
 1721            if ((*ret).wtblact == row.wtblact) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 1722                retval = false;
 1723                break;
 1724            }
 1725            prev = &ret->ind_wtblact_next;
 1726        } while (true);
 1727        if (retval) {
 1728            row.ind_wtblact_next = *prev;
 1729            _db.ind_wtblact_n++;
 1730            *prev = &row;
 1731        }
 1732    }
 1733    return retval;
 1734}
 1735
 1736// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wtblact.Remove
 1737// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 1738void wcli::ind_wtblact_Remove(wcli::FWtblact& row) {
 1739    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wtblact_next != (wcli::FWtblact*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 1740        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wtblact) & (_db.ind_wtblact_buckets_n - 1);
 1741        wcli::FWtblact* *prev = &_db.ind_wtblact_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 1742        while (wcli::FWtblact *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 1743            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 1744                *prev = next->ind_wtblact_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 1745                _db.ind_wtblact_n--;
 1746                row.ind_wtblact_next = (wcli::FWtblact*)-1;// not-in-hash
 1747                break;
 1748            }
 1749            prev = &next->ind_wtblact_next;
 1750        }
 1751    }
 1752}
 1753
 1754// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wtblact.Reserve
 1755// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 1756void wcli::ind_wtblact_Reserve(int n) {
 1757    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wtblact_buckets_n;
 1758    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wtblact_n + n;
 1759    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 1760    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 1761        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 1762        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWtblact*);
 1763        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWtblact*);
 1764        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 1765        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 1766        wcli::FWtblact* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWtblact**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 1767        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 1768            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wtblact");
 1769        }
 1770        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 1771        // rehash all entries
 1772        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wtblact_buckets_n; i++) {
 1773            wcli::FWtblact* elem = _db.ind_wtblact_buckets_elems[i];
 1774            while (elem) {
 1775                wcli::FWtblact &row        = *elem;
 1776                wcli::FWtblact* next       = row.ind_wtblact_next;
 1777                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wtblact) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 1778                row.ind_wtblact_next     = new_buckets[index];
 1779                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 1780                elem               = next;
 1781            }
 1782        }
 1783        // free old array
 1784        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wtblact_buckets_elems, old_size);
 1785        _db.ind_wtblact_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 1786        _db.ind_wtblact_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 1787    }
 1788}
 1789
 1790// --- wcli.FDb.zd_wtblact.Insert
 1791// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
 1792void wcli::zd_wtblact_Insert(wcli::FWtblact& row) {
 1793    if (!zd_wtblact_InLlistQ(row)) {
 1794        wcli::FWtblact* old_tail = _db.zd_wtblact_tail;
 1795        row.zd_wtblact_next = NULL;
 1796        row.zd_wtblact_prev = old_tail;
 1797        _db.zd_wtblact_tail = &row;
 1798        wcli::FWtblact **new_row_a = &old_tail->zd_wtblact_next;
 1799        wcli::FWtblact **new_row_b = &_db.zd_wtblact_head;
 1800        wcli::FWtblact **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
 1801        *new_row = &row;
 1802        _db.zd_wtblact_n++;
 1803    }
 1804}
 1805
 1806// --- wcli.FDb.zd_wtblact.Remove
 1807// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
 1808void wcli::zd_wtblact_Remove(wcli::FWtblact& row) {
 1809    if (zd_wtblact_InLlistQ(row)) {
 1810        wcli::FWtblact* old_head       = _db.zd_wtblact_head;
 1811        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
 1812        wcli::FWtblact* prev = row.zd_wtblact_prev;
 1813        wcli::FWtblact* next = row.zd_wtblact_next;
 1814        // if element is first, adjust list head; otherwise, adjust previous element's next
 1815        wcli::FWtblact **new_next_a = &prev->zd_wtblact_next;
 1816        wcli::FWtblact **new_next_b = &_db.zd_wtblact_head;
 1817        wcli::FWtblact **new_next = prev ? new_next_a : new_next_b;
 1818        *new_next = next;
 1819        // if element is last, adjust list tail; otherwise, adjust next element's prev
 1820        wcli::FWtblact **new_prev_a = &next->zd_wtblact_prev;
 1821        wcli::FWtblact **new_prev_b = &_db.zd_wtblact_tail;
 1822        wcli::FWtblact **new_prev = next ? new_prev_a : new_prev_b;
 1823        *new_prev = prev;
 1824        _db.zd_wtblact_n--;
 1825        row.zd_wtblact_next=(wcli::FWtblact*)-1; // not-in-list
 1826    }
 1827}
 1828
 1829// --- wcli.FDb.zd_wtblact.RemoveAll
 1830// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
 1831void wcli::zd_wtblact_RemoveAll() {
 1832    wcli::FWtblact* row = _db.zd_wtblact_head;
 1833    _db.zd_wtblact_head = NULL;
 1834    _db.zd_wtblact_tail = NULL;
 1835    _db.zd_wtblact_n = 0;
 1836    while (row) {
 1837        wcli::FWtblact* row_next = row->zd_wtblact_next;
 1838        row->zd_wtblact_next  = (wcli::FWtblact*)-1;
 1839        row->zd_wtblact_prev  = NULL;
 1840        row = row_next;
 1841    }
 1842}
 1843
 1844// --- wcli.FDb.zd_wtblact.RemoveFirst
 1845// If linked list is empty, return NULL. Otherwise unlink and return pointer to first element.
 1846wcli::FWtblact* wcli::zd_wtblact_RemoveFirst() {
 1847    wcli::FWtblact *row = NULL;
 1848    row = _db.zd_wtblact_head;
 1849    if (row) {
 1850        wcli::FWtblact *next = row->zd_wtblact_next;
 1851        _db.zd_wtblact_head = next;
 1852        wcli::FWtblact **new_end_a = &next->zd_wtblact_prev;
 1853        wcli::FWtblact **new_end_b = &_db.zd_wtblact_tail;
 1854        wcli::FWtblact **new_end = next ? new_end_a : new_end_b;
 1855        *new_end = NULL;
 1856        _db.zd_wtblact_n--;
 1857        row->zd_wtblact_next = (wcli::FWtblact*)-1; // mark as not-in-list
 1858    }
 1859    return row;
 1860}
 1861
 1862// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.Insert
 1863// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
 1864// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
 1865void wcli::c_page_foutput_Insert(wcli::FPage& row) {
 1866    if (bool_Update(row._db_c_page_foutput_in_ary,true)) {
 1867        // reserve space
 1868        c_page_foutput_Reserve(1);
 1869        u32 n  = _db.c_page_foutput_n;
 1870        u32 at = n;
 1871        wcli::FPage* *elems = _db.c_page_foutput_elems;
 1872        elems[at] = &row;
 1873        _db.c_page_foutput_n = n+1;
 1874
 1875    }
 1876}
 1877
 1878// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.InsertMaybe
 1879// Insert pointer to row in array.
 1880// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
 1881// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
 1882bool wcli::c_page_foutput_InsertMaybe(wcli::FPage& row) {
 1883    bool retval = !row._db_c_page_foutput_in_ary;
 1884    c_page_foutput_Insert(row); // check is performed in _Insert again
 1885    return retval;
 1886}
 1887
 1888// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.Remove
 1889// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
 1890void wcli::c_page_foutput_Remove(wcli::FPage& row) {
 1891    if (bool_Update(row._db_c_page_foutput_in_ary,false)) {
 1892        int lim = _db.c_page_foutput_n;
 1893        wcli::FPage* *elems = _db.c_page_foutput_elems;
 1894        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
 1895        // if found, shift array.
 1896        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
 1897            wcli::FPage* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
 1898            if (elem == &row) {
 1899                int j = i + 1;
 1900                size_t nbytes = sizeof(wcli::FPage*) * (lim - j);
 1901                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
 1902                _db.c_page_foutput_n = lim - 1;
 1903                break;
 1904            }
 1905        }
 1906    }
 1907}
 1908
 1909// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.Reserve
 1910// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
 1911void wcli::c_page_foutput_Reserve(u32 n) {
 1912    u32 old_max = _db.c_page_foutput_max;
 1913    if (UNLIKELY(_db.c_page_foutput_n + n > old_max)) {
 1914        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
 1915        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(wcli::FPage*);
 1916        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(wcli::FPage*);
 1917        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(_db.c_page_foutput_elems, old_size, new_size);
 1918        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 1919            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput");
 1920        }
 1921        _db.c_page_foutput_elems = (wcli::FPage**)new_mem;
 1922        _db.c_page_foutput_max = new_max;
 1923    }
 1924}
 1925
 1926// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.Swap
 1927// Swap values elem_a and elem_b
 1928inline static void wcli::c_page_foutput_Swap(wcli::FPage* &elem_a, wcli::FPage* &elem_b) {
 1929    wcli::FPage *temp = elem_a;
 1930    elem_a = elem_b;
 1931    elem_b = temp;
 1932}
 1933
 1934// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.Rotleft
 1935// Left circular shift of three-tuple
 1936inline static void wcli::c_page_foutput_Rotleft(wcli::FPage* &elem_a, wcli::FPage* &elem_b, wcli::FPage* &elem_c) {
 1937    wcli::FPage *temp = elem_a;
 1938    elem_a = elem_b;
 1939    elem_b = elem_c;
 1940    elem_c = temp;
 1941}
 1942
 1943// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.Lt
 1944// Compare values elem_a and elem_b
 1945// The comparison function must be anti-symmetric: if a>b, then !(b>a).
 1946// If not, mayhem results.
 1947static bool wcli::c_page_foutput_Lt(wcli::FPage &elem_a, wcli::FPage &elem_b) {
 1948    bool ret;
 1949    ret = elem_a.page < elem_b.page;
 1950    return ret;
 1951}
 1952
 1953// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.SortedQ
 1954// Verify whether array is sorted
 1955bool wcli::c_page_foutput_SortedQ() {
 1956    wcli::FPage* *elems = c_page_foutput_Getary().elems;
 1957    int n = c_page_foutput_N();
 1958    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
 1959        if (c_page_foutput_Lt(*elems[i], *elems[i-1])) {
 1960            return false;
 1961        }
 1962    }
 1963    return true;
 1964}
 1965
 1966// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.IntInsertionSort
 1967// Internal insertion sort
 1968static void wcli::c_page_foutput_IntInsertionSort(wcli::FPage* *elems, int n) {
 1969    for (int i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
 1970        int j = i;
 1971        wcli::FPage *tmp = elems[i];
 1972        // shift elements up by one
 1973        if (c_page_foutput_Lt(*tmp, *elems[j-1])) {
 1974            do {
 1975                elems[j] = elems[j-1];
 1976                j--;
 1977            } while (j>0 && c_page_foutput_Lt(*tmp, *elems[j-1]));
 1978            elems[j] = tmp;
 1979        }
 1980    }
 1981}
 1982
 1983// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.IntHeapSort
 1984// Internal heap sort
 1985static void wcli::c_page_foutput_IntHeapSort(wcli::FPage* *elems, int n) {
 1986    // construct max-heap.
 1987    // k=current element
 1988    // j=parent element
 1989    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
 1990        int k=i;
 1991        int j=(i-1)/2;
 1992        while (c_page_foutput_Lt(*elems[j], *elems[k])) {
 1993            c_page_foutput_Swap(elems[k],elems[j]);
 1994            k=j;
 1995            j=(k-1)/2;
 1996        }
 1997    }
 1998    // remove elements from heap one-by-one,
 1999    // deposit them in reverse order starting at the end of ARY.
 2000    for (int i = n - 1; i>=0; i--) {
 2001        int k = 0;
 2002        int l = 1;
 2003        while (l<i) {
 2004            l += l<i-1 && c_page_foutput_Lt(*elems[l], *elems[l+1]);
 2005            if (c_page_foutput_Lt(*elems[l], *elems[i])) {
 2006                break;
 2007            }
 2008            c_page_foutput_Swap(elems[k], elems[l]);
 2009            k = l;
 2010            l = k*2+1;
 2011        }
 2012        if (i != k) {
 2013            c_page_foutput_Swap(elems[i],elems[k]);
 2014        }
 2015    }
 2016}
 2017
 2018// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.IntQuickSort
 2019// Quick sort engine
 2020static void wcli::c_page_foutput_IntQuickSort(wcli::FPage* *elems, int n, int depth) {
 2021    while (n>16) {
 2022        // detect degenerate case and revert to heap sort
 2023        if (depth==0) {
 2024            c_page_foutput_IntHeapSort(elems,n);
 2025            return;
 2026        }
 2027        // elements to sort initially to determine pivot.
 2028        // choose pp=n/2 in case the input is already sorted.
 2029        int pi = 0;
 2030        int pp = n/2;
 2031        int pj = n-1;
 2032        // insertion sort for 1st, middle and last element
 2033        if (c_page_foutput_Lt(*elems[pp], *elems[pi])) {
 2034            c_page_foutput_Swap(elems[pi], elems[pp]);
 2035        }
 2036        if (c_page_foutput_Lt(*elems[pj], *elems[pp])) {
 2037            if (c_page_foutput_Lt(*elems[pj], *elems[pi])) {
 2038                c_page_foutput_Rotleft(elems[pi], elems[pj], elems[pp]);
 2039            } else {
 2040                c_page_foutput_Swap(elems[pj], elems[pp]);
 2041            }
 2042        }
 2043        // deposit pivot near the end of the array and skip it.
 2044        c_page_foutput_Swap(elems[--pj], elems[pp]);
 2045        // copy pivot into temporary variable
 2046        wcli::FPage *pivot = elems[pj];
 2047        for(;;){
 2048            while (c_page_foutput_Lt(*elems[++pi], *pivot)) {
 2049            }
 2050            while (c_page_foutput_Lt(*pivot, *elems[--pj])) {
 2051            }
 2052            if (pj <= pi) {
 2053                break;
 2054            }
 2055            c_page_foutput_Swap(elems[pi],elems[pj]);
 2056        }
 2057        depth -= 1;
 2058        c_page_foutput_IntQuickSort(elems, pi, depth);
 2059        elems += pi;
 2060        n -= pi;
 2061    }
 2062    // sort the remainder of this section
 2063    c_page_foutput_IntInsertionSort(elems,n);
 2064}
 2065
 2066// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.InsertionSort
 2067// Insertion sort
 2068void wcli::c_page_foutput_InsertionSort() {
 2069    wcli::FPage* *elems = c_page_foutput_Getary().elems;
 2070    int n = c_page_foutput_N();
 2071    c_page_foutput_IntInsertionSort(elems, n);
 2072}
 2073
 2074// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.HeapSort
 2075// Heap sort
 2076void wcli::c_page_foutput_HeapSort() {
 2077    wcli::FPage* *elems = c_page_foutput_Getary().elems;
 2078    int n = c_page_foutput_N();
 2079    c_page_foutput_IntHeapSort(elems, n);
 2080}
 2081
 2082// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.QuickSort
 2083// Quick sort
 2084void wcli::c_page_foutput_QuickSort() {
 2085    // compute max recursion depth based on number of elements in the array
 2086    int max_depth = algo::CeilingLog2(u32(c_page_foutput_N() + 1)) + 3;
 2087    wcli::FPage* *elems = c_page_foutput_Getary().elems;
 2088    int n = c_page_foutput_N();
 2089    c_page_foutput_IntQuickSort(elems, n, max_depth);
 2090}
 2091
 2092// --- wcli.FDb.c_page_foutput.SaveSsimfile
 2093// Save table to ssimfile
 2094bool wcli::c_page_foutput_SaveSsimfile(algo::strptr fname) {
 2095    cstring text;
 2096    ind_beg(wcli::_db_c_page_foutput_curs, c_page_foutput, wcli::_db) {
 2097        wclidb::Page out;
 2098        page_CopyOut(c_page_foutput, out);
 2099        wclidb::Page_Print(out, text);
 2100        text << eol;
 2101    }ind_end;
 2102    (void)algo::CreateDirRecurse(algo::GetDirName(fname));
 2103    // it is a silent error if the file cannot be saved.
 2104    return algo::SafeStringToFile(text, fname);
 2105}

 2211// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikiuser_foutput.IntInsertionSort
 2212// Internal insertion sort
 2213static void wcli::c_wikiuser_foutput_IntInsertionSort(wcli::FWikiuser* *elems, int n) {
 2214    for (int i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
 2215        int j = i;
 2216        wcli::FWikiuser *tmp = elems[i];
 2217        // shift elements up by one
 2218        if (c_wikiuser_foutput_Lt(*tmp, *elems[j-1])) {
 2219            do {
 2220                elems[j] = elems[j-1];
 2221                j--;
 2222            } while (j>0 && c_wikiuser_foutput_Lt(*tmp, *elems[j-1]));
 2223            elems[j] = tmp;
 2224        }
 2225    }
 2226}
 2227
 2228// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikiuser_foutput.IntHeapSort
 2229// Internal heap sort
 2230static void wcli::c_wikiuser_foutput_IntHeapSort(wcli::FWikiuser* *elems, int n) {
 2231    // construct max-heap.
 2232    // k=current element
 2233    // j=parent element
 2234    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
 2235        int k=i;
 2236        int j=(i-1)/2;
 2237        while (c_wikiuser_foutput_Lt(*elems[j], *elems[k])) {
 2238            c_wikiuser_foutput_Swap(elems[k],elems[j]);
 2239            k=j;
 2240            j=(k-1)/2;
 2241        }
 2242    }
 2243    // remove elements from heap one-by-one,
 2244    // deposit them in reverse order starting at the end of ARY.
 2245    for (int i = n - 1; i>=0; i--) {
 2246        int k = 0;
 2247        int l = 1;
 2248        while (l<i) {
 2249            l += l<i-1 && c_wikiuser_foutput_Lt(*elems[l], *elems[l+1]);
 2250            if (c_wikiuser_foutput_Lt(*elems[l], *elems[i])) {
 2251                break;
 2252            }
 2253            c_wikiuser_foutput_Swap(elems[k], elems[l]);
 2254            k = l;
 2255            l = k*2+1;
 2256        }
 2257        if (i != k) {
 2258            c_wikiuser_foutput_Swap(elems[i],elems[k]);
 2259        }
 2260    }
 2261}
 2262
 2263// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikiuser_foutput.IntQuickSort
 2264// Quick sort engine
 2265static void wcli::c_wikiuser_foutput_IntQuickSort(wcli::FWikiuser* *elems, int n, int depth) {
 2266    while (n>16) {
 2267        // detect degenerate case and revert to heap sort
 2268        if (depth==0) {
 2269            c_wikiuser_foutput_IntHeapSort(elems,n);
 2270            return;
 2271        }
 2272        // elements to sort initially to determine pivot.
 2273        // choose pp=n/2 in case the input is already sorted.
 2274        int pi = 0;
 2275        int pp = n/2;
 2276        int pj = n-1;
 2277        // insertion sort for 1st, middle and last element
 2278        if (c_wikiuser_foutput_Lt(*elems[pp], *elems[pi])) {
 2279            c_wikiuser_foutput_Swap(elems[pi], elems[pp]);
 2280        }
 2281        if (c_wikiuser_foutput_Lt(*elems[pj], *elems[pp])) {
 2282            if (c_wikiuser_foutput_Lt(*elems[pj], *elems[pi])) {
 2283                c_wikiuser_foutput_Rotleft(elems[pi], elems[pj], elems[pp]);
 2284            } else {
 2285                c_wikiuser_foutput_Swap(elems[pj], elems[pp]);
 2286            }
 2287        }
 2288        // deposit pivot near the end of the array and skip it.
 2289        c_wikiuser_foutput_Swap(elems[--pj], elems[pp]);
 2290        // copy pivot into temporary variable
 2291        wcli::FWikiuser *pivot = elems[pj];
 2292        for(;;){
 2293            while (c_wikiuser_foutput_Lt(*elems[++pi], *pivot)) {
 2294            }
 2295            while (c_wikiuser_foutput_Lt(*pivot, *elems[--pj])) {
 2296            }
 2297            if (pj <= pi) {
 2298                break;
 2299            }
 2300            c_wikiuser_foutput_Swap(elems[pi],elems[pj]);
 2301        }
 2302        depth -= 1;
 2303        c_wikiuser_foutput_IntQuickSort(elems, pi, depth);
 2304        elems += pi;
 2305        n -= pi;
 2306    }
 2307    // sort the remainder of this section
 2308    c_wikiuser_foutput_IntInsertionSort(elems,n);
 2309}
 2310
 2311// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikiuser_foutput.InsertionSort
 2312// Insertion sort
 2313void wcli::c_wikiuser_foutput_InsertionSort() {
 2314    wcli::FWikiuser* *elems = c_wikiuser_foutput_Getary().elems;
 2315    int n = c_wikiuser_foutput_N();
 2316    c_wikiuser_foutput_IntInsertionSort(elems, n);
 2317}
 2318
 2319// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikiuser_foutput.HeapSort
 2320// Heap sort
 2321void wcli::c_wikiuser_foutput_HeapSort() {
 2322    wcli::FWikiuser* *elems = c_wikiuser_foutput_Getary().elems;
 2323    int n = c_wikiuser_foutput_N();
 2324    c_wikiuser_foutput_IntHeapSort(elems, n);
 2325}
 2326
 2327// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikiuser_foutput.QuickSort
 2328// Quick sort
 2329void wcli::c_wikiuser_foutput_QuickSort() {
 2330    // compute max recursion depth based on number of elements in the array
 2331    int max_depth = algo::CeilingLog2(u32(c_wikiuser_foutput_N() + 1)) + 3;
 2332    wcli::FWikiuser* *elems = c_wikiuser_foutput_Getary().elems;
 2333    int n = c_wikiuser_foutput_N();
 2334    c_wikiuser_foutput_IntQuickSort(elems, n, max_depth);
 2335}

 2338// Save table to ssimfile
 2339bool wcli::c_wikiuser_foutput_SaveSsimfile(algo::strptr fname) {
 2340    cstring text;
 2341    ind_beg(wcli::_db_c_wikiuser_foutput_curs, c_wikiuser_foutput, wcli::_db) {
 2342        wclidb::Wikiuser out;
 2343        wikiuser_CopyOut(c_wikiuser_foutput, out);
 2344        wclidb::Wikiuser_Print(out, text);

 2350}
 2351
 2352// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.Insert
 2353// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
 2354// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
 2355void wcli::c_wikigroup_user_Insert(wcli::FWikigroup& row) {
 2356    if (bool_Update(row._db_c_wikigroup_user_in_ary,true)) {
 2357        // reserve space
 2358        c_wikigroup_user_Reserve(1);
 2359        u32 n  = _db.c_wikigroup_user_n;
 2360        u32 at = n;
 2361        wcli::FWikigroup* *elems = _db.c_wikigroup_user_elems;
 2362        elems[at] = &row;
 2363        _db.c_wikigroup_user_n = n+1;
 2364
 2365    }
 2366}
 2367
 2368// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.InsertMaybe
 2369// Insert pointer to row in array.
 2370// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
 2371// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
 2372bool wcli::c_wikigroup_user_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWikigroup& row) {
 2373    bool retval = !row._db_c_wikigroup_user_in_ary;
 2374    c_wikigroup_user_Insert(row); // check is performed in _Insert again
 2375    return retval;
 2376}
 2377
 2378// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.Remove
 2379// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
 2380void wcli::c_wikigroup_user_Remove(wcli::FWikigroup& row) {
 2381    if (bool_Update(row._db_c_wikigroup_user_in_ary,false)) {
 2382        int lim = _db.c_wikigroup_user_n;
 2383        wcli::FWikigroup* *elems = _db.c_wikigroup_user_elems;
 2384        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
 2385        // if found, shift array.
 2386        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
 2387            wcli::FWikigroup* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
 2388            if (elem == &row) {
 2389                int j = i + 1;
 2390                size_t nbytes = sizeof(wcli::FWikigroup*) * (lim - j);
 2391                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
 2392                _db.c_wikigroup_user_n = lim - 1;
 2393                break;
 2394            }
 2395        }
 2396    }
 2397}
 2398
 2399// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.Reserve
 2400// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
 2401void wcli::c_wikigroup_user_Reserve(u32 n) {
 2402    u32 old_max = _db.c_wikigroup_user_max;
 2403    if (UNLIKELY(_db.c_wikigroup_user_n + n > old_max)) {
 2404        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
 2405        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(wcli::FWikigroup*);
 2406        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(wcli::FWikigroup*);
 2407        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(_db.c_wikigroup_user_elems, old_size, new_size);
 2408        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 2409            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user");
 2410        }
 2411        _db.c_wikigroup_user_elems = (wcli::FWikigroup**)new_mem;
 2412        _db.c_wikigroup_user_max = new_max;
 2413    }
 2414}
 2415
 2416// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.Swap
 2417// Swap values elem_a and elem_b
 2418inline static void wcli::c_wikigroup_user_Swap(wcli::FWikigroup* &elem_a, wcli::FWikigroup* &elem_b) {
 2419    wcli::FWikigroup *temp = elem_a;
 2420    elem_a = elem_b;
 2421    elem_b = temp;
 2422}
 2423
 2424// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.Rotleft
 2425// Left circular shift of three-tuple
 2426inline static void wcli::c_wikigroup_user_Rotleft(wcli::FWikigroup* &elem_a, wcli::FWikigroup* &elem_b, wcli::FWikigroup* &elem_c) {
 2427    wcli::FWikigroup *temp = elem_a;
 2428    elem_a = elem_b;
 2429    elem_b = elem_c;
 2430    elem_c = temp;
 2431}
 2432
 2433// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.Lt
 2434// Compare values elem_a and elem_b
 2435// The comparison function must be anti-symmetric: if a>b, then !(b>a).
 2436// If not, mayhem results.
 2437static bool wcli::c_wikigroup_user_Lt(wcli::FWikigroup &elem_a, wcli::FWikigroup &elem_b) {
 2438    bool ret;
 2439    ret = elem_a.wikigroup < elem_b.wikigroup;
 2440    return ret;
 2441}
 2442
 2443// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.SortedQ
 2444// Verify whether array is sorted
 2445bool wcli::c_wikigroup_user_SortedQ() {
 2446    wcli::FWikigroup* *elems = c_wikigroup_user_Getary().elems;
 2447    int n = c_wikigroup_user_N();
 2448    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
 2449        if (c_wikigroup_user_Lt(*elems[i], *elems[i-1])) {
 2450            return false;
 2451        }
 2452    }
 2453    return true;
 2454}
 2455
 2456// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.IntInsertionSort
 2457// Internal insertion sort
 2458static void wcli::c_wikigroup_user_IntInsertionSort(wcli::FWikigroup* *elems, int n) {
 2459    for (int i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
 2460        int j = i;
 2461        wcli::FWikigroup *tmp = elems[i];
 2462        // shift elements up by one
 2463        if (c_wikigroup_user_Lt(*tmp, *elems[j-1])) {
 2464            do {
 2465                elems[j] = elems[j-1];
 2466                j--;
 2467            } while (j>0 && c_wikigroup_user_Lt(*tmp, *elems[j-1]));
 2468            elems[j] = tmp;
 2469        }
 2470    }
 2471}
 2472
 2473// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.IntHeapSort
 2474// Internal heap sort
 2475static void wcli::c_wikigroup_user_IntHeapSort(wcli::FWikigroup* *elems, int n) {
 2476    // construct max-heap.
 2477    // k=current element
 2478    // j=parent element
 2479    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
 2480        int k=i;
 2481        int j=(i-1)/2;
 2482        while (c_wikigroup_user_Lt(*elems[j], *elems[k])) {
 2483            c_wikigroup_user_Swap(elems[k],elems[j]);
 2484            k=j;
 2485            j=(k-1)/2;
 2486        }
 2487    }
 2488    // remove elements from heap one-by-one,
 2489    // deposit them in reverse order starting at the end of ARY.
 2490    for (int i = n - 1; i>=0; i--) {
 2491        int k = 0;
 2492        int l = 1;
 2493        while (l<i) {
 2494            l += l<i-1 && c_wikigroup_user_Lt(*elems[l], *elems[l+1]);
 2495            if (c_wikigroup_user_Lt(*elems[l], *elems[i])) {
 2496                break;
 2497            }
 2498            c_wikigroup_user_Swap(elems[k], elems[l]);
 2499            k = l;
 2500            l = k*2+1;
 2501        }
 2502        if (i != k) {
 2503            c_wikigroup_user_Swap(elems[i],elems[k]);
 2504        }
 2505    }
 2506}
 2507
 2508// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.IntQuickSort
 2509// Quick sort engine
 2510static void wcli::c_wikigroup_user_IntQuickSort(wcli::FWikigroup* *elems, int n, int depth) {
 2511    while (n>16) {
 2512        // detect degenerate case and revert to heap sort
 2513        if (depth==0) {
 2514            c_wikigroup_user_IntHeapSort(elems,n);
 2515            return;
 2516        }
 2517        // elements to sort initially to determine pivot.
 2518        // choose pp=n/2 in case the input is already sorted.
 2519        int pi = 0;
 2520        int pp = n/2;
 2521        int pj = n-1;
 2522        // insertion sort for 1st, middle and last element
 2523        if (c_wikigroup_user_Lt(*elems[pp], *elems[pi])) {
 2524            c_wikigroup_user_Swap(elems[pi], elems[pp]);
 2525        }
 2526        if (c_wikigroup_user_Lt(*elems[pj], *elems[pp])) {
 2527            if (c_wikigroup_user_Lt(*elems[pj], *elems[pi])) {
 2528                c_wikigroup_user_Rotleft(elems[pi], elems[pj], elems[pp]);
 2529            } else {
 2530                c_wikigroup_user_Swap(elems[pj], elems[pp]);
 2531            }
 2532        }
 2533        // deposit pivot near the end of the array and skip it.
 2534        c_wikigroup_user_Swap(elems[--pj], elems[pp]);
 2535        // copy pivot into temporary variable
 2536        wcli::FWikigroup *pivot = elems[pj];
 2537        for(;;){
 2538            while (c_wikigroup_user_Lt(*elems[++pi], *pivot)) {
 2539            }
 2540            while (c_wikigroup_user_Lt(*pivot, *elems[--pj])) {
 2541            }
 2542            if (pj <= pi) {
 2543                break;
 2544            }
 2545            c_wikigroup_user_Swap(elems[pi],elems[pj]);
 2546        }
 2547        depth -= 1;
 2548        c_wikigroup_user_IntQuickSort(elems, pi, depth);
 2549        elems += pi;
 2550        n -= pi;
 2551    }
 2552    // sort the remainder of this section
 2553    c_wikigroup_user_IntInsertionSort(elems,n);
 2554}
 2555
 2556// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.InsertionSort
 2557// Insertion sort
 2558void wcli::c_wikigroup_user_InsertionSort() {
 2559    wcli::FWikigroup* *elems = c_wikigroup_user_Getary().elems;
 2560    int n = c_wikigroup_user_N();
 2561    c_wikigroup_user_IntInsertionSort(elems, n);
 2562}
 2563
 2564// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.HeapSort
 2565// Heap sort
 2566void wcli::c_wikigroup_user_HeapSort() {
 2567    wcli::FWikigroup* *elems = c_wikigroup_user_Getary().elems;
 2568    int n = c_wikigroup_user_N();
 2569    c_wikigroup_user_IntHeapSort(elems, n);
 2570}
 2571
 2572// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikigroup_user.QuickSort
 2573// Quick sort
 2574void wcli::c_wikigroup_user_QuickSort() {
 2575    // compute max recursion depth based on number of elements in the array
 2576    int max_depth = algo::CeilingLog2(u32(c_wikigroup_user_N() + 1)) + 3;
 2577    wcli::FWikigroup* *elems = c_wikigroup_user_Getary().elems;
 2578    int n = c_wikigroup_user_N();
 2579    c_wikigroup_user_IntQuickSort(elems, n, max_depth);
 2580}

 2582// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmd.Alloc
 2583// Allocate memory for new default row.
 2584// If out of memory, process is killed.
 2585wcli::FWclicmd& wcli::wclicmd_Alloc() {
 2586    wcli::FWclicmd* row = wclicmd_AllocMaybe();
 2587    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 2588        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.wclicmd  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 2589    }
 2590    return *row;
 2591}
 2592
 2593// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmd.AllocMaybe
 2594// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 2595wcli::FWclicmd* wcli::wclicmd_AllocMaybe() {
 2596    wcli::FWclicmd *row = (wcli::FWclicmd*)wclicmd_AllocMem();
 2597    if (row) {
 2598        new (row) wcli::FWclicmd; // call constructor
 2599    }
 2600    return row;
 2601}
 2602
 2603// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmd.InsertMaybe
 2604// Create new row from struct.
 2605// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 2606wcli::FWclicmd* wcli::wclicmd_InsertMaybe(const wclidb::Wclicmd &value) {
 2607    wcli::FWclicmd *row = &wclicmd_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 2608    wclicmd_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<wclidb::Wclicmd&>(value));
 2609    bool ok = wclicmd_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 2610    if (!ok) {
 2611        wclicmd_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 2612        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 2613    }
 2614    return row;
 2615}
 2616
 2617// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmd.AllocMem
 2618// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 2619void* wcli::wclicmd_AllocMem() {
 2620    u64 new_nelems     = _db.wclicmd_n+1;
 2621    // compute level and index on level
 2622    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 2623    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 2624    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 2625    void *ret = NULL;
 2626    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 2627    wcli::FWclicmd*  lev   = NULL;
 2628    if (bsr < 32) {
 2629        lev = _db.wclicmd_lary[bsr];
 2630        if (!lev) {
 2631            lev=(wcli::FWclicmd*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FWclicmd) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 2632            _db.wclicmd_lary[bsr] = lev;
 2633        }
 2634    }
 2635    // allocate element from this level
 2636    if (lev) {
 2637        _db.wclicmd_n = i32(new_nelems);
 2638        ret = lev + index;
 2639    }
 2640    return ret;
 2641}
 2642
 2643// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmd.RemoveAll
 2644// Remove all elements from Lary
 2645void wcli::wclicmd_RemoveAll() {
 2646    for (u64 n = _db.wclicmd_n; n>0; ) {
 2647        n--;
 2648        wclicmd_qFind(u64(n)).~FWclicmd(); // destroy last element
 2649        _db.wclicmd_n = i32(n);
 2650    }
 2651}
 2652
 2653// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmd.RemoveLast
 2654// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 2655void wcli::wclicmd_RemoveLast() {
 2656    u64 n = _db.wclicmd_n;
 2657    if (n > 0) {
 2658        n -= 1;
 2659        wclicmd_qFind(u64(n)).~FWclicmd();
 2660        _db.wclicmd_n = i32(n);
 2661    }
 2662}

 2702// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmd.XrefMaybe
 2703// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 2704// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 2705bool wcli::wclicmd_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWclicmd &row) {
 2706    bool retval = true;
 2707    (void)row;
 2708    // insert wclicmd into index ind_wclicmd
 2709    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 2710        bool success = ind_wclicmd_InsertMaybe(row);
 2711        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 2712            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 2713            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmd"; // check for duplicate key
 2714            return false;
 2715        }
 2716    }
 2717    return retval;
 2718}

 2725    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {

 2731// --- wcli.FDb.dclicmd.AllocMaybe
 2732// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 2733wcli::FDclicmd* wcli::dclicmd_AllocMaybe() {
 2734    wcli::FDclicmd *row = (wcli::FDclicmd*)dclicmd_AllocMem();
 2735    if (row) {
 2736        new (row) wcli::FDclicmd; // call constructor
 2737    }
 2738    return row;
 2739}
 2740
 2741// --- wcli.FDb.dclicmd.InsertMaybe
 2742// Create new row from struct.
 2743// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 2744wcli::FDclicmd* wcli::dclicmd_InsertMaybe(const dclidb::Dclicmd &value) {
 2745    wcli::FDclicmd *row = &dclicmd_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 2746    dclicmd_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dclidb::Dclicmd&>(value));
 2747    bool ok = dclicmd_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 2748    if (!ok) {
 2749        dclicmd_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 2750        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 2751    }
 2752    return row;
 2753}
 2754
 2755// --- wcli.FDb.dclicmd.AllocMem
 2756// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 2757void* wcli::dclicmd_AllocMem() {
 2758    u64 new_nelems     = _db.dclicmd_n+1;
 2759    // compute level and index on level
 2760    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 2761    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 2762    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 2763    void *ret = NULL;
 2764    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 2765    wcli::FDclicmd*  lev   = NULL;
 2766    if (bsr < 32) {
 2767        lev = _db.dclicmd_lary[bsr];
 2768        if (!lev) {
 2769            lev=(wcli::FDclicmd*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FDclicmd) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 2770            _db.dclicmd_lary[bsr] = lev;
 2771        }
 2772    }
 2773    // allocate element from this level
 2774    if (lev) {
 2775        _db.dclicmd_n = i32(new_nelems);
 2776        ret = lev + index;
 2777    }
 2778    return ret;
 2779}
 2780
 2781// --- wcli.FDb.dclicmd.RemoveAll
 2782// Remove all elements from Lary
 2783void wcli::dclicmd_RemoveAll() {
 2784    for (u64 n = _db.dclicmd_n; n>0; ) {
 2785        n--;
 2786        dclicmd_qFind(u64(n)).~FDclicmd(); // destroy last element
 2787        _db.dclicmd_n = i32(n);
 2788    }
 2789}
 2790
 2791// --- wcli.FDb.dclicmd.RemoveLast
 2792// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 2793void wcli::dclicmd_RemoveLast() {
 2794    u64 n = _db.dclicmd_n;
 2795    if (n > 0) {
 2796        n -= 1;
 2797        dclicmd_qFind(u64(n)).~FDclicmd();
 2798        _db.dclicmd_n = i32(n);
 2799    }
 2800}

 2804    bool retval = true;
 2805    retval = dclicmd_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
 2806    return retval;
 2807}

 3128
 3129// --- wcli.FDb._db.ReadArgv
 3130// Read argc,argv directly into the fields of the command line(s)
 3131// The following fields are updated:
 3132//     wcli.FDb.cmdline
 3133//     algo_lib.FDb.cmdline
 3134void wcli::ReadArgv() {
 3135    command::wcli &cmd = wcli::_db.cmdline;
 3136    algo_lib::Cmdline &base = algo_lib::_db.cmdline;
 3137    int needarg=-1;// unknown
 3138    int argidx=1;// skip process name
 3139    int anonidx=0;
 3140    algo::strptr nextanon = command::wcli_GetAnon(cmd, anonidx);
 3141    tempstr err;
 3142    algo::strptr attrname;
 3143    bool isanon=false; // true if attrname is anonfld (positional)
 3144    algo_lib::FieldId baseattrid;
 3145    command::FieldId attrid;
 3146    bool endopt=false;
 3147    int whichns=0;// which namespace does the current attribute belong to
 3148    for (; argidx < algo_lib::_db.argc; argidx++) {
 3149        algo::strptr arg = algo_lib::_db.argv[argidx];
 3150        algo::strptr attrval;
 3151        algo::strptr dfltval;
 3152        bool haveval=false;
 3153        bool dash=elems_N(arg)>1 && arg.elems[0]=='-'; // a single dash is not an option
 3154        // this attribute is a value
 3155        if (endopt || needarg>0 || !dash) {
 3156            attrval=arg;
 3157            haveval=true;
 3158        } else {
 3159            // this attribute is a field name (with - or --)
 3160            // or a -- by itself
 3161            bool dashdash = elems_N(arg) >= 2 && arg.elems[1]=='-';
 3162            int skip = int(dash) + dashdash;
 3163            attrname=ch_RestFrom(arg,skip);
 3164            if (skip==2 && elems_N(arg)==2) {
 3165                endopt=true;
 3166                continue;// nothing else to do here
 3167            }
 3168            // parse "-a:B" arg into attrname,attrvalue
 3169            algo::i32_Range colon = TFind(attrname,':');
 3170            if (colon.beg < colon.end) {
 3171                attrval=ch_RestFrom(attrname,colon.end);
 3172                attrname=ch_FirstN(attrname,colon.beg);
 3173                haveval=true;
 3174            }
 3175            // look up which command (this one or the base) contains the field
 3176            whichns=0;
 3177            needarg=-1;
 3178            // look up parameter information in base namespace (needarg will be -1 if lookup fails)
 3179            if (algo_lib::FieldId_ReadStrptrMaybe(baseattrid,attrname)) {
 3180                needarg = algo_lib::Cmdline_NArgs(baseattrid,dfltval,&isanon);
 3181            }
 3182            if (needarg<0) {
 3183                whichns=1;
 3184                // look up parameter information in this namespace (needarg will be -1 if lookup fails)
 3185                if (command::FieldId_ReadStrptrMaybe(attrid,attrname)) {
 3186                    needarg = command::wcli_NArgs(attrid,dfltval,&isanon);
 3187                }
 3188            }
 3189            if (attrval == "" && dfltval != "") {
 3190                attrval=dfltval;
 3191                haveval=true;
 3192            }
 3193            if (needarg<0) {
 3194                err<<"wcli: unknown option "<<Keyval("value",arg)<<eol;
 3195            } else {
 3196                if (isanon) {
 3197                    if (attrname == nextanon) { // treat named anon (positional) argument as unnamed
 3198                        attrname = ""; // treat it as unnamed
 3199                    } else if (nextanon != "") { // disallow out-of-order anon (positional) args
 3200                        err<<"wcli: error at "<<algo::strptr_ToSsim(arg)<<": must be preceded by [-"<<nextanon<<"]"<<eol;
 3201                    }
 3202                }
 3203            }
 3204        }
 3205        // look up anon field name based on index
 3206        // anon fields are only allowed in the leaf ns, never base
 3207        if (ch_N(attrname) == 0) {
 3208            attrname = nextanon;
 3209            nextanon = command::wcli_GetAnon(cmd, ++anonidx);
 3210            command::FieldId_ReadStrptrMaybe(attrid,attrname);
 3211            whichns=1;
 3212        }
 3213        if (ch_N(attrname) == 0) {
 3214            err << "wcli: too many arguments. error at "<<algo::strptr_ToSsim(arg)<<eol;
 3215        }
 3216        // read value into currently selected arg
 3217        if (haveval) {
 3218            bool ret=false;
 3219            // it's already known which namespace is consuming the args,
 3220            // so directly go there
 3221            if (whichns == 0) {
 3222                ret=algo_lib::Cmdline_ReadFieldMaybe(base, attrname, attrval);
 3223            }
 3224            if (whichns==1) {
 3225                ret=command::wcli_ReadFieldMaybe(cmd, attrname, attrval);
 3226                switch(attrid.value) {
 3227                    default:break;
 3228                }
 3229            }
 3230            if (!ret) {
 3231                err<<"wcli: error in "
 3232                <<Keyval("option",attrname)
 3233                <<Keyval("value",attrval)<<eol;
 3234            }
 3235            needarg--;
 3236            if (needarg <= 0) {
 3237                attrname="";// forget which argument was being filled
 3238            }
 3239        }
 3240    }
 3241    bool dohelp = false;
 3242    bool doexit=false;
 3243    if (algo_lib::_db.cmdline.help) {
 3244        dohelp = true;
 3245        doexit = true;
 3246        algo_lib::_db.exit_code = 1; // help exits with non-zero status code
 3247    } else if (algo_lib::_db.cmdline.version) {
 3248        // -ver output goes to stdout
 3249        prlog(algo::gitinfo_Get());
 3250        doexit = true;
 3251    } else if (algo_lib::_db.cmdline.signature) {
 3252        ind_beg(algo_lib::_db_dispsigcheck_curs,dispsigcheck,algo_lib::_db) {
 3253            // dispsig goes to stdout
 3254            dmmeta::Dispsigcheck out;
 3255            dispsigcheck_CopyOut(dispsigcheck,out);
 3256            prlog(out);
 3257        }ind_end
 3258        doexit = true;
 3259    }
 3260    if (!dohelp) {
 3261    }
 3262    // dmmeta.floadtuples:wcli.FDb.cmdline
 3263    if (!dohelp && err=="") {
 3264        algo_lib::ResetErrtext();
 3265        if (!wcli::LoadTuplesMaybe(cmd.in,true)) {
 3266            err << "wcli.load_input  "<<algo_lib::DetachBadTags()<<eol;
 3267        }
 3268    }
 3269    if (err != "") {
 3270        algo_lib::_db.exit_code=1;
 3271        prerr(err);
 3272        doexit=true;
 3273    }
 3274    if (dohelp) {
 3275        prlog(wcli_help);
 3276    }
 3277    if (doexit) {
 3278        _exit(algo_lib::_db.exit_code);
 3279    }
 3280    algo_lib::ResetErrtext();
 3281}
 3282
 3283// --- wcli.FDb._db.MainLoop
 3284// Main loop.
 3285void wcli::MainLoop() {
 3286    algo::SchedTime time(algo::get_cycles());
 3287    algo_lib::_db.clock          = time;
 3288    do {
 3289        algo_lib::_db.next_loop.value = algo_lib::_db.limit;
 3290        wcli::Steps();
 3291    } while (algo_lib::_db.next_loop < algo_lib::_db.limit);
 3292}
 3293
 3294// --- wcli.FDb._db.Step
 3295// Main step
 3296void wcli::Step() {
 3297}

 3319// --- wcli.FDb._db.InsertStrptrMaybe

 3444// --- wcli.FDb._db.LoadTuplesMaybe
 3445// Load all finputs from given directory.
 3446bool wcli::LoadTuplesMaybe(algo::strptr root, bool recursive) {
 3447    bool retval = true;
 3448    if (FileQ(root)) {
 3449        retval = wcli::LoadTuplesFile(root, recursive);
 3450    } else if (root == "-") {
 3451        retval = wcli::LoadTuplesFd(algo::Fildes(0),"(stdin)",recursive);
 3452    } else if (DirectoryQ(root)) {
 3453        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"x2db.user"),recursive);
 3454        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wwiki"),recursive);
 3455        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wact"),recursive);
 3456        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wtbl"),recursive);
 3457        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wfld"),recursive);
 3458        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wtblactfld"),recursive);
 3459        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wikiuser"),recursive);
 3460        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wikiuseruser"),recursive);
 3461        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wclicmdapi"),recursive);
 3462        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wikitoken"),recursive);
 3463        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wikitokenapi"),recursive);
 3464        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wikigroup"),recursive);
 3465        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wikiext"),recursive);
 3466        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.wclicmdf2j"),recursive);
 3467        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.pagetitle"),recursive);
 3468        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.page"),recursive);
 3469        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"wclidb.pagesec"),recursive);
 3470        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.dispsigcheck"),recursive);
 3471        retval = retval && wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dclidb.dclicmd"),recursive);
 3472    } else {
 3473        algo_lib::SaveBadTag("path", root);
 3474        algo_lib::SaveBadTag("comment", "Wrong working directory?");
 3475        retval = false;
 3476    }
 3477    return retval;
 3478}

 3480// --- wcli.FDb._db.LoadTuplesFile
 3481// Load all finputs from given file.
 3482// Read tuples from file FNAME into this namespace's in-memory database.
 3483// If RECURSIVE is TRUE, then also load these tuples into any parent namespaces
 3484// It a file referred to by FNAME is missing, no error is reported (it's considered an empty set).
 3485// Function returns TRUE if all records were parsed and inserted without error.
 3486// If the function returns FALSE, use algo_lib::DetachBadTags() for error description
 3487bool wcli::LoadTuplesFile(algo::strptr fname, bool recursive) {
 3488    bool retval = true;
 3489    algo_lib::FFildes fildes;
 3490    // missing files are not an error
 3491    fildes.fd = OpenRead(fname,algo::FileFlags());
 3492    if (ValidQ(fildes.fd)) {
 3493        retval = LoadTuplesFd(fildes.fd, fname, recursive);
 3494    }
 3495    return retval;
 3496}
 3497
 3498// --- wcli.FDb._db.LoadTuplesFd
 3499// Load all finputs from given file descriptor.
 3500bool wcli::LoadTuplesFd(algo::Fildes fd, algo::strptr fname, bool recursive) {
 3501    bool retval = true;
 3502    ind_beg(algo::FileLine_curs,line,fd) {
 3503        if (recursive) {
 3504            retval = retval && algo_lib::InsertStrptrMaybe(line);
 3505        }
 3506        retval = retval && wcli::InsertStrptrMaybe(line);
 3507        if (!retval) {
 3508            algo_lib::_db.errtext << eol
 3509            << fname << ":"
 3510            << (ind_curs(line).i+1)
 3511            << ": " << line << eol;
 3512            break;
 3513        }
 3514    }ind_end;
 3515    return retval;
 3516}

 3518// --- wcli.FDb._db.SaveTuples
 3519// Save ssim data to given directory.
 3520u32 wcli::SaveTuples(algo::strptr root) {
 3521    u32 retval = 0;
 3522    u32 nbefore = algo_lib::_db.stringtofile_nwrite;
 3523    (void)c_page_foutput_SaveSsimfile(SsimFname(root, "wclidb.page"));
 3524    (void)c_wikiuser_foutput_SaveSsimfile(SsimFname(root, "wclidb.wikiuser"));
 3525    retval = algo_lib::_db.stringtofile_nwrite - nbefore;
 3526    return retval;
 3527}

 3553// --- wcli.FDb.page.Alloc
 3554// Allocate memory for new default row.
 3555// If out of memory, process is killed.
 3556wcli::FPage& wcli::page_Alloc() {
 3557    wcli::FPage* row = page_AllocMaybe();
 3558    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 3559        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.page  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 3560    }
 3561    return *row;
 3562}
 3563
 3564// --- wcli.FDb.page.AllocMaybe
 3565// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 3566wcli::FPage* wcli::page_AllocMaybe() {
 3567    wcli::FPage *row = (wcli::FPage*)page_AllocMem();
 3568    if (row) {
 3569        new (row) wcli::FPage; // call constructor
 3570    }
 3571    return row;
 3572}
 3573
 3574// --- wcli.FDb.page.InsertMaybe
 3575// Create new row from struct.
 3576// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 3577wcli::FPage* wcli::page_InsertMaybe(const wclidb::Page &value) {
 3578    wcli::FPage *row = &page_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 3579    page_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<wclidb::Page&>(value));
 3580    bool ok = page_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 3581    if (!ok) {
 3582        page_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 3583        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 3584    }
 3585    return row;
 3586}
 3587
 3588// --- wcli.FDb.page.AllocMem
 3589// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 3590void* wcli::page_AllocMem() {
 3591    u64 new_nelems     = _db.page_n+1;
 3592    // compute level and index on level
 3593    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 3594    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 3595    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 3596    void *ret = NULL;
 3597    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 3598    wcli::FPage*  lev   = NULL;
 3599    if (bsr < 32) {
 3600        lev = _db.page_lary[bsr];
 3601        if (!lev) {
 3602            lev=(wcli::FPage*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FPage) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 3603            _db.page_lary[bsr] = lev;
 3604        }
 3605    }
 3606    // allocate element from this level
 3607    if (lev) {
 3608        _db.page_n = i32(new_nelems);
 3609        ret = lev + index;
 3610    }
 3611    return ret;
 3612}
 3613
 3614// --- wcli.FDb.page.RemoveAll
 3615// Remove all elements from Lary
 3616void wcli::page_RemoveAll() {
 3617    for (u64 n = _db.page_n; n>0; ) {
 3618        n--;
 3619        page_qFind(u64(n)).~FPage(); // destroy last element
 3620        _db.page_n = i32(n);
 3621    }
 3622}
 3623
 3624// --- wcli.FDb.page.RemoveLast
 3625// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 3626void wcli::page_RemoveLast() {
 3627    u64 n = _db.page_n;
 3628    if (n > 0) {
 3629        n -= 1;
 3630        page_qFind(u64(n)).~FPage();
 3631        _db.page_n = i32(n);
 3632    }
 3633}
 3634
 3635// --- wcli.FDb.page.InputMaybe
 3636static bool wcli::page_InputMaybe(wclidb::Page &elem) {
 3637    bool retval = true;
 3638    retval = page_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
 3639    return retval;
 3640}
 3641
 3642// --- wcli.FDb.page.XrefMaybe
 3643// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 3644// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 3645bool wcli::page_XrefMaybe(wcli::FPage &row) {
 3646    bool retval = true;
 3647    (void)row;
 3648    // insert page into index ind_page
 3649    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 3650        bool success = ind_page_InsertMaybe(row);
 3651        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 3652            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 3653            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_page"; // check for duplicate key
 3654            return false;
 3655        }
 3656    }
 3657    // insert page into index ind_page_id
 3658    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 3659        bool success = ind_page_id_InsertMaybe(row);
 3660        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 3661            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 3662            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_page_id"; // check for duplicate key
 3663            return false;
 3664        }
 3665    }
 3666    // insert page into index c_page_foutput
 3667    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 3668        c_page_foutput_Insert(row);
 3669    }
 3670    return retval;
 3671}

 3733
 3734// --- wcli.FDb.pagetitle.RemoveAll
 3735// Remove all elements from Lary
 3736void wcli::pagetitle_RemoveAll() {
 3737    for (u64 n = _db.pagetitle_n; n>0; ) {
 3738        n--;
 3739        pagetitle_qFind(u64(n)).~FPagetitle(); // destroy last element
 3740        _db.pagetitle_n = i32(n);
 3741    }
 3742}
 3743
 3744// --- wcli.FDb.pagetitle.RemoveLast
 3745// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 3746void wcli::pagetitle_RemoveLast() {
 3747    u64 n = _db.pagetitle_n;
 3748    if (n > 0) {
 3749        n -= 1;
 3750        pagetitle_qFind(u64(n)).~FPagetitle();
 3751        _db.pagetitle_n = i32(n);
 3752    }
 3753}

 3794    wcli::FWikiuser *row = (wcli::FWikiuser*)wikiuser_AllocMem();
 3795    if (row) {

 3800
 3801// --- wcli.FDb.wikiuser.InsertMaybe
 3802// Create new row from struct.
 3803// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 3804wcli::FWikiuser* wcli::wikiuser_InsertMaybe(const wclidb::Wikiuser &value) {
 3805    wcli::FWikiuser *row = &wikiuser_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 3806    wikiuser_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<wclidb::Wikiuser&>(value));
 3807    bool ok = wikiuser_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 3808    if (!ok) {
 3809        wikiuser_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 3810        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 3811    }
 3812    return row;
 3813}
 3814
 3815// --- wcli.FDb.wikiuser.AllocMem
 3816// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 3817void* wcli::wikiuser_AllocMem() {
 3818    u64 new_nelems     = _db.wikiuser_n+1;
 3819    // compute level and index on level
 3820    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 3821    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 3822    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 3823    void *ret = NULL;
 3824    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 3825    wcli::FWikiuser*  lev   = NULL;
 3826    if (bsr < 32) {
 3827        lev = _db.wikiuser_lary[bsr];
 3828        if (!lev) {
 3829            lev=(wcli::FWikiuser*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FWikiuser) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 3830            _db.wikiuser_lary[bsr] = lev;
 3831        }
 3832    }
 3833    // allocate element from this level
 3834    if (lev) {
 3835        _db.wikiuser_n = i32(new_nelems);
 3836        ret = lev + index;
 3837    }
 3838    return ret;
 3839}
 3840
 3841// --- wcli.FDb.wikiuser.RemoveAll
 3842// Remove all elements from Lary
 3843void wcli::wikiuser_RemoveAll() {
 3844    for (u64 n = _db.wikiuser_n; n>0; ) {
 3845        n--;
 3846        wikiuser_qFind(u64(n)).~FWikiuser(); // destroy last element
 3847        _db.wikiuser_n = i32(n);
 3848    }
 3849}
 3850
 3851// --- wcli.FDb.wikiuser.RemoveLast
 3852// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 3853void wcli::wikiuser_RemoveLast() {
 3854    u64 n = _db.wikiuser_n;
 3855    if (n > 0) {
 3856        n -= 1;
 3857        wikiuser_qFind(u64(n)).~FWikiuser();
 3858        _db.wikiuser_n = i32(n);
 3859    }
 3860}

 3874    (void)row;
 3875    // insert wikiuser into index ind_wikiuser

 3881            return false;

 3884    // insert wikiuser into index c_wikiuser_foutput

 3986    wcli::FUser* p_user = wcli::ind_user_Find(row.user);
 3987    if (UNLIKELY(!p_user)) {
 3988        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "wcli.bad_xref  index:wcli.FDb.ind_user" << Keyval("key", row.user);
 3989        return false;
 3990    }
 3991    // wikiuseruser: save pointer to user
 3992    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 3993        row.p_user = p_user;
 3994    }
 3995    // insert wikiuseruser into index ind_wikiuseruser
 3996    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 3997        bool success = ind_wikiuseruser_InsertMaybe(row);
 3998        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 3999            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 4000            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_wikiuseruser"; // check for duplicate key
 4001            return false;
 4002        }
 4003    }

 4005}

 4276        _db.wclicmdapi_n = i32(new_nelems);
 4277        ret = lev + index;
 4278    }
 4279    return ret;
 4280}
 4281
 4282// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdapi.RemoveAll
 4283// Remove all elements from Lary
 4284void wcli::wclicmdapi_RemoveAll() {
 4285    for (u64 n = _db.wclicmdapi_n; n>0; ) {
 4286        n--;
 4287        wclicmdapi_qFind(u64(n)).~FWclicmdapi(); // destroy last element
 4288        _db.wclicmdapi_n = i32(n);
 4289    }
 4290}
 4291
 4292// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdapi.RemoveLast
 4293// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 4294void wcli::wclicmdapi_RemoveLast() {
 4295    u64 n = _db.wclicmdapi_n;
 4296    if (n > 0) {
 4297        n -= 1;
 4298        wclicmdapi_qFind(u64(n)).~FWclicmdapi();
 4299        _db.wclicmdapi_n = i32(n);
 4300    }
 4301}
 4302
 4303// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdapi.InputMaybe
 4304static bool wcli::wclicmdapi_InputMaybe(wclidb::Wclicmdapi &elem) {
 4305    bool retval = true;
 4306    retval = wclicmdapi_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
 4307    return retval;
 4308}
 4309
 4310// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdapi.XrefMaybe
 4311// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 4312// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 4313bool wcli::wclicmdapi_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdapi &row) {
 4314    bool retval = true;
 4315    (void)row;
 4316    // insert wclicmdapi into index ind_wclicmdapi
 4317    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 4318        bool success = ind_wclicmdapi_InsertMaybe(row);
 4319        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 4320            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 4321            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdapi"; // check for duplicate key
 4322            return false;
 4323        }
 4324    }
 4325    wcli::FWclicmd* p_wclicmd = wcli::ind_wclicmd_Find(wclicmd_Get(row));
 4326    if (UNLIKELY(!p_wclicmd)) {
 4327        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "wcli.bad_xref  index:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmd" << Keyval("key", wclicmd_Get(row));
 4328        return false;
 4329    }
 4330    // insert wclicmdapi into index c_wclicmdapi
 4331    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 4332        c_wclicmdapi_Insert(*p_wclicmd, row);
 4333    }
 4334    return retval;
 4335}
 4336
 4337// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikins_exec.Insert
 4338// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
 4339// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
 4340void wcli::c_wikins_exec_Insert(wcli::FWikins& row) {
 4341    if (bool_Update(row._db_c_wikins_exec_in_ary,true)) {
 4342        // reserve space
 4343        c_wikins_exec_Reserve(1);
 4344        u32 n  = _db.c_wikins_exec_n;
 4345        u32 at = n;
 4346        wcli::FWikins* *elems = _db.c_wikins_exec_elems;
 4347        elems[at] = &row;
 4348        _db.c_wikins_exec_n = n+1;
 4349
 4350    }
 4351}
 4352
 4353// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikins_exec.InsertMaybe
 4354// Insert pointer to row in array.
 4355// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
 4356// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
 4357bool wcli::c_wikins_exec_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWikins& row) {
 4358    bool retval = !row._db_c_wikins_exec_in_ary;
 4359    c_wikins_exec_Insert(row); // check is performed in _Insert again
 4360    return retval;
 4361}
 4362
 4363// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikins_exec.Remove
 4364// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
 4365void wcli::c_wikins_exec_Remove(wcli::FWikins& row) {
 4366    if (bool_Update(row._db_c_wikins_exec_in_ary,false)) {
 4367        int lim = _db.c_wikins_exec_n;
 4368        wcli::FWikins* *elems = _db.c_wikins_exec_elems;
 4369        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
 4370        // if found, shift array.
 4371        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
 4372            wcli::FWikins* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
 4373            if (elem == &row) {
 4374                int j = i + 1;
 4375                size_t nbytes = sizeof(wcli::FWikins*) * (lim - j);
 4376                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
 4377                _db.c_wikins_exec_n = lim - 1;
 4378                break;
 4379            }
 4380        }
 4381    }
 4382}
 4383
 4384// --- wcli.FDb.c_wikins_exec.Reserve
 4385// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
 4386void wcli::c_wikins_exec_Reserve(u32 n) {
 4387    u32 old_max = _db.c_wikins_exec_max;
 4388    if (UNLIKELY(_db.c_wikins_exec_n + n > old_max)) {
 4389        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
 4390        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(wcli::FWikins*);
 4391        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(wcli::FWikins*);
 4392        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(_db.c_wikins_exec_elems, old_size, new_size);
 4393        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 4394            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.c_wikins_exec");
 4395        }
 4396        _db.c_wikins_exec_elems = (wcli::FWikins**)new_mem;
 4397        _db.c_wikins_exec_max = new_max;
 4398    }
 4399}
 4400

 4403// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.

 4431        int lim = _db.c_wclicmdarg_exec_n;

 4441                _db.c_wclicmdarg_exec_n = lim - 1;
 4442                break;
 4443            }
 4444        }
 4445    }
 4446}

 4464
 4465// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikigroup.Find
 4466// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 4467wcli::FWikigroup* wcli::ind_wikigroup_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 4468    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_wikigroup_buckets_n - 1);
 4469    wcli::FWikigroup* *e = &_db.ind_wikigroup_buckets_elems[index];
 4470    wcli::FWikigroup* ret=NULL;
 4471    do {
 4472        ret       = *e;
 4473        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wikigroup == key;
 4474        if (done) break;
 4475        e         = &ret->ind_wikigroup_next;
 4476    } while (true);
 4477    return ret;
 4478}
 4479
 4480// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikigroup.FindX
 4481// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
 4482wcli::FWikigroup& wcli::ind_wikigroup_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
 4483    wcli::FWikigroup* ret = ind_wikigroup_Find(key);
 4484    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_wikigroup  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
 4485    return *ret;
 4486}
 4487
 4488// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikigroup.GetOrCreate
 4489// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 4490wcli::FWikigroup& wcli::ind_wikigroup_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 4491    wcli::FWikigroup* ret = ind_wikigroup_Find(key);
 4492    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 4493        ret         = &wikigroup_Alloc();
 4494        (*ret).wikigroup = key;
 4495        bool good = wikigroup_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 4496        if (!good) {
 4497            wikigroup_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 4498            ret = NULL;
 4499        }
 4500    }
 4501    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_wikigroup  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 4502    return *ret;
 4503}
 4504
 4505// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikigroup.InsertMaybe
 4506// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 4507bool wcli::ind_wikigroup_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWikigroup& row) {
 4508    ind_wikigroup_Reserve(1);
 4509    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 4510    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wikigroup_next == (wcli::FWikigroup*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 4511        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wikigroup) & (_db.ind_wikigroup_buckets_n - 1);
 4512        wcli::FWikigroup* *prev = &_db.ind_wikigroup_buckets_elems[index];
 4513        do {
 4514            wcli::FWikigroup* ret = *prev;
 4515            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 4516                break;
 4517            }
 4518            if ((*ret).wikigroup == row.wikigroup) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 4519                retval = false;
 4520                break;
 4521            }
 4522            prev = &ret->ind_wikigroup_next;
 4523        } while (true);
 4524        if (retval) {
 4525            row.ind_wikigroup_next = *prev;
 4526            _db.ind_wikigroup_n++;
 4527            *prev = &row;
 4528        }
 4529    }
 4530    return retval;
 4531}
 4532
 4533// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikigroup.Remove
 4534// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 4535void wcli::ind_wikigroup_Remove(wcli::FWikigroup& row) {
 4536    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wikigroup_next != (wcli::FWikigroup*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 4537        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wikigroup) & (_db.ind_wikigroup_buckets_n - 1);
 4538        wcli::FWikigroup* *prev = &_db.ind_wikigroup_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 4539        while (wcli::FWikigroup *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 4540            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 4541                *prev = next->ind_wikigroup_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 4542                _db.ind_wikigroup_n--;
 4543                row.ind_wikigroup_next = (wcli::FWikigroup*)-1;// not-in-hash
 4544                break;
 4545            }
 4546            prev = &next->ind_wikigroup_next;
 4547        }
 4548    }
 4549}
 4550
 4551// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikigroup.Reserve
 4552// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 4553void wcli::ind_wikigroup_Reserve(int n) {
 4554    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wikigroup_buckets_n;
 4555    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wikigroup_n + n;
 4556    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 4557    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 4558        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 4559        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWikigroup*);
 4560        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWikigroup*);
 4561        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 4562        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 4563        wcli::FWikigroup* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWikigroup**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 4564        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 4565            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wikigroup");
 4566        }
 4567        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 4568        // rehash all entries
 4569        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wikigroup_buckets_n; i++) {
 4570            wcli::FWikigroup* elem = _db.ind_wikigroup_buckets_elems[i];
 4571            while (elem) {
 4572                wcli::FWikigroup &row        = *elem;
 4573                wcli::FWikigroup* next       = row.ind_wikigroup_next;
 4574                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wikigroup) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 4575                row.ind_wikigroup_next     = new_buckets[index];
 4576                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 4577                elem               = next;
 4578            }
 4579        }
 4580        // free old array
 4581        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wikigroup_buckets_elems, old_size);
 4582        _db.ind_wikigroup_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 4583        _db.ind_wikigroup_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 4584    }
 4585}

 4599    return ret;
 4600}

 4641                retval = false;

 4673// --- wcli.FDb.ind_user.Reserve
 4674// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 4675void wcli::ind_user_Reserve(int n) {
 4676    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_user_buckets_n;
 4677    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_user_n + n;
 4678    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 4679    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 4680        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 4681        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FUser*);
 4682        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FUser*);
 4683        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 4684        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 4685        wcli::FUser* *new_buckets = (wcli::FUser**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 4686        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 4687            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_user");
 4688        }
 4689        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 4690        // rehash all entries
 4691        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_user_buckets_n; i++) {
 4692            wcli::FUser* elem = _db.ind_user_buckets_elems[i];
 4693            while (elem) {
 4694                wcli::FUser &row        = *elem;
 4695                wcli::FUser* next       = row.ind_user_next;
 4696                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.user) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 4697                row.ind_user_next     = new_buckets[index];
 4698                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 4699                elem               = next;
 4700            }
 4701        }
 4702        // free old array
 4703        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_user_buckets_elems, old_size);
 4704        _db.ind_user_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 4705        _db.ind_user_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 4706    }
 4707}

 4732// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikiuseruser.InsertMaybe

 4734bool wcli::ind_wikiuseruser_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWikiuseruser& row) {
 4735    ind_wikiuseruser_Reserve(1);
 4736    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 4737    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wikiuseruser_next == (wcli::FWikiuseruser*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 4738        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wikiuser) & (_db.ind_wikiuseruser_buckets_n - 1);
 4739        wcli::FWikiuseruser* *prev = &_db.ind_wikiuseruser_buckets_elems[index];
 4740        do {
 4741            wcli::FWikiuseruser* ret = *prev;
 4742            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 4743                break;
 4744            }
 4745            if ((*ret).wikiuser == row.wikiuser) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 4746                retval = false;
 4747                break;
 4748            }
 4749            prev = &ret->ind_wikiuseruser_next;
 4750        } while (true);
 4751        if (retval) {
 4752            row.ind_wikiuseruser_next = *prev;
 4753            _db.ind_wikiuseruser_n++;
 4754            *prev = &row;
 4755        }
 4756    }
 4757    return retval;
 4758}
 4759
 4760// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikiuseruser.Remove
 4761// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 4762void wcli::ind_wikiuseruser_Remove(wcli::FWikiuseruser& row) {
 4763    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wikiuseruser_next != (wcli::FWikiuseruser*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 4764        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wikiuser) & (_db.ind_wikiuseruser_buckets_n - 1);
 4765        wcli::FWikiuseruser* *prev = &_db.ind_wikiuseruser_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 4766        while (wcli::FWikiuseruser *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 4767            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 4768                *prev = next->ind_wikiuseruser_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 4769                _db.ind_wikiuseruser_n--;
 4770                row.ind_wikiuseruser_next = (wcli::FWikiuseruser*)-1;// not-in-hash
 4771                break;
 4772            }
 4773            prev = &next->ind_wikiuseruser_next;
 4774        }
 4775    }
 4776}
 4777
 4778// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikiuseruser.Reserve
 4779// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 4780void wcli::ind_wikiuseruser_Reserve(int n) {
 4781    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wikiuseruser_buckets_n;
 4782    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wikiuseruser_n + n;
 4783    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 4784    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 4785        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 4786        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWikiuseruser*);
 4787        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWikiuseruser*);
 4788        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 4789        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 4790        wcli::FWikiuseruser* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWikiuseruser**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 4791        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 4792            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wikiuseruser");
 4793        }
 4794        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 4795        // rehash all entries
 4796        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wikiuseruser_buckets_n; i++) {
 4797            wcli::FWikiuseruser* elem = _db.ind_wikiuseruser_buckets_elems[i];
 4798            while (elem) {
 4799                wcli::FWikiuseruser &row        = *elem;
 4800                wcli::FWikiuseruser* next       = row.ind_wikiuseruser_next;
 4801                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wikiuser) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 4802                row.ind_wikiuseruser_next     = new_buckets[index];
 4803                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 4804                elem               = next;
 4805            }
 4806        }
 4807        // free old array
 4808        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wikiuseruser_buckets_elems, old_size);
 4809        _db.ind_wikiuseruser_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 4810        _db.ind_wikiuseruser_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 4811    }
 4812}

 4814// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikiuser.Find
 4815// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 4816wcli::FWikiuser* wcli::ind_wikiuser_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 4817    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_wikiuser_buckets_n - 1);
 4818    wcli::FWikiuser* *e = &_db.ind_wikiuser_buckets_elems[index];
 4819    wcli::FWikiuser* ret=NULL;
 4820    do {
 4821        ret       = *e;
 4822        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wikiuser == key;
 4823        if (done) break;
 4824        e         = &ret->ind_wikiuser_next;
 4825    } while (true);
 4826    return ret;
 4827}

 4833    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_wikiuser  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");

 4835}

 4848                break;
 4849            }

 4851                retval = false;
 4852                break;

 4858            _db.ind_wikiuser_n++;
 4859            *prev = &row;
 4860        }
 4861    }
 4862    return retval;

 4942// --- wcli.FDb.ind_pagetitle.GetOrCreate
 4943// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 4944wcli::FPagetitle& wcli::ind_pagetitle_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 4945    wcli::FPagetitle* ret = ind_pagetitle_Find(key);
 4946    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 4947        ret         = &pagetitle_Alloc();
 4948        (*ret).pagetitle = key;
 4949        bool good = pagetitle_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 4950        if (!good) {
 4951            pagetitle_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 4952            ret = NULL;
 4953        }
 4954    }
 4955    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_pagetitle  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 4956    return *ret;
 4957}
