 5169// --- wcli.FDb.ind_page_id.InsertMaybe
 5170// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 5171bool wcli::ind_page_id_InsertMaybe(wcli::FPage& row) {
 5172    ind_page_id_Reserve(1);
 5173    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 5174    if (LIKELY(row.ind_page_id_next == (wcli::FPage*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 5175        u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, id_Get(row)) & (_db.ind_page_id_buckets_n - 1);
 5176        wcli::FPage* *prev = &_db.ind_page_id_buckets_elems[index];
 5177        do {
 5178            wcli::FPage* ret = *prev;
 5179            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 5180                break;
 5181            }
 5182            if (id_Get((*ret)) == id_Get(row)) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 5183                retval = false;
 5184                break;
 5185            }
 5186            prev = &ret->ind_page_id_next;
 5187        } while (true);
 5188        if (retval) {
 5189            row.ind_page_id_next = *prev;
 5190            _db.ind_page_id_n++;
 5191            *prev = &row;
 5192        }
 5193    }
 5194    return retval;
 5195}
 5196
 5197// --- wcli.FDb.ind_page_id.Remove
 5198// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 5199void wcli::ind_page_id_Remove(wcli::FPage& row) {
 5200    if (LIKELY(row.ind_page_id_next != (wcli::FPage*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 5201        u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, id_Get(row)) & (_db.ind_page_id_buckets_n - 1);
 5202        wcli::FPage* *prev = &_db.ind_page_id_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 5203        while (wcli::FPage *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 5204            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 5205                *prev = next->ind_page_id_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 5206                _db.ind_page_id_n--;
 5207                row.ind_page_id_next = (wcli::FPage*)-1;// not-in-hash
 5208                break;
 5209            }
 5210            prev = &next->ind_page_id_next;
 5211        }
 5212    }
 5213}
 5214
 5215// --- wcli.FDb.ind_page_id.Reserve
 5216// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 5217void wcli::ind_page_id_Reserve(int n) {
 5218    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_page_id_buckets_n;
 5219    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_page_id_n + n;
 5220    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 5221    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 5222        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 5223        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FPage*);
 5224        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FPage*);
 5225        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 5226        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 5227        wcli::FPage* *new_buckets = (wcli::FPage**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 5228        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 5229            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_page_id");
 5230        }
 5231        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 5232        // rehash all entries
 5233        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_page_id_buckets_n; i++) {
 5234            wcli::FPage* elem = _db.ind_page_id_buckets_elems[i];
 5235            while (elem) {
 5236                wcli::FPage &row        = *elem;
 5237                wcli::FPage* next       = row.ind_page_id_next;
 5238                u32 index          = algo::cstring_Hash(0, id_Get(row)) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 5239                row.ind_page_id_next     = new_buckets[index];
 5240                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 5241                elem               = next;
 5242            }
 5243        }
 5244        // free old array
 5245        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_page_id_buckets_elems, old_size);
 5246        _db.ind_page_id_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 5247        _db.ind_page_id_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 5248    }
 5249}

 5251// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdapi.Find
 5252// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 5253wcli::FWclicmdapi* wcli::ind_wclicmdapi_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 5254    u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_wclicmdapi_buckets_n - 1);
 5255    wcli::FWclicmdapi* *e = &_db.ind_wclicmdapi_buckets_elems[index];
 5256    wcli::FWclicmdapi* ret=NULL;
 5257    do {
 5258        ret       = *e;
 5259        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wclicmdapi == key;
 5260        if (done) break;
 5261        e         = &ret->ind_wclicmdapi_next;
 5262    } while (true);
 5263    return ret;
 5264}

 5274// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdapi.InsertMaybe
 5275// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 5276bool wcli::ind_wclicmdapi_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdapi& row) {
 5277    ind_wclicmdapi_Reserve(1);
 5278    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 5279    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wclicmdapi_next == (wcli::FWclicmdapi*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 5280        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdapi) & (_db.ind_wclicmdapi_buckets_n - 1);
 5281        wcli::FWclicmdapi* *prev = &_db.ind_wclicmdapi_buckets_elems[index];
 5282        do {
 5283            wcli::FWclicmdapi* ret = *prev;
 5284            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 5285                break;
 5286            }
 5287            if ((*ret).wclicmdapi == row.wclicmdapi) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 5288                retval = false;
 5289                break;
 5290            }
 5291            prev = &ret->ind_wclicmdapi_next;
 5292        } while (true);
 5293        if (retval) {
 5294            row.ind_wclicmdapi_next = *prev;
 5295            _db.ind_wclicmdapi_n++;
 5296            *prev = &row;
 5297        }
 5298    }
 5299    return retval;
 5300}

 5379// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdarg.GetOrCreate
 5380// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 5381wcli::FWclicmdarg& wcli::ind_wclicmdarg_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 5382    wcli::FWclicmdarg* ret = ind_wclicmdarg_Find(key);
 5383    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 5384        ret         = &wclicmdarg_Alloc();
 5385        (*ret).wclicmdarg = key;
 5386        bool good = wclicmdarg_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 5387        if (!good) {
 5388            wclicmdarg_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 5389            ret = NULL;
 5390        }
 5391    }
 5392    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_wclicmdarg  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 5393    return *ret;
 5394}

 5617wcli::FDclicmd& wcli::ind_dclicmd_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
 5618    wcli::FDclicmd* ret = ind_dclicmd_Find(key);
 5619    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_dclicmd  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
 5620    return *ret;
 5621}
 5622
 5623// --- wcli.FDb.ind_dclicmd.GetOrCreate
 5624// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 5625wcli::FDclicmd& wcli::ind_dclicmd_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 5626    wcli::FDclicmd* ret = ind_dclicmd_Find(key);
 5627    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 5628        ret         = &dclicmd_Alloc();
 5629        (*ret).dclicmd = key;
 5630        bool good = dclicmd_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 5631        if (!good) {
 5632            dclicmd_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 5633            ret = NULL;
 5634        }
 5635    }
 5636    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_dclicmd  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 5637    return *ret;
 5638}
 5639
 5640// --- wcli.FDb.ind_dclicmd.InsertMaybe
 5641// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 5642bool wcli::ind_dclicmd_InsertMaybe(wcli::FDclicmd& row) {
 5643    ind_dclicmd_Reserve(1);
 5644    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 5645    if (LIKELY(row.ind_dclicmd_next == (wcli::FDclicmd*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 5646        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.dclicmd) & (_db.ind_dclicmd_buckets_n - 1);
 5647        wcli::FDclicmd* *prev = &_db.ind_dclicmd_buckets_elems[index];
 5648        do {
 5649            wcli::FDclicmd* ret = *prev;
 5650            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 5651                break;
 5652            }
 5653            if ((*ret).dclicmd == row.dclicmd) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 5654                retval = false;
 5655                break;
 5656            }
 5657            prev = &ret->ind_dclicmd_next;
 5658        } while (true);
 5659        if (retval) {
 5660            row.ind_dclicmd_next = *prev;
 5661            _db.ind_dclicmd_n++;
 5662            *prev = &row;
 5663        }
 5664    }
 5665    return retval;
 5666}
 5667
 5668// --- wcli.FDb.ind_dclicmd.Remove
 5669// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 5670void wcli::ind_dclicmd_Remove(wcli::FDclicmd& row) {
 5671    if (LIKELY(row.ind_dclicmd_next != (wcli::FDclicmd*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 5672        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.dclicmd) & (_db.ind_dclicmd_buckets_n - 1);
 5673        wcli::FDclicmd* *prev = &_db.ind_dclicmd_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 5674        while (wcli::FDclicmd *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 5675            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 5676                *prev = next->ind_dclicmd_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 5677                _db.ind_dclicmd_n--;
 5678                row.ind_dclicmd_next = (wcli::FDclicmd*)-1;// not-in-hash
 5679                break;
 5680            }
 5681            prev = &next->ind_dclicmd_next;
 5682        }
 5683    }
 5684}
 5685
 5686// --- wcli.FDb.ind_dclicmd.Reserve
 5687// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 5688void wcli::ind_dclicmd_Reserve(int n) {
 5689    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_dclicmd_buckets_n;
 5690    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_dclicmd_n + n;
 5691    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 5692    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 5693        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 5694        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FDclicmd*);
 5695        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FDclicmd*);
 5696        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 5697        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 5698        wcli::FDclicmd* *new_buckets = (wcli::FDclicmd**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 5699        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 5700            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_dclicmd");
 5701        }
 5702        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 5703        // rehash all entries
 5704        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_dclicmd_buckets_n; i++) {
 5705            wcli::FDclicmd* elem = _db.ind_dclicmd_buckets_elems[i];
 5706            while (elem) {
 5707                wcli::FDclicmd &row        = *elem;
 5708                wcli::FDclicmd* next       = row.ind_dclicmd_next;
 5709                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.dclicmd) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 5710                row.ind_dclicmd_next     = new_buckets[index];
 5711                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 5712                elem               = next;
 5713            }
 5714        }
 5715        // free old array
 5716        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_dclicmd_buckets_elems, old_size);
 5717        _db.ind_dclicmd_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 5718        _db.ind_dclicmd_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 5719    }
 5720}
 5721
 5722// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmd.Find
 5723// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 5724wcli::FWclicmd* wcli::ind_wclicmd_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 5725    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_wclicmd_buckets_n - 1);
 5726    wcli::FWclicmd* *e = &_db.ind_wclicmd_buckets_elems[index];
 5727    wcli::FWclicmd* ret=NULL;
 5728    do {
 5729        ret       = *e;
 5730        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wclicmd == key;
 5731        if (done) break;
 5732        e         = &ret->ind_wclicmd_next;
 5733    } while (true);
 5734    return ret;
 5735}
 5736
 5737// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmd.FindX
 5738// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
 5739wcli::FWclicmd& wcli::ind_wclicmd_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
 5740    wcli::FWclicmd* ret = ind_wclicmd_Find(key);
 5741    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_wclicmd  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
 5742    return *ret;
 5743}
 5744
 5745// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmd.GetOrCreate
 5746// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 5747wcli::FWclicmd& wcli::ind_wclicmd_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 5748    wcli::FWclicmd* ret = ind_wclicmd_Find(key);
 5749    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 5750        ret         = &wclicmd_Alloc();
 5751        (*ret).wclicmd = key;
 5752        bool good = wclicmd_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 5753        if (!good) {
 5754            wclicmd_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 5755            ret = NULL;
 5756        }
 5757    }
 5758    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_wclicmd  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 5759    return *ret;
 5760}

 5764bool wcli::ind_wclicmd_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWclicmd& row) {

 5766    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 5767    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wclicmd_next == (wcli::FWclicmd*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 5768        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wclicmd) & (_db.ind_wclicmd_buckets_n - 1);
 5769        wcli::FWclicmd* *prev = &_db.ind_wclicmd_buckets_elems[index];
 5770        do {
 5771            wcli::FWclicmd* ret = *prev;
 5772            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 5773                break;
 5774            }
 5775            if ((*ret).wclicmd == row.wclicmd) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 5776                retval = false;
 5777                break;
 5778            }
 5779            prev = &ret->ind_wclicmd_next;
 5780        } while (true);
 5781        if (retval) {
 5782            row.ind_wclicmd_next = *prev;
 5783            _db.ind_wclicmd_n++;
 5784            *prev = &row;
 5785        }
 5786    }
 5787    return retval;
 5788}

 5795        wcli::FWclicmd* *prev = &_db.ind_wclicmd_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element

 5800                row.ind_wclicmd_next = (wcli::FWclicmd*)-1;// not-in-hash

 5808// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmd.Reserve
 5809// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 5810void wcli::ind_wclicmd_Reserve(int n) {
 5811    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wclicmd_buckets_n;
 5812    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wclicmd_n + n;
 5813    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 5814    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 5815        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 5816        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmd*);
 5817        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmd*);
 5818        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 5819        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 5820        wcli::FWclicmd* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWclicmd**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 5821        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 5822            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmd");
 5823        }
 5824        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 5825        // rehash all entries
 5826        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wclicmd_buckets_n; i++) {
 5827            wcli::FWclicmd* elem = _db.ind_wclicmd_buckets_elems[i];
 5828            while (elem) {
 5829                wcli::FWclicmd &row        = *elem;
 5830                wcli::FWclicmd* next       = row.ind_wclicmd_next;
 5831                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wclicmd) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 5832                row.ind_wclicmd_next     = new_buckets[index];
 5833                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 5834                elem               = next;
 5835            }
 5836        }
 5837        // free old array
 5838        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wclicmd_buckets_elems, old_size);
 5839        _db.ind_wclicmd_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 5840        _db.ind_wclicmd_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 5841    }
 5842}
 5843
 5844// --- wcli.FDb.wtbl.Alloc
 5845// Allocate memory for new default row.
 5846// If out of memory, process is killed.
 5847wcli::FWtbl& wcli::wtbl_Alloc() {
 5848    wcli::FWtbl* row = wtbl_AllocMaybe();
 5849    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 5850        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.wtbl  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 5851    }
 5852    return *row;
 5853}
 5854
 5855// --- wcli.FDb.wtbl.AllocMaybe
 5856// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 5857wcli::FWtbl* wcli::wtbl_AllocMaybe() {
 5858    wcli::FWtbl *row = (wcli::FWtbl*)wtbl_AllocMem();
 5859    if (row) {
 5860        new (row) wcli::FWtbl; // call constructor
 5861    }
 5862    return row;
 5863}
 5864
 5865// --- wcli.FDb.wtbl.InsertMaybe
 5866// Create new row from struct.
 5867// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 5868wcli::FWtbl* wcli::wtbl_InsertMaybe(const wclidb::Wtbl &value) {
 5869    wcli::FWtbl *row = &wtbl_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 5870    wtbl_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<wclidb::Wtbl&>(value));
 5871    bool ok = wtbl_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 5872    if (!ok) {
 5873        wtbl_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 5874        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 5875    }
 5876    return row;
 5877}
 5878
 5879// --- wcli.FDb.wtbl.AllocMem
 5880// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 5881void* wcli::wtbl_AllocMem() {
 5882    u64 new_nelems     = _db.wtbl_n+1;
 5883    // compute level and index on level
 5884    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 5885    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 5886    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 5887    void *ret = NULL;
 5888    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 5889    wcli::FWtbl*  lev   = NULL;
 5890    if (bsr < 32) {
 5891        lev = _db.wtbl_lary[bsr];
 5892        if (!lev) {
 5893            lev=(wcli::FWtbl*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FWtbl) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 5894            _db.wtbl_lary[bsr] = lev;
 5895        }
 5896    }
 5897    // allocate element from this level
 5898    if (lev) {
 5899        _db.wtbl_n = i32(new_nelems);
 5900        ret = lev + index;
 5901    }
 5902    return ret;
 5903}
 5904
 5905// --- wcli.FDb.wtbl.RemoveAll
 5906// Remove all elements from Lary
 5907void wcli::wtbl_RemoveAll() {
 5908    for (u64 n = _db.wtbl_n; n>0; ) {
 5909        n--;
 5910        wtbl_qFind(u64(n)).~FWtbl(); // destroy last element
 5911        _db.wtbl_n = i32(n);
 5912    }
 5913}
 5914
 5915// --- wcli.FDb.wtbl.RemoveLast
 5916// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 5917void wcli::wtbl_RemoveLast() {
 5918    u64 n = _db.wtbl_n;
 5919    if (n > 0) {
 5920        n -= 1;
 5921        wtbl_qFind(u64(n)).~FWtbl();
 5922        _db.wtbl_n = i32(n);
 5923    }
 5924}
 5925
 5926// --- wcli.FDb.wtbl.InputMaybe
 5927static bool wcli::wtbl_InputMaybe(wclidb::Wtbl &elem) {
 5928    bool retval = true;
 5929    retval = wtbl_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
 5930    return retval;
 5931}
 5932
 5933// --- wcli.FDb.wtbl.XrefMaybe
 5934// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 5935// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 5936bool wcli::wtbl_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWtbl &row) {
 5937    bool retval = true;
 5938    (void)row;
 5939    // insert wtbl into index ind_wtbl
 5940    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 5941        bool success = ind_wtbl_InsertMaybe(row);
 5942        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 5943            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 5944            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_wtbl"; // check for duplicate key
 5945            return false;
 5946        }
 5947    }
 5948    return retval;
 5949}

 5958        ret       = *e;
 5959        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wtbl == key;
 5960        if (done) break;
 5961        e         = &ret->ind_wtbl_next;
 5962    } while (true);
 5963    return ret;
 5964}

 5996    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wtbl_next == (wcli::FWtbl*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 5997        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wtbl) & (_db.ind_wtbl_buckets_n - 1);
 5998        wcli::FWtbl* *prev = &_db.ind_wtbl_buckets_elems[index];
 5999        do {
 6000            wcli::FWtbl* ret = *prev;
 6001            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 6002                break;
 6003            }
 6004            if ((*ret).wtbl == row.wtbl) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 6005                retval = false;
 6006                break;
 6007            }

 6009        } while (true);

 6011            row.ind_wtbl_next = *prev;
 6012            _db.ind_wtbl_n++;
 6013            *prev = &row;
 6014        }
 6015    }
 6016    return retval;
 6017}

 6073// --- wcli.FDb.wact.Alloc
 6074// Allocate memory for new default row.
 6075// If out of memory, process is killed.
 6076wcli::FWact& wcli::wact_Alloc() {
 6077    wcli::FWact* row = wact_AllocMaybe();
 6078    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 6079        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.wact  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 6080    }

 6082}
 6083
 6084// --- wcli.FDb.wact.AllocMaybe
 6085// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 6086wcli::FWact* wcli::wact_AllocMaybe() {
 6087    wcli::FWact *row = (wcli::FWact*)wact_AllocMem();
 6088    if (row) {
 6089        new (row) wcli::FWact; // call constructor
 6090    }
 6091    return row;
 6092}
 6093
 6094// --- wcli.FDb.wact.InsertMaybe
 6095// Create new row from struct.
 6096// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 6097wcli::FWact* wcli::wact_InsertMaybe(const wclidb::Wact &value) {
 6098    wcli::FWact *row = &wact_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 6099    wact_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<wclidb::Wact&>(value));
 6100    bool ok = wact_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 6101    if (!ok) {
 6102        wact_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 6103        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 6104    }
 6105    return row;
 6106}
 6107
 6108// --- wcli.FDb.wact.AllocMem
 6109// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 6110void* wcli::wact_AllocMem() {
 6111    u64 new_nelems     = _db.wact_n+1;
 6112    // compute level and index on level
 6113    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 6114    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 6115    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 6116    void *ret = NULL;
 6117    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 6118    wcli::FWact*  lev   = NULL;
 6119    if (bsr < 32) {
 6120        lev = _db.wact_lary[bsr];
 6121        if (!lev) {
 6122            lev=(wcli::FWact*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FWact) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 6123            _db.wact_lary[bsr] = lev;
 6124        }
 6125    }
 6126    // allocate element from this level
 6127    if (lev) {
 6128        _db.wact_n = i32(new_nelems);
 6129        ret = lev + index;
 6130    }
 6131    return ret;
 6132}
 6133
 6134// --- wcli.FDb.wact.RemoveAll
 6135// Remove all elements from Lary
 6136void wcli::wact_RemoveAll() {
 6137    for (u64 n = _db.wact_n; n>0; ) {
 6138        n--;
 6139        wact_qFind(u64(n)).~FWact(); // destroy last element
 6140        _db.wact_n = i32(n);
 6141    }
 6142}
 6143
 6144// --- wcli.FDb.wact.RemoveLast
 6145// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 6146void wcli::wact_RemoveLast() {
 6147    u64 n = _db.wact_n;
 6148    if (n > 0) {
 6149        n -= 1;
 6150        wact_qFind(u64(n)).~FWact();
 6151        _db.wact_n = i32(n);
 6152    }
 6153}
 6154
 6155// --- wcli.FDb.wact.InputMaybe
 6156static bool wcli::wact_InputMaybe(wclidb::Wact &elem) {
 6157    bool retval = true;
 6158    retval = wact_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
 6159    return retval;
 6160}
 6161
 6162// --- wcli.FDb.wact.XrefMaybe
 6163// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 6164// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 6165bool wcli::wact_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWact &row) {
 6166    bool retval = true;
 6167    (void)row;
 6168    // insert wact into index ind_wact
 6169    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 6170        bool success = ind_wact_InsertMaybe(row);
 6171        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 6172            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 6173            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_wact"; // check for duplicate key
 6174            return false;
 6175        }
 6176    }
 6177    return retval;
 6178}
 6179
 6180// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wact.Find
 6181// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 6182wcli::FWact* wcli::ind_wact_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 6183    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_wact_buckets_n - 1);
 6184    wcli::FWact* *e = &_db.ind_wact_buckets_elems[index];
 6185    wcli::FWact* ret=NULL;
 6186    do {
 6187        ret       = *e;
 6188        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wact == key;
 6189        if (done) break;
 6190        e         = &ret->ind_wact_next;
 6191    } while (true);
 6192    return ret;
 6193}
 6194
 6195// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wact.FindX
 6196// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
 6197wcli::FWact& wcli::ind_wact_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
 6198    wcli::FWact* ret = ind_wact_Find(key);
 6199    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_wact  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
 6200    return *ret;
 6201}
 6202
 6203// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wact.GetOrCreate
 6204// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 6205wcli::FWact& wcli::ind_wact_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 6206    wcli::FWact* ret = ind_wact_Find(key);
 6207    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 6208        ret         = &wact_Alloc();
 6209        (*ret).wact = key;
 6210        bool good = wact_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 6211        if (!good) {
 6212            wact_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 6213            ret = NULL;
 6214        }
 6215    }
 6216    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_wact  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 6217    return *ret;
 6218}
 6219
 6220// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wact.InsertMaybe
 6221// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 6222bool wcli::ind_wact_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWact& row) {
 6223    ind_wact_Reserve(1);
 6224    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 6225    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wact_next == (wcli::FWact*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 6226        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wact) & (_db.ind_wact_buckets_n - 1);
 6227        wcli::FWact* *prev = &_db.ind_wact_buckets_elems[index];
 6228        do {
 6229            wcli::FWact* ret = *prev;
 6230            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 6231                break;
 6232            }
 6233            if ((*ret).wact == row.wact) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 6234                retval = false;
 6235                break;
 6236            }
 6237            prev = &ret->ind_wact_next;
 6238        } while (true);
 6239        if (retval) {
 6240            row.ind_wact_next = *prev;
 6241            _db.ind_wact_n++;
 6242            *prev = &row;
 6243        }
 6244    }
 6245    return retval;
 6246}
 6247
 6248// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wact.Remove
 6249// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 6250void wcli::ind_wact_Remove(wcli::FWact& row) {
 6251    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wact_next != (wcli::FWact*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 6252        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wact) & (_db.ind_wact_buckets_n - 1);
 6253        wcli::FWact* *prev = &_db.ind_wact_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 6254        while (wcli::FWact *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 6255            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 6256                *prev = next->ind_wact_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 6257                _db.ind_wact_n--;
 6258                row.ind_wact_next = (wcli::FWact*)-1;// not-in-hash
 6259                break;
 6260            }
 6261            prev = &next->ind_wact_next;
 6262        }
 6263    }
 6264}
 6265
 6266// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wact.Reserve
 6267// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 6268void wcli::ind_wact_Reserve(int n) {
 6269    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wact_buckets_n;
 6270    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wact_n + n;
 6271    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 6272    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 6273        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 6274        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWact*);
 6275        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWact*);
 6276        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 6277        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 6278        wcli::FWact* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWact**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 6279        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 6280            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wact");
 6281        }
 6282        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 6283        // rehash all entries
 6284        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wact_buckets_n; i++) {
 6285            wcli::FWact* elem = _db.ind_wact_buckets_elems[i];
 6286            while (elem) {
 6287                wcli::FWact &row        = *elem;
 6288                wcli::FWact* next       = row.ind_wact_next;
 6289                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wact) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 6290                row.ind_wact_next     = new_buckets[index];
 6291                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 6292                elem               = next;
 6293            }
 6294        }
 6295        // free old array
 6296        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wact_buckets_elems, old_size);
 6297        _db.ind_wact_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 6298        _db.ind_wact_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 6299    }
 6300}

 6495// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wwiki.Reserve
 6496// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 6497void wcli::ind_wwiki_Reserve(int n) {
 6498    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wwiki_buckets_n;
 6499    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wwiki_n + n;
 6500    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 6501    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 6502        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 6503        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWwiki*);
 6504        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWwiki*);
 6505        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 6506        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 6507        wcli::FWwiki* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWwiki**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 6508        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 6509            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wwiki");
 6510        }
 6511        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 6512        // rehash all entries
 6513        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wwiki_buckets_n; i++) {

 6515            while (elem) {

 6519                row.ind_wwiki_next     = new_buckets[index];
 6520                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 6521                elem               = next;
 6522            }
 6523        }
 6524        // free old array
 6525        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wwiki_buckets_elems, old_size);
 6526        _db.ind_wwiki_buckets_elems = new_buckets;

 6529}

 6588// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdargsub.RemoveLast
 6589// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 6590void wcli::wclicmdargsub_RemoveLast() {
 6591    u64 n = _db.wclicmdargsub_n;
 6592    if (n > 0) {
 6593        n -= 1;
 6594        wclicmdargsub_qFind(u64(n)).~FWclicmdargsub();
 6595        _db.wclicmdargsub_n = i32(n);
 6596    }
 6597}
 6598
 6599// --- wcli.FDb.wclicmdargsub.XrefMaybe
 6600// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 6601// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 6602bool wcli::wclicmdargsub_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdargsub &row) {
 6603    bool retval = true;
 6604    (void)row;
 6605    wcli::FWclicmdapi* p_sub = wcli::ind_wclicmdapi_Find(sub_Get(row));
 6606    if (UNLIKELY(!p_sub)) {
 6607        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "wcli.bad_xref  index:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdapi" << Keyval("key", sub_Get(row));
 6608        return false;
 6609    }
 6610    // wclicmdargsub: save pointer to sub
 6611    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 6612        row.p_wclicmdapi = p_sub;
 6613    }
 6614    wcli::FWclicmdarg* p_wclicmdarg = wcli::ind_wclicmdarg_Find(wclicmdarg_Get(row));
 6615    if (UNLIKELY(!p_wclicmdarg)) {
 6616        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "wcli.bad_xref  index:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdarg" << Keyval("key", wclicmdarg_Get(row));
 6617        return false;
 6618    }
 6619    // insert wclicmdargsub into index c_wclicmdargsub
 6620    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 6621        c_wclicmdargsub_Insert(*p_wclicmdarg, row);
 6622    }
 6623    // insert wclicmdargsub into index ind_wclicmdargsub
 6624    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 6625        bool success = ind_wclicmdargsub_InsertMaybe(row);
 6626        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 6627            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 6628            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdargsub"; // check for duplicate key
 6629            return false;
 6630        }
 6631    }
 6632    return retval;
 6633}
 6634
 6635// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdargsub.Find
 6636// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 6637wcli::FWclicmdargsub* wcli::ind_wclicmdargsub_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 6638    u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_wclicmdargsub_buckets_n - 1);
 6639    wcli::FWclicmdargsub* *e = &_db.ind_wclicmdargsub_buckets_elems[index];
 6640    wcli::FWclicmdargsub* ret=NULL;
 6641    do {
 6642        ret       = *e;
 6643        bool done = !ret || (*ret).wclicmdargsub == key;
 6644        if (done) break;
 6645        e         = &ret->ind_wclicmdargsub_next;
 6646    } while (true);
 6647    return ret;
 6648}
 6649
 6650// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdargsub.FindX
 6651// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
 6652wcli::FWclicmdargsub& wcli::ind_wclicmdargsub_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
 6653    wcli::FWclicmdargsub* ret = ind_wclicmdargsub_Find(key);
 6654    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_wclicmdargsub  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
 6655    return *ret;
 6656}
 6657
 6658// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdargsub.InsertMaybe
 6659// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 6660bool wcli::ind_wclicmdargsub_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdargsub& row) {
 6661    ind_wclicmdargsub_Reserve(1);
 6662    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 6663    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wclicmdargsub_next == (wcli::FWclicmdargsub*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 6664        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdargsub) & (_db.ind_wclicmdargsub_buckets_n - 1);
 6665        wcli::FWclicmdargsub* *prev = &_db.ind_wclicmdargsub_buckets_elems[index];
 6666        do {
 6667            wcli::FWclicmdargsub* ret = *prev;
 6668            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 6669                break;
 6670            }
 6671            if ((*ret).wclicmdargsub == row.wclicmdargsub) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 6672                retval = false;
 6673                break;
 6674            }
 6675            prev = &ret->ind_wclicmdargsub_next;
 6676        } while (true);
 6677        if (retval) {
 6678            row.ind_wclicmdargsub_next = *prev;
 6679            _db.ind_wclicmdargsub_n++;
 6680            *prev = &row;
 6681        }
 6682    }
 6683    return retval;
 6684}
 6685
 6686// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdargsub.Remove
 6687// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 6688void wcli::ind_wclicmdargsub_Remove(wcli::FWclicmdargsub& row) {
 6689    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wclicmdargsub_next != (wcli::FWclicmdargsub*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 6690        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdargsub) & (_db.ind_wclicmdargsub_buckets_n - 1);
 6691        wcli::FWclicmdargsub* *prev = &_db.ind_wclicmdargsub_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 6692        while (wcli::FWclicmdargsub *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 6693            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 6694                *prev = next->ind_wclicmdargsub_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 6695                _db.ind_wclicmdargsub_n--;
 6696                row.ind_wclicmdargsub_next = (wcli::FWclicmdargsub*)-1;// not-in-hash
 6697                break;
 6698            }
 6699            prev = &next->ind_wclicmdargsub_next;
 6700        }
 6701    }
 6702}
 6703
 6704// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdargsub.Reserve
 6705// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 6706void wcli::ind_wclicmdargsub_Reserve(int n) {
 6707    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wclicmdargsub_buckets_n;
 6708    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wclicmdargsub_n + n;
 6709    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 6710    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 6711        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 6712        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdargsub*);
 6713        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdargsub*);
 6714        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 6715        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 6716        wcli::FWclicmdargsub* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWclicmdargsub**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 6717        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 6718            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdargsub");
 6719        }
 6720        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 6721        // rehash all entries
 6722        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wclicmdargsub_buckets_n; i++) {
 6723            wcli::FWclicmdargsub* elem = _db.ind_wclicmdargsub_buckets_elems[i];
 6724            while (elem) {
 6725                wcli::FWclicmdargsub &row        = *elem;
 6726                wcli::FWclicmdargsub* next       = row.ind_wclicmdargsub_next;
 6727                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wclicmdargsub) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 6728                row.ind_wclicmdargsub_next     = new_buckets[index];
 6729                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 6730                elem               = next;
 6731            }
 6732        }
 6733        // free old array
 6734        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wclicmdargsub_buckets_elems, old_size);
 6735        _db.ind_wclicmdargsub_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 6736        _db.ind_wclicmdargsub_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 6737    }
 6738}
 6739
 6740// --- wcli.FDb.wikitokenapi.Alloc
 6741// Allocate memory for new default row.
 6742// If out of memory, process is killed.
 6743wcli::FWikitokenapi& wcli::wikitokenapi_Alloc() {
 6744    wcli::FWikitokenapi* row = wikitokenapi_AllocMaybe();
 6745    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 6746        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.wikitokenapi  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 6747    }
 6748    return *row;
 6749}
 6750
 6751// --- wcli.FDb.wikitokenapi.AllocMaybe
 6752// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 6753wcli::FWikitokenapi* wcli::wikitokenapi_AllocMaybe() {
 6754    wcli::FWikitokenapi *row = (wcli::FWikitokenapi*)wikitokenapi_AllocMem();
 6755    if (row) {
 6756        new (row) wcli::FWikitokenapi; // call constructor
 6757    }
 6758    return row;
 6759}
 6760
 6761// --- wcli.FDb.wikitokenapi.InsertMaybe
 6762// Create new row from struct.
 6763// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 6764wcli::FWikitokenapi* wcli::wikitokenapi_InsertMaybe(const wclidb::Wikitokenapi &value) {
 6765    wcli::FWikitokenapi *row = &wikitokenapi_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 6766    wikitokenapi_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<wclidb::Wikitokenapi&>(value));
 6767    bool ok = wikitokenapi_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 6768    if (!ok) {
 6769        wikitokenapi_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 6770        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 6771    }
 6772    return row;
 6773}
 6774
 6775// --- wcli.FDb.wikitokenapi.AllocMem
 6776// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 6777void* wcli::wikitokenapi_AllocMem() {
 6778    u64 new_nelems     = _db.wikitokenapi_n+1;
 6779    // compute level and index on level
 6780    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 6781    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 6782    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 6783    void *ret = NULL;
 6784    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 6785    wcli::FWikitokenapi*  lev   = NULL;
 6786    if (bsr < 32) {
 6787        lev = _db.wikitokenapi_lary[bsr];
 6788        if (!lev) {
 6789            lev=(wcli::FWikitokenapi*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FWikitokenapi) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 6790            _db.wikitokenapi_lary[bsr] = lev;
 6791        }
 6792    }
 6793    // allocate element from this level
 6794    if (lev) {
 6795        _db.wikitokenapi_n = i32(new_nelems);
 6796        ret = lev + index;
 6797    }
 6798    return ret;
 6799}
 6800
 6801// --- wcli.FDb.wikitokenapi.RemoveAll
 6802// Remove all elements from Lary
 6803void wcli::wikitokenapi_RemoveAll() {
 6804    for (u64 n = _db.wikitokenapi_n; n>0; ) {
 6805        n--;
 6806        wikitokenapi_qFind(u64(n)).~FWikitokenapi(); // destroy last element
 6807        _db.wikitokenapi_n = i32(n);
 6808    }
 6809}
 6810
 6811// --- wcli.FDb.wikitokenapi.RemoveLast
 6812// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 6813void wcli::wikitokenapi_RemoveLast() {
 6814    u64 n = _db.wikitokenapi_n;
 6815    if (n > 0) {
 6816        n -= 1;
 6817        wikitokenapi_qFind(u64(n)).~FWikitokenapi();
 6818        _db.wikitokenapi_n = i32(n);
 6819    }
 6820}
 6821
 6822// --- wcli.FDb.wikitokenapi.InputMaybe
 6823static bool wcli::wikitokenapi_InputMaybe(wclidb::Wikitokenapi &elem) {
 6824    bool retval = true;
 6825    retval = wikitokenapi_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
 6826    return retval;
 6827}

 6829// --- wcli.FDb.wikitokenapi.XrefMaybe
 6830// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 6831// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 6832bool wcli::wikitokenapi_XrefMaybe(wcli::FWikitokenapi &row) {
 6833    bool retval = true;
 6834    (void)row;
 6835    wcli::FWclicmdapi* p_wclicmdapi = wcli::ind_wclicmdapi_Find(wclicmdapi_Get(row));
 6836    if (UNLIKELY(!p_wclicmdapi)) {
 6837        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "wcli.bad_xref  index:wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdapi" << Keyval("key", wclicmdapi_Get(row));
 6838        return false;
 6839    }
 6840    // wikitokenapi: save pointer to wclicmdapi
 6841    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 6842        row.p_wclicmdapi = p_wclicmdapi;
 6843    }
 6844    wcli::FWikitoken* p_wikitoken = wcli::ind_wikitoken_Find(wikitoken_Get(row));
 6845    if (UNLIKELY(!p_wikitoken)) {
 6846        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "wcli.bad_xref  index:wcli.FDb.ind_wikitoken" << Keyval("key", wikitoken_Get(row));
 6847        return false;
 6848    }
 6849    // insert wikitokenapi into index c_wikitokenapi
 6850    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 6851        c_wikitokenapi_Insert(*p_wikitoken, row);
 6852    }
 6853    return retval;
 6854}

 6879// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikins.InsertMaybe
 6880// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 6881bool wcli::ind_wikins_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWikins& row) {
 6882    ind_wikins_Reserve(1);
 6883    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 6884    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wikins_next == (wcli::FWikins*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 6885        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wikins) & (_db.ind_wikins_buckets_n - 1);
 6886        wcli::FWikins* *prev = &_db.ind_wikins_buckets_elems[index];
 6887        do {
 6888            wcli::FWikins* ret = *prev;
 6889            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 6890                break;
 6891            }
 6892            if ((*ret).wikins == row.wikins) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 6893                retval = false;
 6894                break;
 6895            }
 6896            prev = &ret->ind_wikins_next;
 6897        } while (true);
 6898        if (retval) {
 6899            row.ind_wikins_next = *prev;
 6900            _db.ind_wikins_n++;
 6901            *prev = &row;
 6902        }
 6903    }
 6904    return retval;
 6905}

 6909void wcli::ind_wikins_Remove(wcli::FWikins& row) {
 6910    if (LIKELY(row.ind_wikins_next != (wcli::FWikins*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 6911        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wikins) & (_db.ind_wikins_buckets_n - 1);
 6912        wcli::FWikins* *prev = &_db.ind_wikins_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 6913        while (wcli::FWikins *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 6914            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 6915                *prev = next->ind_wikins_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 6916                _db.ind_wikins_n--;
 6917                row.ind_wikins_next = (wcli::FWikins*)-1;// not-in-hash
 6918                break;

 6925// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikins.Reserve
 6926// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 6927void wcli::ind_wikins_Reserve(int n) {
 6928    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wikins_buckets_n;
 6929    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wikins_n + n;
 6930    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 6931    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 6932        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 6933        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWikins*);
 6934        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWikins*);
 6935        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 6936        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 6937        wcli::FWikins* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWikins**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 6938        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 6939            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wikins");
 6940        }
 6941        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 6942        // rehash all entries
 6943        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wikins_buckets_n; i++) {
 6944            wcli::FWikins* elem = _db.ind_wikins_buckets_elems[i];
 6945            while (elem) {
 6946                wcli::FWikins &row        = *elem;
 6947                wcli::FWikins* next       = row.ind_wikins_next;
 6948                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.wikins) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 6949                row.ind_wikins_next     = new_buckets[index];
 6950                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 6951                elem               = next;
 6952            }
 6953        }
 6954        // free old array
 6955        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wikins_buckets_elems, old_size);
 6956        _db.ind_wikins_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 6957        _db.ind_wikins_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 6958    }
 6959}

 7030// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikins_id.Reserve
 7031// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 7032void wcli::ind_wikins_id_Reserve(int n) {
 7033    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wikins_id_buckets_n;
 7034    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wikins_id_n + n;
 7035    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 7036    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 7037        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 7038        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWikins*);
 7039        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWikins*);
 7040        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 7041        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 7042        wcli::FWikins* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWikins**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 7043        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 7044            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wikins_id");
 7045        }
 7046        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 7047        // rehash all entries
 7048        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wikins_id_buckets_n; i++) {
 7049            wcli::FWikins* elem = _db.ind_wikins_id_buckets_elems[i];
 7050            while (elem) {
 7051                wcli::FWikins &row        = *elem;
 7052                wcli::FWikins* next       = row.ind_wikins_id_next;
 7053                u32 index          = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.id) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 7054                row.ind_wikins_id_next     = new_buckets[index];
 7055                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 7056                elem               = next;
 7057            }
 7058        }
 7059        // free old array
 7060        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wikins_id_buckets_elems, old_size);
 7061        _db.ind_wikins_id_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 7062        _db.ind_wikins_id_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 7063    }
 7064}
 7065
 7066// --- wcli.FDb.pagesec.Alloc
 7067// Allocate memory for new default row.
 7068// If out of memory, process is killed.
 7069wcli::FPagesec& wcli::pagesec_Alloc() {
 7070    wcli::FPagesec* row = pagesec_AllocMaybe();
 7071    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 7072        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.pagesec  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 7073    }
 7074    return *row;
 7075}
 7076
 7077// --- wcli.FDb.pagesec.AllocMaybe
 7078// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 7079wcli::FPagesec* wcli::pagesec_AllocMaybe() {
 7080    wcli::FPagesec *row = (wcli::FPagesec*)pagesec_AllocMem();
 7081    if (row) {
 7082        new (row) wcli::FPagesec; // call constructor
 7083    }
 7084    return row;
 7085}
 7086
 7087// --- wcli.FDb.pagesec.InsertMaybe
 7088// Create new row from struct.
 7089// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 7090wcli::FPagesec* wcli::pagesec_InsertMaybe(const wclidb::Pagesec &value) {
 7091    wcli::FPagesec *row = &pagesec_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 7092    pagesec_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<wclidb::Pagesec&>(value));
 7093    bool ok = pagesec_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 7094    if (!ok) {
 7095        pagesec_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 7096        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 7097    }
 7098    return row;
 7099}
 7100
 7101// --- wcli.FDb.pagesec.AllocMem
 7102// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 7103void* wcli::pagesec_AllocMem() {
 7104    u64 new_nelems     = _db.pagesec_n+1;
 7105    // compute level and index on level
 7106    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 7107    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 7108    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 7109    void *ret = NULL;
 7110    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 7111    wcli::FPagesec*  lev   = NULL;
 7112    if (bsr < 32) {
 7113        lev = _db.pagesec_lary[bsr];
 7114        if (!lev) {
 7115            lev=(wcli::FPagesec*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FPagesec) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 7116            _db.pagesec_lary[bsr] = lev;
 7117        }
 7118    }
 7119    // allocate element from this level
 7120    if (lev) {
 7121        _db.pagesec_n = i32(new_nelems);
 7122        ret = lev + index;
 7123    }
 7124    return ret;
 7125}
 7126
 7127// --- wcli.FDb.pagesec.RemoveAll
 7128// Remove all elements from Lary
 7129void wcli::pagesec_RemoveAll() {
 7130    for (u64 n = _db.pagesec_n; n>0; ) {
 7131        n--;
 7132        pagesec_qFind(u64(n)).~FPagesec(); // destroy last element
 7133        _db.pagesec_n = i32(n);
 7134    }
 7135}
 7136
 7137// --- wcli.FDb.pagesec.RemoveLast
 7138// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 7139void wcli::pagesec_RemoveLast() {
 7140    u64 n = _db.pagesec_n;
 7141    if (n > 0) {
 7142        n -= 1;
 7143        pagesec_qFind(u64(n)).~FPagesec();
 7144        _db.pagesec_n = i32(n);
 7145    }
 7146}
 7147
 7148// --- wcli.FDb.pagesec.InputMaybe
 7149static bool wcli::pagesec_InputMaybe(wclidb::Pagesec &elem) {
 7150    bool retval = true;
 7151    retval = pagesec_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
 7152    return retval;
 7153}
 7154
 7155// --- wcli.FDb.pagesec.XrefMaybe
 7156// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 7157// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 7158bool wcli::pagesec_XrefMaybe(wcli::FPagesec &row) {
 7159    bool retval = true;
 7160    (void)row;
 7161    // insert pagesec into index ind_pagesec
 7162    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 7163        bool success = ind_pagesec_InsertMaybe(row);
 7164        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 7165            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 7166            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_pagesec"; // check for duplicate key
 7167            return false;
 7168        }
 7169    }
 7170    wcli::FPage* p_page = wcli::ind_page_Find(page_Get(row));
 7171    if (UNLIKELY(!p_page)) {
 7172        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "wcli.bad_xref  index:wcli.FDb.ind_page" << Keyval("key", page_Get(row));
 7173        return false;
 7174    }
 7175    // insert pagesec into index c_pagesec
 7176    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 7177        c_pagesec_Insert(*p_page, row);
 7178    }
 7179    return retval;
 7180}
 7181
 7182// --- wcli.FDb.ind_pagesec.Find
 7183// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 7184wcli::FPagesec* wcli::ind_pagesec_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 7185    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_pagesec_buckets_n - 1);
 7186    wcli::FPagesec* *e = &_db.ind_pagesec_buckets_elems[index];
 7187    wcli::FPagesec* ret=NULL;
 7188    do {
 7189        ret       = *e;
 7190        bool done = !ret || (*ret).pagesec == key;
 7191        if (done) break;
 7192        e         = &ret->ind_pagesec_next;
 7193    } while (true);
 7194    return ret;
 7195}
 7196
 7197// --- wcli.FDb.ind_pagesec.FindX
 7198// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
 7199wcli::FPagesec& wcli::ind_pagesec_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
 7200    wcli::FPagesec* ret = ind_pagesec_Find(key);
 7201    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_pagesec  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
 7202    return *ret;
 7203}
 7204
 7205// --- wcli.FDb.ind_pagesec.InsertMaybe
 7206// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 7207bool wcli::ind_pagesec_InsertMaybe(wcli::FPagesec& row) {
 7208    ind_pagesec_Reserve(1);
 7209    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 7210    if (LIKELY(row.ind_pagesec_next == (wcli::FPagesec*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 7211        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.pagesec) & (_db.ind_pagesec_buckets_n - 1);
 7212        wcli::FPagesec* *prev = &_db.ind_pagesec_buckets_elems[index];
 7213        do {
 7214            wcli::FPagesec* ret = *prev;
 7215            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 7216                break;
 7217            }
 7218            if ((*ret).pagesec == row.pagesec) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 7219                retval = false;
 7220                break;
 7221            }
 7222            prev = &ret->ind_pagesec_next;
 7223        } while (true);
 7224        if (retval) {
 7225            row.ind_pagesec_next = *prev;
 7226            _db.ind_pagesec_n++;
 7227            *prev = &row;
 7228        }
 7229    }
 7230    return retval;
 7231}
 7232
 7233// --- wcli.FDb.ind_pagesec.Remove
 7234// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 7235void wcli::ind_pagesec_Remove(wcli::FPagesec& row) {
 7236    if (LIKELY(row.ind_pagesec_next != (wcli::FPagesec*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 7237        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.pagesec) & (_db.ind_pagesec_buckets_n - 1);
 7238        wcli::FPagesec* *prev = &_db.ind_pagesec_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 7239        while (wcli::FPagesec *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 7240            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 7241                *prev = next->ind_pagesec_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 7242                _db.ind_pagesec_n--;
 7243                row.ind_pagesec_next = (wcli::FPagesec*)-1;// not-in-hash
 7244                break;
 7245            }
 7246            prev = &next->ind_pagesec_next;
 7247        }
 7248    }
 7249}
 7250
 7251// --- wcli.FDb.ind_pagesec.Reserve
 7252// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 7253void wcli::ind_pagesec_Reserve(int n) {
 7254    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_pagesec_buckets_n;
 7255    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_pagesec_n + n;
 7256    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 7257    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 7258        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 7259        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FPagesec*);
 7260        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FPagesec*);
 7261        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 7262        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 7263        wcli::FPagesec* *new_buckets = (wcli::FPagesec**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 7264        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 7265            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_pagesec");
 7266        }
 7267        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 7268        // rehash all entries
 7269        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_pagesec_buckets_n; i++) {
 7270            wcli::FPagesec* elem = _db.ind_pagesec_buckets_elems[i];
 7271            while (elem) {
 7272                wcli::FPagesec &row        = *elem;
 7273                wcli::FPagesec* next       = row.ind_pagesec_next;
 7274                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.pagesec) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 7275                row.ind_pagesec_next     = new_buckets[index];
 7276                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 7277                elem               = next;
 7278            }
 7279        }
 7280        // free old array
 7281        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_pagesec_buckets_elems, old_size);
 7282        _db.ind_pagesec_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 7283        _db.ind_pagesec_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 7284    }
 7285}

 7417// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikiext.GetOrCreate
 7418// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 7419wcli::FWikiext& wcli::ind_wikiext_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 7420    wcli::FWikiext* ret = ind_wikiext_Find(key);
 7421    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 7422        ret         = &wikiext_Alloc();
 7423        (*ret).wikiext = key;
 7424        bool good = wikiext_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 7425        if (!good) {
 7426            wikiext_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 7427            ret = NULL;
 7428        }
 7429    }
 7430    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_wikiext  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 7431    return *ret;
 7432}

 7459    return retval;
 7460}
