 7480// --- wcli.FDb.ind_wikiext.Reserve
 7481// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 7482void wcli::ind_wikiext_Reserve(int n) {
 7483    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_wikiext_buckets_n;
 7484    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_wikiext_n + n;
 7485    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 7486    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 7487        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 7488        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWikiext*);
 7489        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FWikiext*);
 7490        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 7491        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 7492        wcli::FWikiext* *new_buckets = (wcli::FWikiext**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 7493        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 7494            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_wikiext");
 7495        }
 7496        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 7497        // rehash all entries
 7498        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_wikiext_buckets_n; i++) {
 7499            wcli::FWikiext* elem = _db.ind_wikiext_buckets_elems[i];
 7500            while (elem) {
 7501                wcli::FWikiext &row        = *elem;
 7502                wcli::FWikiext* next       = row.ind_wikiext_next;
 7503                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.wikiext) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 7504                row.ind_wikiext_next     = new_buckets[index];
 7505                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 7506                elem               = next;
 7507            }
 7508        }
 7509        // free old array
 7510        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_wikiext_buckets_elems, old_size);
 7511        _db.ind_wikiext_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 7512        _db.ind_wikiext_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 7513    }
 7514}
 7515
 7516// --- wcli.FDb.ftypefile.Alloc
 7517// Allocate memory for new default row.
 7518// If out of memory, process is killed.
 7519wcli::FFtypefile& wcli::ftypefile_Alloc() {
 7520    wcli::FFtypefile* row = ftypefile_AllocMaybe();
 7521    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 7522        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.ftypefile  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 7523    }
 7524    return *row;
 7525}
 7526
 7527// --- wcli.FDb.ftypefile.AllocMaybe
 7528// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 7529wcli::FFtypefile* wcli::ftypefile_AllocMaybe() {
 7530    wcli::FFtypefile *row = (wcli::FFtypefile*)ftypefile_AllocMem();
 7531    if (row) {
 7532        new (row) wcli::FFtypefile; // call constructor
 7533    }
 7534    return row;
 7535}
 7536
 7537// --- wcli.FDb.ftypefile.AllocMem
 7538// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 7539void* wcli::ftypefile_AllocMem() {
 7540    u64 new_nelems     = _db.ftypefile_n+1;
 7541    // compute level and index on level
 7542    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 7543    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 7544    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 7545    void *ret = NULL;
 7546    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 7547    wcli::FFtypefile*  lev   = NULL;
 7548    if (bsr < 32) {
 7549        lev = _db.ftypefile_lary[bsr];
 7550        if (!lev) {
 7551            lev=(wcli::FFtypefile*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FFtypefile) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 7552            _db.ftypefile_lary[bsr] = lev;
 7553        }
 7554    }
 7555    // allocate element from this level
 7556    if (lev) {
 7557        _db.ftypefile_n = i32(new_nelems);
 7558        ret = lev + index;
 7559    }
 7560    return ret;
 7561}
 7562
 7563// --- wcli.FDb.ftypefile.RemoveAll
 7564// Remove all elements from Lary
 7565void wcli::ftypefile_RemoveAll() {
 7566    for (u64 n = _db.ftypefile_n; n>0; ) {
 7567        n--;
 7568        ftypefile_qFind(u64(n)).~FFtypefile(); // destroy last element
 7569        _db.ftypefile_n = i32(n);
 7570    }
 7571}
 7572
 7573// --- wcli.FDb.ftypefile.RemoveLast
 7574// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 7575void wcli::ftypefile_RemoveLast() {
 7576    u64 n = _db.ftypefile_n;
 7577    if (n > 0) {
 7578        n -= 1;
 7579        ftypefile_qFind(u64(n)).~FFtypefile();
 7580        _db.ftypefile_n = i32(n);
 7581    }
 7582}
 7583
 7584// --- wcli.FDb.ftypefile.XrefMaybe
 7585// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 7586// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 7587bool wcli::ftypefile_XrefMaybe(wcli::FFtypefile &row) {
 7588    bool retval = true;
 7589    (void)row;
 7590    wcli::FFtype* p_ftype = wcli::ind_ftype_Find(ftype_Get(row));
 7591    if (UNLIKELY(!p_ftype)) {
 7592        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "wcli.bad_xref  index:wcli.FDb.ind_ftype" << Keyval("key", ftype_Get(row));
 7593        return false;
 7594    }
 7595    // ftypefile: save pointer to ftype
 7596    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 7597        row.p_ftype = p_ftype;
 7598    }
 7599    // insert ftypefile into index ind_ftypefile
 7600    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 7601        bool success = ind_ftypefile_InsertMaybe(row);
 7602        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 7603            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 7604            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_ftypefile"; // check for duplicate key
 7605            return false;
 7606        }
 7607    }
 7608    // insert ftypefile into index c_ftypefile
 7609    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 7610        c_ftypefile_Insert(*p_ftype, row);
 7611    }
 7612    return retval;
 7613}
 7614
 7615// --- wcli.FDb.ind_ftypefile.Find
 7616// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 7617wcli::FFtypefile* wcli::ind_ftypefile_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 7618    u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_ftypefile_buckets_n - 1);
 7619    wcli::FFtypefile* *e = &_db.ind_ftypefile_buckets_elems[index];
 7620    wcli::FFtypefile* ret=NULL;
 7621    do {
 7622        ret       = *e;
 7623        bool done = !ret || (*ret).ftypefile == key;
 7624        if (done) break;
 7625        e         = &ret->ind_ftypefile_next;
 7626    } while (true);
 7627    return ret;
 7628}
 7629
 7630// --- wcli.FDb.ind_ftypefile.FindX
 7631// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
 7632wcli::FFtypefile& wcli::ind_ftypefile_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
 7633    wcli::FFtypefile* ret = ind_ftypefile_Find(key);
 7634    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_ftypefile  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
 7635    return *ret;
 7636}
 7637
 7638// --- wcli.FDb.ind_ftypefile.InsertMaybe
 7639// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 7640bool wcli::ind_ftypefile_InsertMaybe(wcli::FFtypefile& row) {
 7641    ind_ftypefile_Reserve(1);
 7642    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 7643    if (LIKELY(row.ind_ftypefile_next == (wcli::FFtypefile*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 7644        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.ftypefile) & (_db.ind_ftypefile_buckets_n - 1);
 7645        wcli::FFtypefile* *prev = &_db.ind_ftypefile_buckets_elems[index];
 7646        do {
 7647            wcli::FFtypefile* ret = *prev;
 7648            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 7649                break;
 7650            }
 7651            if ((*ret).ftypefile == row.ftypefile) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 7652                retval = false;
 7653                break;
 7654            }
 7655            prev = &ret->ind_ftypefile_next;
 7656        } while (true);
 7657        if (retval) {
 7658            row.ind_ftypefile_next = *prev;
 7659            _db.ind_ftypefile_n++;
 7660            *prev = &row;
 7661        }
 7662    }
 7663    return retval;
 7664}
 7665
 7666// --- wcli.FDb.ind_ftypefile.Remove
 7667// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 7668void wcli::ind_ftypefile_Remove(wcli::FFtypefile& row) {
 7669    if (LIKELY(row.ind_ftypefile_next != (wcli::FFtypefile*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 7670        u32 index = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.ftypefile) & (_db.ind_ftypefile_buckets_n - 1);
 7671        wcli::FFtypefile* *prev = &_db.ind_ftypefile_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 7672        while (wcli::FFtypefile *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 7673            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 7674                *prev = next->ind_ftypefile_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 7675                _db.ind_ftypefile_n--;
 7676                row.ind_ftypefile_next = (wcli::FFtypefile*)-1;// not-in-hash
 7677                break;
 7678            }
 7679            prev = &next->ind_ftypefile_next;
 7680        }
 7681    }
 7682}
 7683
 7684// --- wcli.FDb.ind_ftypefile.Reserve
 7685// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 7686void wcli::ind_ftypefile_Reserve(int n) {
 7687    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_ftypefile_buckets_n;
 7688    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_ftypefile_n + n;
 7689    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 7690    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 7691        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 7692        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FFtypefile*);
 7693        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FFtypefile*);
 7694        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 7695        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 7696        wcli::FFtypefile* *new_buckets = (wcli::FFtypefile**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 7697        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 7698            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_ftypefile");
 7699        }
 7700        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 7701        // rehash all entries
 7702        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_ftypefile_buckets_n; i++) {
 7703            wcli::FFtypefile* elem = _db.ind_ftypefile_buckets_elems[i];
 7704            while (elem) {
 7705                wcli::FFtypefile &row        = *elem;
 7706                wcli::FFtypefile* next       = row.ind_ftypefile_next;
 7707                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr250_Hash(0, row.ftypefile) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 7708                row.ind_ftypefile_next     = new_buckets[index];
 7709                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 7710                elem               = next;
 7711            }
 7712        }
 7713        // free old array
 7714        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_ftypefile_buckets_elems, old_size);
 7715        _db.ind_ftypefile_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 7716        _db.ind_ftypefile_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 7717    }
 7718}
 7719
 7720// --- wcli.FDb.ftype.Alloc
 7721// Allocate memory for new default row.
 7722// If out of memory, process is killed.
 7723wcli::FFtype& wcli::ftype_Alloc() {
 7724    wcli::FFtype* row = ftype_AllocMaybe();
 7725    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 7726        FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_mem  field:wcli.FDb.ftype  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 7727    }
 7728    return *row;
 7729}
 7730
 7731// --- wcli.FDb.ftype.AllocMaybe
 7732// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 7733wcli::FFtype* wcli::ftype_AllocMaybe() {
 7734    wcli::FFtype *row = (wcli::FFtype*)ftype_AllocMem();
 7735    if (row) {
 7736        new (row) wcli::FFtype; // call constructor
 7737    }
 7738    return row;
 7739}
 7740
 7741// --- wcli.FDb.ftype.InsertMaybe
 7742// Create new row from struct.
 7743// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 7744wcli::FFtype* wcli::ftype_InsertMaybe(const wclidb::Ftype &value) {
 7745    wcli::FFtype *row = &ftype_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 7746    ftype_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<wclidb::Ftype&>(value));
 7747    bool ok = ftype_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 7748    if (!ok) {
 7749        ftype_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 7750        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 7751    }
 7752    return row;
 7753}
 7754
 7755// --- wcli.FDb.ftype.AllocMem
 7756// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 7757void* wcli::ftype_AllocMem() {
 7758    u64 new_nelems     = _db.ftype_n+1;
 7759    // compute level and index on level
 7760    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 7761    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 7762    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 7763    void *ret = NULL;
 7764    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 7765    wcli::FFtype*  lev   = NULL;
 7766    if (bsr < 32) {
 7767        lev = _db.ftype_lary[bsr];
 7768        if (!lev) {
 7769            lev=(wcli::FFtype*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FFtype) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 7770            _db.ftype_lary[bsr] = lev;
 7771        }
 7772    }
 7773    // allocate element from this level
 7774    if (lev) {
 7775        _db.ftype_n = i32(new_nelems);
 7776        ret = lev + index;
 7777    }
 7778    return ret;
 7779}
 7780
 7781// --- wcli.FDb.ftype.RemoveAll
 7782// Remove all elements from Lary
 7783void wcli::ftype_RemoveAll() {
 7784    for (u64 n = _db.ftype_n; n>0; ) {
 7785        n--;
 7786        ftype_qFind(u64(n)).~FFtype(); // destroy last element
 7787        _db.ftype_n = i32(n);
 7788    }
 7789}
 7790
 7791// --- wcli.FDb.ftype.RemoveLast
 7792// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 7793void wcli::ftype_RemoveLast() {
 7794    u64 n = _db.ftype_n;
 7795    if (n > 0) {
 7796        n -= 1;
 7797        ftype_qFind(u64(n)).~FFtype();
 7798        _db.ftype_n = i32(n);
 7799    }
 7800}
 7801
 7802// --- wcli.FDb.ftype.LoadStatic
 7803static void wcli::ftype_LoadStatic() {
 7804    static struct _t {
 7805        const char *s;
 7806        void (*step)(wcli::FFtypefile&);
 7807    } data[] = {
 7808        { "wclidb.ftype  ftype:directory  comment:\"directory, ignore\"", wcli::ftype_directory }
 7809        ,{ "wclidb.ftype  ftype:empty  comment:\"empty file, ignore\"", wcli::ftype_empty }
 7810        ,{ "wclidb.ftype  ftype:html  comment:\"xml special:import pages\"", wcli::ftype_html }
 7811        ,{ "wclidb.ftype  ftype:image  comment:\"image ftype\"", wcli::ftype_image }
 7812        ,{ "wclidb.ftype  ftype:page  comment:\"page ftype\"", wcli::ftype_page }
 7813        ,{NULL, NULL}
 7814    };
 7815    (void)data;
 7816    wclidb::Ftype ftype;
 7817    for (int i=0; data[i].s; i++) {
 7818        (void)wclidb::Ftype_ReadStrptrMaybe(ftype, algo::strptr(data[i].s));
 7819        wcli::FFtype *elem = ftype_InsertMaybe(ftype);
 7820        vrfy(elem, tempstr("wcli.static_insert_fatal_error")
 7821        << Keyval("tuple",algo::strptr(data[i].s))
 7822        << Keyval("comment",algo_lib::DetachBadTags()));
 7823        elem->step = data[i].step;
 7824    }
 7825}
 7826
 7827// --- wcli.FDb.ftype.XrefMaybe
 7828// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 7829// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 7830bool wcli::ftype_XrefMaybe(wcli::FFtype &row) {
 7831    bool retval = true;
 7832    (void)row;
 7833    // insert ftype into index ind_ftype
 7834    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 7835        bool success = ind_ftype_InsertMaybe(row);
 7836        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 7837            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 7838            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "wcli.duplicate_key  xref:wcli.FDb.ind_ftype"; // check for duplicate key
 7839            return false;
 7840        }
 7841    }
 7842    return retval;
 7843}
 7844
 7845// --- wcli.FDb.ind_ftype.Find
 7846// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 7847wcli::FFtype* wcli::ind_ftype_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 7848    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_ftype_buckets_n - 1);
 7849    wcli::FFtype* *e = &_db.ind_ftype_buckets_elems[index];
 7850    wcli::FFtype* ret=NULL;
 7851    do {
 7852        ret       = *e;
 7853        bool done = !ret || (*ret).ftype == key;
 7854        if (done) break;
 7855        e         = &ret->ind_ftype_next;
 7856    } while (true);
 7857    return ret;
 7858}
 7859
 7860// --- wcli.FDb.ind_ftype.FindX
 7861// Look up row by key and return reference. Throw exception if not found
 7862wcli::FFtype& wcli::ind_ftype_FindX(const algo::strptr& key) {
 7863    wcli::FFtype* ret = ind_ftype_Find(key);
 7864    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.key_error  table:ind_ftype  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'key not found'");
 7865    return *ret;
 7866}
 7867
 7868// --- wcli.FDb.ind_ftype.GetOrCreate
 7869// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 7870wcli::FFtype& wcli::ind_ftype_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 7871    wcli::FFtype* ret = ind_ftype_Find(key);
 7872    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 7873        ret         = &ftype_Alloc();
 7874        (*ret).ftype = key;
 7875        bool good = ftype_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 7876        if (!good) {
 7877            ftype_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 7878            ret = NULL;
 7879        }
 7880    }
 7881    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "wcli.create_error  table:ind_ftype  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 7882    return *ret;
 7883}
 7884
 7885// --- wcli.FDb.ind_ftype.InsertMaybe
 7886// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 7887bool wcli::ind_ftype_InsertMaybe(wcli::FFtype& row) {
 7888    ind_ftype_Reserve(1);
 7889    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 7890    if (LIKELY(row.ind_ftype_next == (wcli::FFtype*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 7891        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.ftype) & (_db.ind_ftype_buckets_n - 1);
 7892        wcli::FFtype* *prev = &_db.ind_ftype_buckets_elems[index];
 7893        do {
 7894            wcli::FFtype* ret = *prev;
 7895            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 7896                break;
 7897            }
 7898            if ((*ret).ftype == row.ftype) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 7899                retval = false;
 7900                break;
 7901            }
 7902            prev = &ret->ind_ftype_next;
 7903        } while (true);
 7904        if (retval) {
 7905            row.ind_ftype_next = *prev;
 7906            _db.ind_ftype_n++;
 7907            *prev = &row;
 7908        }
 7909    }
 7910    return retval;
 7911}

 7913// --- wcli.FDb.ind_ftype.Remove
 7914// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 7915void wcli::ind_ftype_Remove(wcli::FFtype& row) {
 7916    if (LIKELY(row.ind_ftype_next != (wcli::FFtype*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 7917        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.ftype) & (_db.ind_ftype_buckets_n - 1);
 7918        wcli::FFtype* *prev = &_db.ind_ftype_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 7919        while (wcli::FFtype *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 7920            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 7921                *prev = next->ind_ftype_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 7922                _db.ind_ftype_n--;
 7923                row.ind_ftype_next = (wcli::FFtype*)-1;// not-in-hash
 7924                break;
 7925            }
 7926            prev = &next->ind_ftype_next;
 7927        }
 7928    }
 7929}

 7931// --- wcli.FDb.ind_ftype.Reserve
 7932// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 7933void wcli::ind_ftype_Reserve(int n) {
 7934    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_ftype_buckets_n;
 7935    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_ftype_n + n;
 7936    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 7937    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 7938        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 7939        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FFtype*);
 7940        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(wcli::FFtype*);
 7941        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 7942        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 7943        wcli::FFtype* *new_buckets = (wcli::FFtype**)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(new_size);
 7944        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 7945            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FDb.ind_ftype");
 7946        }
 7947        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 7948        // rehash all entries
 7949        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_ftype_buckets_n; i++) {
 7950            wcli::FFtype* elem = _db.ind_ftype_buckets_elems[i];
 7951            while (elem) {
 7952                wcli::FFtype &row        = *elem;
 7953                wcli::FFtype* next       = row.ind_ftype_next;
 7954                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.ftype) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 7955                row.ind_ftype_next     = new_buckets[index];
 7956                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 7957                elem               = next;
 7958            }
 7959        }
 7960        // free old array
 7961        algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(_db.ind_ftype_buckets_elems, old_size);
 7962        _db.ind_ftype_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 7963        _db.ind_ftype_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 7964    }
 7965}

 7968// find trace by row id (used to implement reflection)
 7969static algo::ImrowPtr wcli::trace_RowidFind(int t) {
 7970    return algo::ImrowPtr(t==0 ? u64(&_db.trace) : u64(0));
 7971}

 7976    return 1;

 7978
 7979// --- wcli.FDb..Init
 7980// Set all fields to initial values.
 7981void wcli::FDb_Init() {
 7982    // initialize LAry tuples (wcli.FDb.tuples)
 7983    _db.tuples_n = 0;
 7984    memset(_db.tuples_lary, 0, sizeof(_db.tuples_lary)); // zero out all level pointers
 7985    wcli::FTuples* tuples_first = (wcli::FTuples*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FTuples) * (u64(1)<<4));
 7986    if (!tuples_first) {
 7987        FatalErrorExit("out of memory");
 7988    }
 7989    for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
 7990        _db.tuples_lary[i]  = tuples_first;
 7991        tuples_first    += 1ULL<<i;
 7992    }
 7993    // initialize LAry wclicmdc (wcli.FDb.wclicmdc)
 7994    _db.wclicmdc_n = 0;
 7995    memset(_db.wclicmdc_lary, 0, sizeof(_db.wclicmdc_lary)); // zero out all level pointers
 7996    wcli::FWclicmdc* wclicmdc_first = (wcli::FWclicmdc*)algo_lib::malloc_AllocMem(sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdc) * (u64(1)<<4));
 7997    if (!wclicmdc_first) {
 7998        FatalErrorExit("out of memory");
 7999    }
 8000    for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
 8001        _db.wclicmdc_lary[i]  = wclicmdc_first;
 8002        wclicmdc_first    += 1ULL<<i;

 8787// --- wcli.FFtype.c_ftypefile.Insert
 8788// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
 8789// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
 8790void wcli::c_ftypefile_Insert(wcli::FFtype& ftype, wcli::FFtypefile& row) {
 8791    if (bool_Update(row.ftype_c_ftypefile_in_ary,true)) {
 8792        // reserve space
 8793        c_ftypefile_Reserve(ftype, 1);
 8794        u32 n  = ftype.c_ftypefile_n;
 8795        u32 at = n;
 8796        wcli::FFtypefile* *elems = ftype.c_ftypefile_elems;
 8797        elems[at] = &row;
 8798        ftype.c_ftypefile_n = n+1;
 8799
 8800    }
 8801}
 8802
 8803// --- wcli.FFtype.c_ftypefile.InsertMaybe
 8804// Insert pointer to row in array.
 8805// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
 8806// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
 8807bool wcli::c_ftypefile_InsertMaybe(wcli::FFtype& ftype, wcli::FFtypefile& row) {
 8808    bool retval = !row.ftype_c_ftypefile_in_ary;
 8809    c_ftypefile_Insert(ftype,row); // check is performed in _Insert again
 8810    return retval;
 8811}
 8812
 8813// --- wcli.FFtype.c_ftypefile.Remove
 8814// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
 8815void wcli::c_ftypefile_Remove(wcli::FFtype& ftype, wcli::FFtypefile& row) {
 8816    if (bool_Update(row.ftype_c_ftypefile_in_ary,false)) {
 8817        int lim = ftype.c_ftypefile_n;
 8818        wcli::FFtypefile* *elems = ftype.c_ftypefile_elems;
 8819        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
 8820        // if found, shift array.
 8821        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
 8822            wcli::FFtypefile* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
 8823            if (elem == &row) {
 8824                int j = i + 1;
 8825                size_t nbytes = sizeof(wcli::FFtypefile*) * (lim - j);
 8826                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
 8827                ftype.c_ftypefile_n = lim - 1;
 8828                break;
 8829            }
 8830        }
 8831    }
 8832}
 8833
 8834// --- wcli.FFtype.c_ftypefile.Reserve
 8835// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
 8836void wcli::c_ftypefile_Reserve(wcli::FFtype& ftype, u32 n) {
 8837    u32 old_max = ftype.c_ftypefile_max;
 8838    if (UNLIKELY(ftype.c_ftypefile_n + n > old_max)) {
 8839        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
 8840        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(wcli::FFtypefile*);
 8841        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(wcli::FFtypefile*);
 8842        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(ftype.c_ftypefile_elems, old_size, new_size);
 8843        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 8844            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FFtype.c_ftypefile");
 8845        }
 8846        ftype.c_ftypefile_elems = (wcli::FFtypefile**)new_mem;
 8847        ftype.c_ftypefile_max = new_max;
 8848    }
 8849}
 8850
 8851// --- wcli.FFtype..Uninit
 8852void wcli::FFtype_Uninit(wcli::FFtype& ftype) {
 8853    wcli::FFtype &row = ftype; (void)row;
 8854    ind_ftype_Remove(row); // remove ftype from index ind_ftype
 8855
 8856    // wcli.FFtype.c_ftypefile.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
 8857    algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(ftype.c_ftypefile_elems, sizeof(wcli::FFtypefile*)*ftype.c_ftypefile_max); // (wcli.FFtype.c_ftypefile)
 8858}

 8861algo::Smallstr50 wcli::ftype_Get(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile) {
 8862    algo::Smallstr50 ret(algo::Pathcomp(ftypefile.ftypefile, "@RL"));
 8863    return ret;
 8864}

 8866// --- wcli.FFtypefile.name.Get
 8867algo::cstring wcli::name_Get(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile) {
 8868    algo::cstring ret(algo::Pathcomp(ftypefile.ftypefile, "@RR"));
 8869    return ret;
 8870}
 8871
 8872// --- wcli.FFtypefile.title.Addary
 8873// Reserve space (this may move memory). Insert N element at the end.
 8874// Return aryptr to newly inserted block.
 8875// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), exit program with fatal error.
 8876algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> wcli::title_Addary(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile, algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> rhs) {
 8877    bool overlaps = rhs.n_elems>0 && rhs.elems >= ftypefile.title_elems && rhs.elems < ftypefile.title_elems + ftypefile.title_max;
 8878    if (UNLIKELY(overlaps)) {
 8879        FatalErrorExit("wcli.tary_alias  field:wcli.FFtypefile.title  comment:'alias error: sub-array is being appended to the whole'");
 8880    }
 8881    int nnew = rhs.n_elems;
 8882    title_Reserve(ftypefile, nnew); // reserve space
 8883    int at = ftypefile.title_n;
 8884    for (int i = 0; i < nnew; i++) {
 8885        new (ftypefile.title_elems + at + i) algo::cstring(rhs[i]);
 8886        ftypefile.title_n++;
 8887    }
 8888    return algo::aryptr<algo::cstring>(ftypefile.title_elems + at, nnew);
 8889}
 8890
 8891// --- wcli.FFtypefile.title.Alloc
 8892// Reserve space. Insert element at the end
 8893// The new element is initialized to a default value
 8894algo::cstring& wcli::title_Alloc(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile) {
 8895    title_Reserve(ftypefile, 1);
 8896    int n  = ftypefile.title_n;
 8897    int at = n;
 8898    algo::cstring *elems = ftypefile.title_elems;
 8899    new (elems + at) algo::cstring(); // construct new element, default initializer
 8900    ftypefile.title_n = n+1;
 8901    return elems[at];
 8902}
 8903
 8904// --- wcli.FFtypefile.title.AllocAt
 8905// Reserve space for new element, reallocating the array if necessary
 8906// Insert new element at specified index. Index must be in range or a fatal error occurs.
 8907algo::cstring& wcli::title_AllocAt(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile, int at) {
 8908    title_Reserve(ftypefile, 1);
 8909    int n  = ftypefile.title_n;
 8910    if (UNLIKELY(u64(at) >= u64(n+1))) {
 8911        FatalErrorExit("wcli.bad_alloc_at  field:wcli.FFtypefile.title  comment:'index out of range'");
 8912    }
 8913    algo::cstring *elems = ftypefile.title_elems;
 8914    memmove(elems + at + 1, elems + at, (n - at) * sizeof(algo::cstring));
 8915    new (elems + at) algo::cstring(); // construct element, default initializer
 8916    ftypefile.title_n = n+1;
 8917    return elems[at];
 8918}
 8919
 8920// --- wcli.FFtypefile.title.AllocN
 8921// Reserve space. Insert N elements at the end of the array, return pointer to array
 8922algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> wcli::title_AllocN(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile, int n_elems) {
 8923    title_Reserve(ftypefile, n_elems);
 8924    int old_n  = ftypefile.title_n;
 8925    int new_n = old_n + n_elems;
 8926    algo::cstring *elems = ftypefile.title_elems;
 8927    for (int i = old_n; i < new_n; i++) {
 8928        new (elems + i) algo::cstring(); // construct new element, default initialize
 8929    }
 8930    ftypefile.title_n = new_n;
 8931    return algo::aryptr<algo::cstring>(elems + old_n, n_elems);
 8932}
 8933
 8934// --- wcli.FFtypefile.title.Remove
 8935// Remove item by index. If index outside of range, do nothing.
 8936void wcli::title_Remove(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile, u32 i) {
 8937    u32 lim = ftypefile.title_n;
 8938    algo::cstring *elems = ftypefile.title_elems;
 8939    if (i < lim) {
 8940        elems[i].~cstring(); // destroy element
 8941        memmove(elems + i, elems + (i + 1), sizeof(algo::cstring) * (lim - (i + 1)));
 8942        ftypefile.title_n = lim - 1;
 8943    }
 8944}
 8945
 8946// --- wcli.FFtypefile.title.RemoveAll
 8947void wcli::title_RemoveAll(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile) {
 8948    u32 n = ftypefile.title_n;
 8949    while (n > 0) {
 8950        n -= 1;
 8951        ftypefile.title_elems[n].~cstring();
 8952        ftypefile.title_n = n;
 8953    }
 8954}
 8955
 8956// --- wcli.FFtypefile.title.RemoveLast
 8957// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 8958void wcli::title_RemoveLast(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile) {
 8959    u64 n = ftypefile.title_n;
 8960    if (n > 0) {
 8961        n -= 1;
 8962        title_qFind(ftypefile, u64(n)).~cstring();
 8963        ftypefile.title_n = n;
 8964    }
 8965}
 8966
 8967// --- wcli.FFtypefile.title.AbsReserve
 8968// Make sure N elements fit in array. Process dies if out of memory
 8969void wcli::title_AbsReserve(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile, int n) {
 8970    u32 old_max  = ftypefile.title_max;
 8971    if (n > i32(old_max)) {
 8972        u32 new_max  = i32_Max(i32_Max(old_max * 2, n), 4);
 8973        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(ftypefile.title_elems, old_max * sizeof(algo::cstring), new_max * sizeof(algo::cstring));
 8974        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 8975            FatalErrorExit("wcli.tary_nomem  field:wcli.FFtypefile.title  comment:'out of memory'");
 8976        }
 8977        ftypefile.title_elems = (algo::cstring*)new_mem;
 8978        ftypefile.title_max = new_max;
 8979    }
 8980}
 8981
 8982// --- wcli.FFtypefile.title.Setary
 8983// Copy contents of RHS to PARENT.
 8984void wcli::title_Setary(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile, wcli::FFtypefile &rhs) {
 8985    title_RemoveAll(ftypefile);
 8986    int nnew = rhs.title_n;
 8987    title_Reserve(ftypefile, nnew); // reserve space
 8988    for (int i = 0; i < nnew; i++) { // copy elements over
 8989        new (ftypefile.title_elems + i) algo::cstring(title_qFind(rhs, i));
 8990        ftypefile.title_n = i + 1;
 8991    }
 8992}
 8993
 8994// --- wcli.FFtypefile.title.Setary2
 8995// Copy specified array into title, discarding previous contents.
 8996// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), throw exception.
 8997void wcli::title_Setary(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile, const algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> &rhs) {
 8998    title_RemoveAll(ftypefile);
 8999    title_Addary(ftypefile, rhs);
 9000}
 9001
 9002// --- wcli.FFtypefile.title.AllocNVal
 9003// Reserve space. Insert N elements at the end of the array, return pointer to array
 9004algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> wcli::title_AllocNVal(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile, int n_elems, const algo::cstring& val) {
 9005    title_Reserve(ftypefile, n_elems);
 9006    int old_n  = ftypefile.title_n;
 9007    int new_n = old_n + n_elems;
 9008    algo::cstring *elems = ftypefile.title_elems;
 9009    for (int i = old_n; i < new_n; i++) {
 9010        new (elems + i) algo::cstring(val);
 9011    }
 9012    ftypefile.title_n = new_n;
 9013    return algo::aryptr<algo::cstring>(elems + old_n, n_elems);
 9014}
 9015
 9016// --- wcli.FFtypefile.title.ReadStrptrMaybe
 9017// A single element is read from input string and appended to the array.
 9018// If the string contains an error, the array is untouched.
 9019// Function returns success value.
 9020bool wcli::title_ReadStrptrMaybe(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile, algo::strptr in_str) {
 9021    bool retval = true;
 9022    algo::cstring &elem = title_Alloc(ftypefile);
 9023    retval = algo::cstring_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, in_str);
 9024    if (!retval) {
 9025        title_RemoveLast(ftypefile);
 9026    }
 9027    return retval;
 9028}

 9030// --- wcli.FFtypefile..Concat_ftype_name
 9031tempstr wcli::FFtypefile_Concat_ftype_name( const algo::strptr& ftype ,const algo::strptr& name ) {
 9032    return tempstr() << ftype <<'@'<< name ;
 9033}
 9034
 9035// --- wcli.FFtypefile..Uninit
 9036void wcli::FFtypefile_Uninit(wcli::FFtypefile& ftypefile) {
 9037    wcli::FFtypefile &row = ftypefile; (void)row;
 9038    ind_ftypefile_Remove(row); // remove ftypefile from index ind_ftypefile
 9039    wcli::FFtype* p_ftype = wcli::ind_ftype_Find(ftype_Get(row));
 9040    if (p_ftype)  {
 9041        c_ftypefile_Remove(*p_ftype, row);// remove ftypefile from index c_ftypefile
 9042    }
 9043
 9044    // wcli.FFtypefile.title.Uninit (Tary)  //
 9045    // remove all elements from wcli.FFtypefile.title
 9046    title_RemoveAll(ftypefile);
 9047    // free memory for Tary wcli.FFtypefile.title
 9048    algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(ftypefile.title_elems, sizeof(algo::cstring)*ftypefile.title_max); // (wcli.FFtypefile.title)
 9049}

 9089// --- wcli.FPage.c_pagesec.Insert
 9090// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
 9091// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
 9092void wcli::c_pagesec_Insert(wcli::FPage& page, wcli::FPagesec& row) {
 9093    if (bool_Update(row.page_c_pagesec_in_ary,true)) {
 9094        // reserve space
 9095        c_pagesec_Reserve(page, 1);
 9096        u32 n  = page.c_pagesec_n;
 9097        u32 at = n;
 9098        wcli::FPagesec* *elems = page.c_pagesec_elems;
 9099        elems[at] = &row;
 9100        page.c_pagesec_n = n+1;
 9101
 9102    }
 9103}
 9104
 9105// --- wcli.FPage.c_pagesec.InsertMaybe
 9106// Insert pointer to row in array.
 9107// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
 9108// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
 9109bool wcli::c_pagesec_InsertMaybe(wcli::FPage& page, wcli::FPagesec& row) {
 9110    bool retval = !row.page_c_pagesec_in_ary;
 9111    c_pagesec_Insert(page,row); // check is performed in _Insert again
 9112    return retval;
 9113}
 9114
 9115// --- wcli.FPage.c_pagesec.Remove
 9116// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
 9117void wcli::c_pagesec_Remove(wcli::FPage& page, wcli::FPagesec& row) {
 9118    if (bool_Update(row.page_c_pagesec_in_ary,false)) {
 9119        int lim = page.c_pagesec_n;
 9120        wcli::FPagesec* *elems = page.c_pagesec_elems;
 9121        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
 9122        // if found, shift array.
 9123        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
 9124            wcli::FPagesec* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
 9125            if (elem == &row) {
 9126                int j = i + 1;
 9127                size_t nbytes = sizeof(wcli::FPagesec*) * (lim - j);
 9128                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
 9129                page.c_pagesec_n = lim - 1;
 9130                break;
 9131            }
 9132        }
 9133    }
 9134}
 9135
 9136// --- wcli.FPage.c_pagesec.Reserve
 9137// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
 9138void wcli::c_pagesec_Reserve(wcli::FPage& page, u32 n) {
 9139    u32 old_max = page.c_pagesec_max;
 9140    if (UNLIKELY(page.c_pagesec_n + n > old_max)) {
 9141        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
 9142        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(wcli::FPagesec*);
 9143        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(wcli::FPagesec*);
 9144        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(page.c_pagesec_elems, old_size, new_size);
 9145        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 9146            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FPage.c_pagesec");
 9147        }
 9148        page.c_pagesec_elems = (wcli::FPagesec**)new_mem;
 9149        page.c_pagesec_max = new_max;
 9150    }
 9151}
 9152
 9153// --- wcli.FPage..Init
 9154// Set all fields to initial values.
 9155void wcli::FPage_Init(wcli::FPage& page) {
 9156    page.select = bool(false);
 9157    page.c_pagesec_elems = NULL; // (wcli.FPage.c_pagesec)
 9158    page.c_pagesec_n = 0; // (wcli.FPage.c_pagesec)
 9159    page.c_pagesec_max = 0; // (wcli.FPage.c_pagesec)
 9160    page.sec_offset = u32(0);
 9161    page._db_c_page_foutput_in_ary = bool(false);
 9162    page.ind_page_next = (wcli::FPage*)-1; // (wcli.FDb.ind_page) not-in-hash
 9163    page.ind_page_id_next = (wcli::FPage*)-1; // (wcli.FDb.ind_page_id) not-in-hash
 9164}
 9165
 9166// --- wcli.FPage..Uninit
 9167void wcli::FPage_Uninit(wcli::FPage& page) {
 9168    wcli::FPage &row = page; (void)row;
 9169    ind_page_Remove(row); // remove page from index ind_page
 9170    ind_page_id_Remove(row); // remove page from index ind_page_id
 9171    c_page_foutput_Remove(row); // remove page from index c_page_foutput
 9172
 9173    // wcli.FPage.c_pagesec.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
 9174    algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(page.c_pagesec_elems, sizeof(wcli::FPagesec*)*page.c_pagesec_max); // (wcli.FPage.c_pagesec)
 9175}

 9216// Set all fields to initial values.
 9217void wcli::FPagesec_Init(wcli::FPagesec& pagesec) {
 9218    pagesec.number = algo::strptr("0");
 9219    pagesec.toclevel = u32(0);
 9220    pagesec.page_c_pagesec_in_ary = bool(false);
 9221    pagesec.ind_pagesec_next = (wcli::FPagesec*)-1; // (wcli.FDb.ind_pagesec) not-in-hash
 9222}

 9224// --- wcli.FPagesec..Uninit
 9225void wcli::FPagesec_Uninit(wcli::FPagesec& pagesec) {
 9226    wcli::FPagesec &row = pagesec; (void)row;
 9227    ind_pagesec_Remove(row); // remove pagesec from index ind_pagesec
 9228    wcli::FPage* p_page = wcli::ind_page_Find(page_Get(row));
 9229    if (p_page)  {
 9230        c_pagesec_Remove(*p_page, row);// remove pagesec from index c_pagesec
 9231    }
 9232}

 9326// --- wcli.FWclicmd.c_tuples.Insert
 9327// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
 9328// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
 9329void wcli::c_tuples_Insert(wcli::FWclicmd& wclicmd, wcli::FTuples& row) {
 9330    // reserve space
 9331    c_tuples_Reserve(wclicmd, 1);
 9332    u32 n  = wclicmd.c_tuples_n;
 9333    u32 at = n;
 9334    wcli::FTuples* *elems = wclicmd.c_tuples_elems;
 9335    elems[at] = &row;
 9336    wclicmd.c_tuples_n = n+1;
 9337
 9338}
 9339
 9340// --- wcli.FWclicmd.c_tuples.ScanInsertMaybe
 9341// Insert pointer to row in array.
 9342// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
 9343// Linear search is used to locate the element.
 9344// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
 9345bool wcli::c_tuples_ScanInsertMaybe(wcli::FWclicmd& wclicmd, wcli::FTuples& row) {
 9346    bool retval = true;
 9347    u32 n  = wclicmd.c_tuples_n;
 9348    for (u32 i = 0; i < n; i++) {
 9349        if (wclicmd.c_tuples_elems[i] == &row) {
 9350            retval = false;
 9351            break;
 9352        }
 9353    }
 9354    if (retval) {
 9355        // reserve space
 9356        c_tuples_Reserve(wclicmd, 1);
 9357        wclicmd.c_tuples_elems[n] = &row;
 9358        wclicmd.c_tuples_n = n+1;
 9359    }
 9360    return retval;
 9361}
 9362
 9363// --- wcli.FWclicmd.c_tuples.Remove
 9364// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
 9365void wcli::c_tuples_Remove(wcli::FWclicmd& wclicmd, wcli::FTuples& row) {
 9366    int lim = wclicmd.c_tuples_n;
 9367    wcli::FTuples* *elems = wclicmd.c_tuples_elems;
 9368    // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
 9369    // if found, shift array.
 9370    for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
 9371        wcli::FTuples* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
 9372        if (elem == &row) {
 9373            int j = i + 1;
 9374            size_t nbytes = sizeof(wcli::FTuples*) * (lim - j);
 9375            memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
 9376            wclicmd.c_tuples_n = lim - 1;
 9377            break;
 9378        }
 9379    }
 9380}
 9381
 9382// --- wcli.FWclicmd.c_tuples.Reserve
 9383// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
 9384void wcli::c_tuples_Reserve(wcli::FWclicmd& wclicmd, u32 n) {
 9385    u32 old_max = wclicmd.c_tuples_max;
 9386    if (UNLIKELY(wclicmd.c_tuples_n + n > old_max)) {
 9387        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
 9388        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(wcli::FTuples*);
 9389        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(wcli::FTuples*);
 9390        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(wclicmd.c_tuples_elems, old_size, new_size);
 9391        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 9392            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FWclicmd.c_tuples");
 9393        }
 9394        wclicmd.c_tuples_elems = (wcli::FTuples**)new_mem;
 9395        wclicmd.c_tuples_max = new_max;
 9396    }
 9397}

 9574// --- wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdapi.Reserve
 9575// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
 9576void wcli::c_wclicmdapi_Reserve(wcli::FWclicmd& wclicmd, u32 n) {
 9577    u32 old_max = wclicmd.c_wclicmdapi_max;
 9578    if (UNLIKELY(wclicmd.c_wclicmdapi_n + n > old_max)) {
 9579        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
 9580        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdapi*);
 9581        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdapi*);
 9582        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(wclicmd.c_wclicmdapi_elems, old_size, new_size);
 9583        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 9584            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdapi");
 9585        }
 9586        wclicmd.c_wclicmdapi_elems = (wcli::FWclicmdapi**)new_mem;
 9587        wclicmd.c_wclicmdapi_max = new_max;
 9588    }
 9589}
 9590
 9591// --- wcli.FWclicmd..Init
 9592// Set all fields to initial values.
 9593void wcli::FWclicmd_Init(wcli::FWclicmd& wclicmd) {
 9594    wclicmd.select = bool(false);
 9595    wclicmd.c_tuples_elems = NULL; // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_tuples)
 9596    wclicmd.c_tuples_n = 0; // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_tuples)
 9597    wclicmd.c_tuples_max = 0; // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_tuples)
 9598    wclicmd.c_wclicmdc_elems = NULL; // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdc)
 9599    wclicmd.c_wclicmdc_n = 0; // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdc)
 9600    wclicmd.c_wclicmdc_max = 0; // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdc)
 9601    wclicmd.c_wclicmdf2j_elems = NULL; // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdf2j)
 9602    wclicmd.c_wclicmdf2j_n = 0; // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdf2j)
 9603    wclicmd.c_wclicmdf2j_max = 0; // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdf2j)
 9604    wclicmd.tot_success = u32(0);
 9605    wclicmd.tot_failure = u32(0);
 9606    wclicmd.c_wclicmdapi_elems = NULL; // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdapi)
 9607    wclicmd.c_wclicmdapi_n = 0; // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdapi)
 9608    wclicmd.c_wclicmdapi_max = 0; // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdapi)
 9609    wclicmd.ind_wclicmd_next = (wcli::FWclicmd*)-1; // (wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmd) not-in-hash
 9610    wclicmd.step = NULL;
 9611}

 9613// --- wcli.FWclicmd..Uninit
 9614void wcli::FWclicmd_Uninit(wcli::FWclicmd& wclicmd) {
 9615    wcli::FWclicmd &row = wclicmd; (void)row;
 9616    ind_wclicmd_Remove(row); // remove wclicmd from index ind_wclicmd
 9617
 9618    // wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdapi.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
 9619    algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(wclicmd.c_wclicmdapi_elems, sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdapi*)*wclicmd.c_wclicmdapi_max); // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdapi)
 9620
 9621    // wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdf2j.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
 9622    algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(wclicmd.c_wclicmdf2j_elems, sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdf2j*)*wclicmd.c_wclicmdf2j_max); // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdf2j)
 9623
 9624    // wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdc.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
 9625    algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(wclicmd.c_wclicmdc_elems, sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdc*)*wclicmd.c_wclicmdc_max); // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_wclicmdc)
 9626
 9627    // wcli.FWclicmd.c_tuples.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
 9628    algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(wclicmd.c_tuples_elems, sizeof(wcli::FTuples*)*wclicmd.c_tuples_max); // (wcli.FWclicmd.c_tuples)
 9629}

 9679// --- wcli.FWclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub.Insert
 9680// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
 9681// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
 9682void wcli::c_wclicmdargsub_Insert(wcli::FWclicmdarg& wclicmdarg, wcli::FWclicmdargsub& row) {
 9683    if (bool_Update(row.wclicmdarg_c_wclicmdargsub_in_ary,true)) {
 9684        // reserve space
 9685        c_wclicmdargsub_Reserve(wclicmdarg, 1);
 9686        u32 n  = wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_n;
 9687        u32 at = n;
 9688        wcli::FWclicmdargsub* *elems = wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_elems;
 9689        elems[at] = &row;
 9690        wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_n = n+1;
 9691
 9692    }
 9693}
 9694
 9695// --- wcli.FWclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub.InsertMaybe
 9696// Insert pointer to row in array.
 9697// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
 9698// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
 9699bool wcli::c_wclicmdargsub_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdarg& wclicmdarg, wcli::FWclicmdargsub& row) {
 9700    bool retval = !row.wclicmdarg_c_wclicmdargsub_in_ary;
 9701    c_wclicmdargsub_Insert(wclicmdarg,row); // check is performed in _Insert again
 9702    return retval;
 9703}
 9704
 9705// --- wcli.FWclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub.Remove
 9706// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
 9707void wcli::c_wclicmdargsub_Remove(wcli::FWclicmdarg& wclicmdarg, wcli::FWclicmdargsub& row) {
 9708    if (bool_Update(row.wclicmdarg_c_wclicmdargsub_in_ary,false)) {
 9709        int lim = wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_n;
 9710        wcli::FWclicmdargsub* *elems = wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_elems;
 9711        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
 9712        // if found, shift array.
 9713        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
 9714            wcli::FWclicmdargsub* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
 9715            if (elem == &row) {
 9716                int j = i + 1;
 9717                size_t nbytes = sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdargsub*) * (lim - j);
 9718                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
 9719                wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_n = lim - 1;
 9720                break;
 9721            }
 9722        }
 9723    }
 9724}
 9725
 9726// --- wcli.FWclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub.Reserve
 9727// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
 9728void wcli::c_wclicmdargsub_Reserve(wcli::FWclicmdarg& wclicmdarg, u32 n) {
 9729    u32 old_max = wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_max;
 9730    if (UNLIKELY(wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_n + n > old_max)) {
 9731        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
 9732        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdargsub*);
 9733        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdargsub*);
 9734        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_elems, old_size, new_size);
 9735        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
 9736            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FWclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub");
 9737        }
 9738        wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_elems = (wcli::FWclicmdargsub**)new_mem;
 9739        wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_max = new_max;
 9740    }
 9741}

 9743// --- wcli.FWclicmdarg..Init
 9744// Set all fields to initial values.
 9745void wcli::FWclicmdarg_Init(wcli::FWclicmdarg& wclicmdarg) {
 9746    wclicmdarg.p_wclicmd = NULL;
 9747    wclicmdarg.p_page = NULL;
 9748    wclicmdarg.p_wikins = NULL;
 9749    wclicmdarg.p_wikiuser = NULL;
 9750    wclicmdarg.subpage = bool(false);
 9751    wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_elems = NULL; // (wcli.FWclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub)
 9752    wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_n = 0; // (wcli.FWclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub)
 9753    wclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub_max = 0; // (wcli.FWclicmdarg.c_wclicmdargsub)
 9754    wclicmdarg._db_c_wclicmdarg_exec_in_ary = bool(false);
 9755    wclicmdarg.ind_wclicmdarg_next = (wcli::FWclicmdarg*)-1; // (wcli.FDb.ind_wclicmdarg) not-in-hash
 9756}

 9979// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
 9980// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
 9981void wcli::c_wclicmdf_Insert(wcli::FWclicmdj2f& wclicmdj2f, wcli::FWclicmdf& row) {
 9982    // reserve space
 9983    c_wclicmdf_Reserve(wclicmdj2f, 1);
 9984    u32 n  = wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_n;
 9985    u32 at = n;
 9986    wcli::FWclicmdf* *elems = wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_elems;
 9987    elems[at] = &row;
 9988    wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_n = n+1;
 9989
 9990}
 9991
 9992// --- wcli.FWclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf.ScanInsertMaybe
 9993// Insert pointer to row in array.
 9994// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
 9995// Linear search is used to locate the element.
 9996// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
 9997bool wcli::c_wclicmdf_ScanInsertMaybe(wcli::FWclicmdj2f& wclicmdj2f, wcli::FWclicmdf& row) {
 9998    bool retval = true;
 9999    u32 n  = wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_n;
10000    for (u32 i = 0; i < n; i++) {
10001        if (wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_elems[i] == &row) {
10002            retval = false;
10003            break;
10004        }
10005    }
10006    if (retval) {
10007        // reserve space
10008        c_wclicmdf_Reserve(wclicmdj2f, 1);
10009        wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_elems[n] = &row;
10010        wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_n = n+1;
10011    }
10012    return retval;
10013}
10014
10015// --- wcli.FWclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf.Remove
10016// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
10017void wcli::c_wclicmdf_Remove(wcli::FWclicmdj2f& wclicmdj2f, wcli::FWclicmdf& row) {
10018    int lim = wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_n;
10019    wcli::FWclicmdf* *elems = wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_elems;
10020    // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
10021    // if found, shift array.
10022    for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
10023        wcli::FWclicmdf* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
10024        if (elem == &row) {
10025            int j = i + 1;
10026            size_t nbytes = sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdf*) * (lim - j);
10027            memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
10028            wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_n = lim - 1;
10029            break;
10030        }
10031    }
10032}
10033
10034// --- wcli.FWclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf.Reserve
10035// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
10036void wcli::c_wclicmdf_Reserve(wcli::FWclicmdj2f& wclicmdj2f, u32 n) {
10037    u32 old_max = wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_max;
10038    if (UNLIKELY(wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_n + n > old_max)) {
10039        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
10040        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdf*);
10041        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(wcli::FWclicmdf*);
10042        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_elems, old_size, new_size);
10043        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
10044            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FWclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf");
10045        }
10046        wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_elems = (wcli::FWclicmdf**)new_mem;
10047        wclicmdj2f.c_wclicmdf_max = new_max;
10048    }
10049}

10053    algo::Smallstr50 ret(algo::Pathcomp(wclicmdj2f.wclicmdj2f, "/LL"));

10438// --- wcli.FWtbl.c_wtblact.InsertMaybe
10439// Insert pointer to row in array.
10440// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
10441// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
10442bool wcli::c_wtblact_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWtbl& wtbl, wcli::FWtblact& row) {
10443    bool retval = !row.wtbl_c_wtblact_in_ary;
10444    c_wtblact_Insert(wtbl,row); // check is performed in _Insert again
10445    return retval;
10446}
10447
10448// --- wcli.FWtbl.c_wtblact.Remove
10449// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
10450void wcli::c_wtblact_Remove(wcli::FWtbl& wtbl, wcli::FWtblact& row) {
10451    if (bool_Update(row.wtbl_c_wtblact_in_ary,false)) {
10452        int lim = wtbl.c_wtblact_n;
10453        wcli::FWtblact* *elems = wtbl.c_wtblact_elems;
10454        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
10455        // if found, shift array.
10456        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
10457            wcli::FWtblact* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
10458            if (elem == &row) {
10459                int j = i + 1;
10460                size_t nbytes = sizeof(wcli::FWtblact*) * (lim - j);
10461                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
10462                wtbl.c_wtblact_n = lim - 1;
10463                break;
10464            }
10465        }
10466    }
10467}
10468
10469// --- wcli.FWtbl.c_wtblact.Reserve
10470// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
10471void wcli::c_wtblact_Reserve(wcli::FWtbl& wtbl, u32 n) {
10472    u32 old_max = wtbl.c_wtblact_max;
10473    if (UNLIKELY(wtbl.c_wtblact_n + n > old_max)) {
10474        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
10475        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(wcli::FWtblact*);
10476        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(wcli::FWtblact*);
10477        void *new_mem = algo_lib::malloc_ReallocMem(wtbl.c_wtblact_elems, old_size, new_size);
10478        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
10479            FatalErrorExit("wcli.out_of_memory  field:wcli.FWtbl.c_wtblact");
10480        }
10481        wtbl.c_wtblact_elems = (wcli::FWtblact**)new_mem;
10482        wtbl.c_wtblact_max = new_max;
10483    }
10484}
10485
10486// --- wcli.FWtbl..Uninit
10487void wcli::FWtbl_Uninit(wcli::FWtbl& wtbl) {
10488    wcli::FWtbl &row = wtbl; (void)row;
10489    ind_wtbl_Remove(row); // remove wtbl from index ind_wtbl
10490
10491    // wcli.FWtbl.c_wtblact.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
10492    algo_lib::malloc_FreeMem(wtbl.c_wtblact_elems, sizeof(wcli::FWtblact*)*wtbl.c_wtblact_max); // (wcli.FWtbl.c_wtblact)
10493}

10527// --- wcli.FWtblact.c_wtblactfld.Insert
10528// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
10529// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
10530void wcli::c_wtblactfld_Insert(wcli::FWtblact& wtblact, wcli::FWtblactfld& row) {
10531    if (bool_Update(row.wtblact_c_wtblactfld_in_ary,true)) {
10532        // reserve space
10533        c_wtblactfld_Reserve(wtblact, 1);
10534        u32 n  = wtblact.c_wtblactfld_n;
10535        u32 at = n;
10536        wcli::FWtblactfld* *elems = wtblact.c_wtblactfld_elems;
10537        elems[at] = &row;
10538        wtblact.c_wtblactfld_n = n+1;
10539
10540    }
10541}
10542
10543// --- wcli.FWtblact.c_wtblactfld.InsertMaybe
10544// Insert pointer to row in array.
10545// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
10546// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
10547bool wcli::c_wtblactfld_InsertMaybe(wcli::FWtblact& wtblact, wcli::FWtblactfld& row) {
10548    bool retval = !row.wtblact_c_wtblactfld_in_ary;
10549    c_wtblactfld_Insert(wtblact,row); // check is performed in _Insert again
10550    return retval;
10551}

10558        wcli::FWtblactfld* *elems = wtblact.c_wtblactfld_elems;
10559        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
10560        // if found, shift array.
10561        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
10562            wcli::FWtblactfld* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
10563            if (elem == &row) {
10564                int j = i + 1;

10570        }
10571    }
10572}

10603    wtblact.zd_wtblact_next = (wcli::FWtblact*)-1; // (wcli.FDb.zd_wtblact) not-in-list
10604    wtblact.zd_wtblact_prev = NULL; // (wcli.FDb.zd_wtblact)
10605    wtblact.step = NULL;
10606}

10666void wcli::FWtblactfld_Uninit(wcli::FWtblactfld& wtblactfld) {
10667    wcli::FWtblactfld &row = wtblactfld; (void)row;

10669    if (p_wtblact)  {
10670        c_wtblactfld_Remove(*p_wtblact, row);// remove wtblactfld from index c_wtblactfld
10671    }
10672    wcli::FWfld* p_field = wcli::ind_wfld_Find(field_Get(row));
10673    if (p_field)  {
10674        c_wtblactfld_Remove(*p_field, row);// remove wtblactfld from index c_wtblactfld
10675    }
10676    ind_wtblactfld_Remove(row); // remove wtblactfld from index ind_wtblactfld
10677}

10719// --- wcli.FieldId.value.ToCstr
10720// Convert numeric value of field to one of predefined string constants.
10721// If string is found, return a static C string. Otherwise, return NULL.
10722const char* wcli::value_ToCstr(const wcli::FieldId& parent) {
10723    const char *ret = NULL;
10724    switch(value_GetEnum(parent)) {
10725        case wcli_FieldId_value            : ret = "value";  break;
10726    }
10727    return ret;
10728}
10729
10730// --- wcli.FieldId.value.Print
10731// Convert value to a string. First, attempt conversion to a known string.
10732// If no string matches, print value as a numeric value.
10733void wcli::value_Print(const wcli::FieldId& parent, algo::cstring &lhs) {
10734    const char *strval = value_ToCstr(parent);
10735    if (strval) {
10736        lhs << strval;
10737    } else {
10738        lhs << parent.value;
10739    }
10740}
10741
10742// --- wcli.FieldId.value.SetStrptrMaybe
10743// Convert string to field.
10744// If the string is invalid, do not modify field and return false.
10745// In case of success, return true
10746bool wcli::value_SetStrptrMaybe(wcli::FieldId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
10747    bool ret = false;
10748    switch (elems_N(rhs)) {
10749        case 5: {
10750            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(rhs[4])<<32)) {
10751                case LE_STR5('v','a','l','u','e'): {
10752                    value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_FieldId_value); ret = true; break;
10753                }
10754            }
10755            break;
10756        }
10757    }
10758    return ret;
10759}
10760
10761// --- wcli.FieldId.value.SetStrptr
10762// Convert string to field.
10763// If the string is invalid, set numeric value to DFLT
10764void wcli::value_SetStrptr(wcli::FieldId& parent, algo::strptr rhs, wcli_FieldIdEnum dflt) {
10765    if (!value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs)) value_SetEnum(parent,dflt);
10766}
10767
10768// --- wcli.FieldId.value.ReadStrptrMaybe
10769// Convert string to field. Return success value
10770bool wcli::value_ReadStrptrMaybe(wcli::FieldId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
10771    bool retval = false;
10772    retval = value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs); // try symbol conversion
10773    if (!retval) { // didn't work? try reading as underlying type
10774        retval = i32_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.value,rhs);
10775    }
10776    return retval;
10777}
10778
10779// --- wcli.FieldId..ReadStrptrMaybe
10780// Read fields of wcli::FieldId from an ascii string.
10781// The format of the string is the format of the wcli::FieldId's only field
10782bool wcli::FieldId_ReadStrptrMaybe(wcli::FieldId &parent, algo::strptr in_str) {
10783    bool retval = true;
10784    retval = retval && value_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent, in_str);
10785    return retval;
10786}

10791void wcli::FieldId_Print(wcli::FieldId& row, algo::cstring& str) {
10792    wcli::value_Print(row, str);
10793}

10835// --- wcli.TableId.value.SetStrptrMaybe
10836// Convert string to field.
10837// If the string is invalid, do not modify field and return false.
10838// In case of success, return true
10839bool wcli::value_SetStrptrMaybe(wcli::TableId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
10840    bool ret = false;
10841    switch (elems_N(rhs)) {
10842        case 9: {
10843            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
10844                case LE_STR8('x','2','d','b','.','U','s','e'): {
10845                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"r",1)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_TableId_x2db_User); ret = true; break; }
10846                    break;
10847                }
10848                case LE_STR8('x','2','d','b','.','u','s','e'): {
10849                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"r",1)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_TableId_x2db_user); ret = true; break; }
10850                    break;
10851                }
10852            }
10853            break;
10854        }
10855        case 11: {
10856            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
10857                case LE_STR8('w','c','l','i','d','b','.','P'): {
10858                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"age",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_TableId_wclidb_Page); ret = true; break; }
10859                    break;
10860                }
10861                case LE_STR8('w','c','l','i','d','b','.','W'): {
10862                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"act",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_TableId_wclidb_Wact); ret = true; break; }
10863                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"fld",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_TableId_wclidb_Wfld); ret = true; break; }
10864                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"tbl",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_TableId_wclidb_Wtbl); ret = true; break; }
10865                    break;
10866                }
10867                case LE_STR8('w','c','l','i','d','b','.','p'): {
10868                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"age",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_TableId_wclidb_page); ret = true; break; }
10869                    break;
10870                }
10871                case LE_STR8('w','c','l','i','d','b','.','w'): {
10872                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"act",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_TableId_wclidb_wact); ret = true; break; }
10873                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"fld",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_TableId_wclidb_wfld); ret = true; break; }
10874                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"tbl",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_TableId_wclidb_wtbl); ret = true; break; }
10875                    break;
10876                }
10877            }
10878            break;
10879        }
10880        case 12: {
10881            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
10882                case LE_STR8('w','c','l','i','d','b','.','W'): {
10883                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"wiki",4)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_TableId_wclidb_Wwiki); ret = true; break; }
10884                    break;
10885                }
10886                case LE_STR8('w','c','l','i','d','b','.','w'): {
10887                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"wiki",4)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,wcli_TableId_wclidb_wwiki); ret = true; break; }
10888                    break;
10889                }
10890            }
10891            break;

10990    }
10991    return ret;

10993
10994// --- wcli.TableId.value.SetStrptr
10995// Convert string to field.
10996// If the string is invalid, set numeric value to DFLT
10997void wcli::value_SetStrptr(wcli::TableId& parent, algo::strptr rhs, wcli_TableIdEnum dflt) {
10998    if (!value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs)) value_SetEnum(parent,dflt);
10999}
11000
11001// --- wcli.TableId.value.ReadStrptrMaybe
11002// Convert string to field. Return success value
11003bool wcli::value_ReadStrptrMaybe(wcli::TableId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
11004    bool retval = false;
11005    retval = value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs); // try symbol conversion
11006    if (!retval) { // didn't work? try reading as underlying type
11007        retval = i32_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.value,rhs);
11008    }
11009    return retval;
11010}
11011
11012// --- wcli.TableId..ReadStrptrMaybe
11013// Read fields of wcli::TableId from an ascii string.
11014// The format of the string is the format of the wcli::TableId's only field
11015bool wcli::TableId_ReadStrptrMaybe(wcli::TableId &parent, algo::strptr in_str) {
11016    bool retval = true;
11017    retval = retval && value_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent, in_str);
11018    return retval;
11019}
11020
11021// --- wcli.TableId..Print
11022// print string representation of ROW to string STR
11023// cfmt:wcli.TableId.String  printfmt:Raw
11024void wcli::TableId_Print(wcli::TableId& row, algo::cstring& str) {
11025    wcli::value_Print(row, str);
11026}

11028// --- wcli...SizeCheck
11029inline static void wcli::SizeCheck() {
11030}
11031
11032// --- wcli...StaticCheck
11033void wcli::StaticCheck() {
11034    algo_assert(sizeof(wcli::ftype_step_hook) == 8); // csize:wcli.ftype_step_hook
11035    algo_assert(sizeof(wcli::wclicmd_step_hook) == 8); // csize:wcli.wclicmd_step_hook
11036    algo_assert(sizeof(wcli::wtblact_step_hook) == 8); // csize:wcli.wtblact_step_hook
11037    algo_assert(_offset_of(wcli::FieldId, value) + sizeof(((wcli::FieldId*)0)->value) == sizeof(wcli::FieldId));
11038}
11039
11040// --- wcli...main
11041int main(int argc, char **argv) {
11042    try {
11043        lib_json::FDb_Init();
11044        algo_lib::FDb_Init();
11045        wcli::FDb_Init();
11046        algo_lib::_db.argc = argc;
11047        algo_lib::_db.argv = argv;
11048        algo_lib::IohookInit();
11049        wcli::ReadArgv(); // dmmeta.main:wcli
11050        wcli::Main(); // user-defined main
11051    } catch(algo_lib::ErrorX &x) {
11052        prerr("wcli.error  " << x); // there may be additional hints in DetachBadTags
11053        algo_lib::_db.exit_code = 1;
11054    }
11055    if (algo_lib::_db.last_signal) {
11056        algo_lib::_db.exit_code = 1;
11057    }
11058    try {
11059        wcli::FDb_Uninit();
11060        algo_lib::FDb_Uninit();
11061        lib_json::FDb_Uninit();
11062    } catch(algo_lib::ErrorX &) {
11063        // don't print anything, might crash
11064        algo_lib::_db.exit_code = 1;
11065    }
11066    // only the lower 1 byte makes it to the outside world
11067    (void)i32_UpdateMin(algo_lib::_db.exit_code,255);
11068    return algo_lib::_db.exit_code;
11069}
